title: broccoli or cauliflower with shrimp sauce
directions: In a saucepan, blend together cream cheese, milk and soup. Heat and stir until hot.
Add lemon juice.
Cook vegetables and pour sauce over.
Srpinkle with almonds and serve.

title: 5 can mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions in a large Dutch oven.
Drain.
Add soups, beans, tomatoes and enchilada sauce.
Simmer 20 minutes. Turn off heat.
Add chips and place into two casserole dishes. Top with cheese.
Put into hot oven long enough to melt cheese.

title: friendship salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in
boiling
water.
Chill
until thick but not set.
Combine
remaining
ingredients.	Add to Jell-O; mix well.
Pour into 9	x 13-inch pan.	Chill until set, about 1 hour.

title: cold cheese dip
directions: In a large saucepan, melt the cheese with milk.
Add remaining ingredients.
Serve cold.

title: eggplant salad
directions: Bake eggplant at 350° for 45 minutes or until soft; cool.
Cut lengthwise; scoop out insides and chop. In large bowl, mix eggplant with tomato, pepper, bell pepper and onion.
Add a touch of vinegar to taste. Chill. Serve on crackers or lettuce. Serves 4.

title: cheese cloud
directions: Trim crust from bread and arrange six slices in bottom of 12 x 8 x 2-inch greased baking dish.
Cover with cheese slices, then remaining bread slices.
Beat eggs, add milk, mustard, onion and seasonings. Pour over casserole and let stand at least one hour. This dish may be prepared the day before and refrigerated overnight if more convenient.
Bake at 325° for one hour.
Serve immediately.
Yields six servings.
(I triple the recipe for 20 people.)

title: oven beef stew
directions: Feel free to improvise; leftovers, frozen bags of "stew" veggies, different fresh veggies (turnips, parsnips, corn).

title: pecan balls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients, except powdered sugar.
Blend well.
Roll mixture into 1-inch balls; set on cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes; cool.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: timothy's white chili
directions: Place beans in heavy large pot.
Add enough cold water to cover by at least 3 inches and soak overnight.
Place chicken in heavy large saucepan.
Add cold water to cover and bring to simmer.
Cook until just tender, about 15 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Remove skin.
Cut chicken into cubes.
Drain beans.
Heat oil; add onions and saute about 10 minutes.
Stir in garlic, chilies, cumin, oregano, cloves and cayenne; saute 2 minutes.
Add beans and stock; bring to a boil.
Simmer about 2 hours.
Add chicken and 1 cup cheese to chili and stir until cheese melts. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Serve with remaining cheese, sour cream, salsa and cilantro.

title: carol's onion beef au jus
directions: In a Dutch oven, over medium-high heat, brown roast on all sides in oil; drain.
In a large skillet, saut onions in 2 teaspoons butter until tender.
Add water, soy sauce, soup mix, garlic and browning sauce (if desired).
Pour over roast.
Cover and bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Before slicing, return meat to pan juices. Slice bread in half lengthwise.
Cut into 3-inch sections.
Spread remaining butter over bread.
Place on a baking sheet.
Broil 4 to 6-inches from the heat for 2 to 3 minutes or until golden brown. Top with beef and onions.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Broil 4 to 6-inches from heat for 1 to 2 minutes or until cheese is melted. Serve with pan juices.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Mix well. Add eggs, one at a time. Add flour and milk alternately. Add flavoring. Cook at 350° until tested done.

title: buttermilk potatoes
directions: Quarter potatoes and boil until tender.
Drain and add oleo. Pour sauce over hot potatoes.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix apples with sugar and cinnamon and put in ungreased 10-inch pie plate.
Mix rest of ingredients adding eggs one at a time.
Spread this batter on top of apples.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: plain pound cake
directions: Mix.
Bake 1 hour at 325° or until toothpick comes out smooth.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Combine jello and hot water.
Stir in mayonnaise.
Add other ingredients.
Chill in mold until firm.

title: blackberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with 2 cups of boiling water.
Add 1/2 cup cold water after Jell-O is dissolved well.
Add blackberries and nuts. Let Jell-O set.

title: my grandmother's date pudding
directions: Mix brown sugar and water.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Add dates and boil several minutes more.
Mix cornstarch in small amount of cold water.
Add to boiling mixture.
Cook until thick and clear.
Pour into serving dish.
Cool and top with whipped cream and nuts.

title: south american beans and rice
directions: In deep pot, cook beans (no salt).
Reserve remaining liquid from cooked beans.
In a different deep pot, heat oil and garlic. Add strained cooked beans and salt and saute for 2 minutes.
Add reserved liquid.
Bring to boil for 5 minutes, mixing.
Simmer until slightly thick, about 15 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice on individual plates.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Heat sugar and vinegar together just until sugar is dissolved. Drain kraut.
Mix kraut, celery, onions, peppers and pimentos. Pour sugar-vinegar mixture over.
Place in covered bowl or jar. Great with black-eyed peas and other vegetables.

title: microwave deep dish apple pie
directions: Mix 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon; set aside. Combine apples, 1/2 cup sugar, the flour and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon or cloves in 1-quart casserole.
Cover.
Microwave at High (100%) until apples are tender and sauce is bubbly, 3 to 4 minutes.

title: blueberry tart
directions: Mix and press into 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350°.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in other ingredients. Spoon into small ovenproof dish sprayed with nonfat cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until bubbly.

title: quick cheese potatoes
directions: Grate the potatoes into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Over medium heat, cook cheese spread, shredded cheese, butter and whipping cream until cheeses are melted.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: old-fashioned fudge
directions: Mix together all ingredients, put on fire. Stir until dissolved, continue cooking until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Remove from fire, pour in bowl.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla, cool slightly.
Add 1 cup nuts and beat.
Pour into greased pan.

title: sun-maid raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Soak raisins in hot water; drain.
Cream the shortening with the sugar, then add beaten eggs and milk.
Combine with oatmeal and raisins; mix well.
Add flour sifted with soda, salt and cinnamon.
Beat thoroughly.
Drop into greased pans and bake for about 12 minutes in a moderate oven at 350° to 375°.
Makes about 3 dozen medium size cookies.

title: sour cream yellow squash
directions: Cook squash.
Drain.
Mash and drain again.
Combine with sour cream, 1/4 cup melted butter, onion, salt and pepper.
Place in casserole.

title: quiche
directions: Beat 4 eggs in bowl; add half and half and sprinkle of nutmeg (1/4 teaspoon).
Mix well.
Place ingredient (broccoli, etc.) in pie crust.
Cover with grated cheese.
Pour egg, half and half mixture on top.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool slightly before cutting.

title: welsh salad dressing
directions: Mix egg, sugar, salt and pepper together.
Add flour and mustard.
Keep it a nice smooth paste.
Add melted butter, milk, water and lastly vinegar.
Cook over low heat until as thick as cream.
Do not boil.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: cucumber salad(weight watchers)
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add vinegar.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 1-quart dish and refrigerate until set.
Serves 8.

title: venison meat loaf
directions: Simmer a hen in water seasoned with a few peppercorns, salt and
bay leaf.
When tender, cool in the broth.
After cooling, cut the breast into thin slices.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Set aside.
Bring milk, sugar and Crisco to boiling point.
Let this mixture cool to lukewarm.
Mix flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Add the yeast to the milk mixture after it has cooled to lukewarm.
Mix in the flour.
Knead all the mixed ingredients in flour, enough to make a workable dough.
Let rise in large pan for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: southern style yellow summer squash
directions: In a large skillet, cut up squash (skin and all if young squash).
Add margarine, salt and pepper and enough water to cover squash.
Bring to a boil.
Turn heat down and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Keep mashing with a fork and add water as it cooks out. When squash is the consistency of mashed potatoes and the liquid is gone, cook slowly turning with spatula until the squash is a golden brown.
Makes a small bowl full.
Very good and worth the effort.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Melt chocolate chips with butter or margarine over low heat, stirring constantly.
Cool slightly.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Gradually add sugar (about 3 minutes until pale yellow).
Add chocolate mixture. At low speed, beat in flour and baking powder.
Stir in walnuts (if desired); pour in pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Center remains soft.
Cool and cut.

title: cheesy meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium bowl; mix well.
Pack into a lightly greased 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.

title: penne al vodka(main dish for 2 to 3)
directions: Fry onion and shallots in olive oil until soft.
Add red pepper flakes.
Add tomatoes and chop them coarsely in pan.
Add vodka and simmer.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and refrigerate.

title: sweet-sour chicken
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet and stir-fry chicken until it turns white; season with salt.
Add green pepper and syrup drained from pineapple.
Bring to a boil and cook 3 minutes.
Mix cornstarch, sugar, soy sauce, vinegar and water and stir into chicken mixture.
Cook until thickened.
Stir in pineapple chunks and chow mein vegetables and heat through.
Makes five 1-cup servings.

title: harvey wallbanger cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together for 3 or 4 minutes.
Pour into a well-greased Bundt pan and bake for 45 minutes or until done at 350°.
No frosting needed.

title: broccoli supreme casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Add soup, mayonnaise and pecans.
Mix well.
Add onion and eggs.
Pour into a 1 1/2 or 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with cheese and top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes to 1 hour, depending on depth of casserole dish.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Preheat oven top 350°.
Combine all ingredients, except eggs and pecans, until well mixed.
Add eggs and stir until well combined; pour into a 3-quart casserole dish.
Top with pecans. Bake 1 hour.
Makes 10 servings, about 480 calories each.

title: sausage bread
directions: Thaw out yeast bread; roll out flat on large cookie sheet. Cook and drain sausage.
Mix together sausage, cheese and eggs. Spread on flat bread dough.
Roll like jelly roll; bake like package for bread says.

title: mrs. ruth's steamed cabbage
directions: Bring water (about 1 1/2-inches deep in pot) to a boil. Slice cabbage into shreds and add to boiling water. Cut bacon into small pieces and add. Salt and pepper to taste. Cover and steam until cabbage is tender. Remove from heat; drain excess water and chop to desired consistency.

title: old fashioned chocolate cake
directions: Boil oil, 3 tablespoons of cocoa, 1 stick butter, water. Mix in flour, sugar, salt, baking soda, eggs, buttermilk and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Bake in a 9 x 13 greased or sprayed pan at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: sherried fruit(very beautiful)
directions: Cut apple rings and pineapple slices in half.
Arrange fruit in layers in 2-quart casserole; set aside.
Melt butter in heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add flour and sugar, stirring until smooth, 1 minute.
Gradually add sherry.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Pour over fruit; cover and chill 8 hours.
Let come to room temperature.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: corned beef patties
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and fry in 3 tablespoons of cooking oil.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Dredge tomatoes in cornmeal. Fry tomato slices in hot oil in a skillet until browned, turning once. Drain well on paper towels. Sprinkle with salt, sugar and pepper. Serve hot. Yields 6 servings.

title: baked stew
directions: Brown stew meat (cut in cubes) in shortening.
Drain off fat. Add the mushrooms, tomato juice, onion soup and horseradish. Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Pare and quarter the potatoes. Place in bottom of a 2-quart casserole. Top with meat. Cover and bake until tender, about 1 1/2 hours. Stir 1 or 2 times during baking.

title: sangria
directions: Thoroughly chill all ingredients.
Pour the wine, brandy and Cointreau into a large punch bowl.
Stir orange and lemon juices with the sugar until sugar dissolves.
Add
to bowl and stir to blend.
Add ice cubes and soda and garnish with fruit slices. Makes about 100 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream oil, sugar and eggs. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well. Pour into greased and floured loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: peach streusel picnic cake
directions: Combine nuts, oats, brown sugar and butter; set aside.
Peel and pit peaches.
Cut into thin slices and toss with lemon juice; set aside.

title: noodle kugel
directions: Boil noodles; drain.
Mix together cheese, sour cream, butter, sugar, raisins and vanilla.
Add noodles.
Beat eggs until foamy and add to noodle mixture.
Pour into large Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: spinach dip
directions: Remove stems and tough bits from spinach.
Boil or steam until wilted; drain thoroughly and chop.
Combine spinach, sour cream, yogurt, parsley, green onions, salt and pepper in small bowl. Cover and refrigerate for at least 4 hours or overnight to blend flavors.

title: ground beef soup
directions: In soup pot, brown ground meat and onion.
Drain all fat.
Add remaining ingredients except parsley.
Cover and simmer 40 minutes until vegetables are tender, but still colorful.
Add parsley and simmer 5 more minutes.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: heath bar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add egg yolk and beat well. Stir in flour and vanilla, mixing well.
Spread in a greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with Heath bar.
Cool before cutting.

title: puffs
directions: Add butter to water and bring to boil. Stir in flour good. Remove from heat. Let mixture cool slightly. Add eggs one at a time, beating in each one well before adding another. Drop by spoonful (1/2 teaspoon) on greased pan about 2-inches apart. Shape into circle. The batter is higher in the center. Bake for 30 minutes at 400°. Reduce heat to 350° and bake 10 minutes more.

title: chocolate crackles
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs and shortening until well blended.
Add water if needed.
Shape dough into balls the size of walnuts. Roll in confectioners sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 48 cookies.

title: golden harvest soup
directions: Boil vegetables until done; drain and add enough milk to cover and margarine to your taste.
Lastly, add 1 pound of Velveeta. Heat until melted.

title: green punch
directions: Mix gelatin and water.
Add ginger ale and pineapple juice. Spoon sherbet into mixture.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Mix together.
Store in sealed jars.
To use, add 2 Tbsp. to 8 oz. boiling water.

title: hash brown skillet breakfast
directions: In electric skillet, fry bacon until crisp.
Drain bacon; reserve 3 tablespoons drippings in skillet.
Stir in potatoes, 1 teaspoon salt, the water and green pepper.
Cook potatoes, uncovered, at 300° until liquid is absorbed and bottom is golden brown; turn.
Reduce temp to 250°.
Sprinkle cheese over potatoes. Beat remaining ingredients; pour over potatoes.
Cover, cook until egg is done and potatoes are golden brown.
Crumble bacon, sprinkle on top.

title: big boy strawberry pie
directions: Boil water, sugar and cornstarch for 5 minutes to thicken. Add jello; let cool.
Add strawberries.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with whipping cream.

title: corn dogs
directions: Mix all ingredients except hot dogs and let set 30 minutes. Dip hot dogs in mixture and fry in olive oil 30 minutes.

title: coffee can bread
directions: Combine 1 cup of very warm milk, 1 cup sugar, butter and salt in a large bowl.
Stir until most of butter is melted.
Sprinkle yeast and the 1 teaspoon sugar into the remaining milk in a 1 cup measure; stir to dissolve.
Let stand to proof until bubbly and raised to double in volume (about 15 minutes).
Stir beaten eggs and yeast mixture into butter mixture.
Beat in about 5 cups flour, one cup at a time, until a soft pliable dough is formed. Place dough onto a well floured surface and knead from 10 to 15 minutes or until smooth and stretchy.
(Only use enough flour necessary to keep dough from sticking.) Place dough in a large, buttered bowl, turning to bring buttered side up and cover with a clean dish towel.

title: caramel cake
directions: Cook cake mix according to package for layer cake.
Mix brown sugar, margarine and milk together; cook until thickened.
Add nuts.
Spread over layers and over top.

title: teriyaki marinade for beef, chicken or pork
directions: Combine all ingredients in a jar. Shake.
Marinated pierced beef and pork at least 1 hour (skinned, pierced chicken, 3/4 hour). Baste with marinade while broiling.

title: delicious baked chicken
directions: Put rice in bottom of pan.
Put chicken pieces on top.
Mix soup and water.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: carol's ham pinwheels
directions: A day or so ahead of time combine the Roquefort cheese, cream cheese and butter.
Spread some on each ham slice.
Then roll up as for a jelly roll and wrap in waxed paper, Saran Wrap or foil. Refrigerate until needed.

title: melt-in-your-mouth chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove meat from bones and skin. Reserve broth.
Cut chicken into small pieces and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a saucepan, bring to a boil the broth and soups. Pour broth mixture over chicken and then put Veg-All on it.
In another bowl, combine flour, pepper, buttermilk and margarine. Mix thoroughly to form batter.
Spoon batter over top.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: apple-oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In medium bowl, combine oats, flour, whole-wheat flour, brown sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon. Mix well. Stir in raisins and apples. In a large bowl, mix egg, honey, oil and milk. Stir in dry ingredients. Mix to form a smooth batter. Drop batter onto ungreased baking sheet using a rounded teaspoonful of dough for each cookie. Leave 2-inches between each row. Press dough down to about 1 1/2-inch diameter.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: ginger crinkles (cookies)
directions: Mix flour, baking soda, cinnamon, ginger and cloves.
Beat butter and brown sugar in a large bowl with electric mixer until pale.
Beat in molasses and egg (mixture will look curdled). Gradually beat in flour mix until blended.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.

title: caramel candy *
directions: Mix sugar, butter and milk together.
Put on stove and bring to boiling point.
Cook for 8 minutes or until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Take off stove and mix marshmallows, caramel tips and nuts.
Pour into greased pan or dish and let cool.
Cut into blocks.

title: heavenly ice cream
directions: Cut up candy and add to condensed milk.
Heat over low heat, stirring constantly, until candy is melted.
Let cool slightly and add milk.
Add chocolate syrup as desired.
Freeze in electric ice cream freezer.

title: five flavors cold oven pound cake
directions: Mix butter, Crisco and sugar until it looks like ice cream (about 5 minutes).
Add eggs, one at a time.
Blend well after each addition.
Add flavorings and blend (about 2 minutes).
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add 1/2 of this mixture and milk and beat 2 minutes.
Add other 1/2 of ingredients and beat about 3 minutes.
Lightly grease and flour Bundt cake pan.
Pour mixture into pan.
Place in cold oven and turn oven to 325° and bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Let cool for 10 minutes in pan.

title: salsa
directions: Drain tomato juice into bowl.
Add green chiles, onions, garlic, lemon juice and chopped cilantro.
Chop tomatoes in blender just until chunky.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
I'm sure you could add jalapenos to this recipe although I didn't miss them.
Enjoy!

title: chicken with cashews, mushrooms and bean sprouts
directions: Place shiitakes in a heatproof bowl.
Add boiling water to cover and soak 20 minutes.
Remove mushrooms and squeeze dry.
Cut off and discard stems; slice caps.
In a medium bowl, combine soy sauce, sherry and sugar.
Add chicken and toss to coat.
Set aside.

title: malted milk cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat butter with an electric mixer on medium to high speed for 30 seconds. Add sugars and baking soda. Beat until combined, scraping sides of bowl occasionally. Beat in eggs, vanilla and malted chocolate until combined. Beat in as much of the flour as you can with the mixer. Stir in any remaining flour and the malted milk powder with a wooden spoon. Stir in chopped malted milk balls. Drop by rounded teaspoons 2 1/2-inches apart onto an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in a 375° oven about 10 minutes or until edges are firm. Cool on cookie sheet for 1 minute. Transfer cookies to a wire rack and let cool.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale until sugar is dissolved.
Freeze in cartons.
When ready to use, pour ginger ale over frozen mixture.

title: chili rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter; combine with rice and sour cream. Season to taste and mix well.
Spoon into 7 1/2 x 11-inch casserole dish.
Spread chili over mixture.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly (about 20 minutes).

title: spam hot dish
directions: Combine soup, milk, green pepper, onion, celery, pepper and cheese (cheese that melts) in a saucepan.
Heat until cheese is melted. Cook macaroni according to directions.
Cube Spam mix with all ingredients. Bake in oven at 325° for 1/2 hour.

title: hearty brunch bread
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a large bowl and stir well. Make a well in the center of the mixture.
Combine yogurt and egg whites.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fold in raisins and pecans.
Spoon batter into an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Yield: 16 servings.
Contains 103 calories, 3.3 protein, 1.9 fat, 19.4 carb. and 1 chol. per serving.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften in medium bowl.
Add onion. Begin adding milk by small amounts while beating at medium speed with mixer.
Add enough milk to achieve desired consistency. Great for vegetable platter or chips.

title: mama's boiled custard
directions: Put milk in double boiler and start heating.
Mix dry ingredients together and sift.
Add the 9 egg yolks (or whites too) and beat with 1/2 cup milk.
Strain into milk mixture.
Cook until thick, stirring almost all of the time.
Add whiskey to taste and strain into containers.

title: chocolate-coconut fudge
directions: Cook sugar, chocolate, milk and butter slowly until it forms a soft ball.
Cool.
Add vanilla and coconut.
Beat until stiff. Pour into buttered pan and cut in squares.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Blend eggs, milk and Bisquick with electric mixer.
Stir in chopped broccoli and 2 cups shredded cheese.
Pour into greased pan.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Sprinkle with 1 cup shredded cheese and return to oven until cheese melts.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and place in a casserole dish.
Top with crackers and drizzle with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until bubbly.

title: french apple pie
directions: Heat oven
Slice apples in greased pie plate. Sprinkle
spices
on top.
Beat remaining ingredients together and pour over apples.
(May add nuts, if desired.)

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Dump in the pie filling and smooth evenly over the bottom of pan. Next, dump in the pineapple and smooth.
Dump in the dry cake mix and then the nuts, again smoothing after each addition.
Place the butter pieces on top and bake for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer of crackers.
Mix chicken, soup and sour cream together. Pour over crackers.
Sprinkle layer of crackers on top.
Melt butter.
Pour over mixture.
Sprinkle poppy seed.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: jello punch
directions: Combine jello, boiling water and sugar to form base.
Add cold water and pineapple juice to base.
Add lemon juice.
Freeze in milk cartons or any containers to fit your needs.
Makes 1 gallon of base.
Thaw 2 hours before serving.
Add 4 quarts ginger ale to each 1/2 gallon of base.
Easily made dietetic by using sugar-free jello and Sweet 'N Low or Equal for sugar.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar, carrots and eggs; beat well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit tray
directions: Wash and slice fruit.
Arrange on serving tray.
Mix marshmallow cream and cream cheese together for dip.
Place in refrigerator until serving time.

title: dad's bran muffins
directions: Combine and stir well the flour, sugar, bran, salt, soda and orange rind.

Beat remaining ingredients. Combine dry and liquid ingredients with a few swift strokes. Fold in, before dry ingredients are entirely moist, the 1 cup nutmeats or 1 cup raisins and 1/2 cup mashed bananas.
GREASE TINS WELL. Bake 25 minutes in 350° oven. Yields 22 (2-inch) muffins.

title: beef-wine casserole
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and pour in 3-quart casserole.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Stir into beef mixture. Cook, uncovered, about 3 hours at 300° to 325°.
Stir occasionally. Add small amount of water if it gets thick before beef is tender. Serve over noodles, rice or with potatoes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350° to 375°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Last add chips, chocolate and nuts.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 11 to 12 minutes. Cookie will be slightly doughy when first removed from oven. Dough or cookies freeze well.

title: squash casserole
directions: Drain squash after it has been cooked.
Mash and add cheese, onion and mushroom soup.
Put in baking dish and sprinkle with cornbread crumbs over top and drizzle with butter.
Bake until brown and bubbly.

title: peach upside-down muffins
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add shortening, eggs and milk; mix until smooth.
In the bottom of 18 greased muffin cups, place 1 teaspoon butter and 1 tablespoon brown sugar.
Place in a 375° oven for 5 minutes. Arrange peaches in the muffin cups.
Fill each half full with batter.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes, or until browned.
Turn out of pans immediately.
Yields 1 1/2 dozen.

title: grandma's chocolate jumbos
directions: Combine ingredients, adding amount of flour needed to make mixture stiff enough for handling.
Roll out mixture and cut into circles.
Make a hole in the middle of each circle.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until dough tests done.
When cool, frost with white icing.
Yield: about 3 dozen cookies.

title: chicken primavera
directions: In a large skillet, saut the red pepper, mushrooms, onions and garlic in butter. Add the cream, basil, chicken and salt. Cook and stir until slightly thickened. Serve over pasta. Yields 4 servings.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine flour with salt and baking powder.
Use 2 knives or a pastry blender to cut in butter or substitute.
No piece of shortening should be larger than a pea. Add buttermilk and stir the mixture until it holds together. Briefly knead on lightly floured surface.
Roll to 1/2-inch thickness and cut into 2-inch rounds.
Place in ungreased 9-inch baking pan and bake at 400° about 12 to 15 minutes, or until the biscuits are nicely browned.
Serve immediately.
Makes about 1 dozen.

title: chicken continental
directions: Layer chipped beef in bottom of casserole.
Wrap each chicken breast with a strip of bacon.
Place on layered chipped beef. Blend sour cream and soup and pour over breasts.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pumpkin dream pie
directions: Combine the eggs, pumpkin, sugar, salt, cinnamon and evaporated milk, mixing thoroughly.
Set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, beat the Dream Whip, whole milk and vanilla.
Beat on high until the topping thickens and forms peaks.
Fold in the pumpkin mixture and spoon into pie crusts.
Pull off 1-inch strips of aluminum foil. Crimp the aluminum foil around the top edge of the pie crusts to protect from burning.
Place pies on heavy-duty cookie sheets and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes, or until knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
Remove the crimped foil edges from the pies, cover with the clear lids and refrigerate.
When completely cool, spread Cool Whip over pie and serve.

title: penna dutch chicken noodle corn soup
directions: Boil chicken breasts.
Cook and remove bone.
Reserve the chicken broth.
Add mushroom soup, canned chicken broth and corn to reserved broth along with cut up chicken.
Add noodles.
Add dry parsley, celery flakes and minced onions to taste.
Add chopped hard-cooked eggs.
If too rich, add water to taste. Yields 6 quarts.

title: almond poppy seed muffins
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease and flour a 12-cup muffin tin or line with paper liners.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all together and chill. Then serve.

title: escalloped chicken
directions: Cook chicken.
Cool.
Remove meat from bones.
Should make approximately 4 cups meat and 6 cups broth.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Place chicken on bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Layer onions and Veg-All.
Spread cream of chicken soup, then golden mushroom soup in top.
Mix flour (or Bisquick), milk and mayonnaise with a wire whisk.
Pour over top of soup.
Cook at 325° for about 1 hour. Turn oven up to brown top of pot pie, if you wish.

title: divinity
directions: Cook and stir sugar and corn syrup in a large saucepan, over medium heat until sugar is dissolved. Cook without stirring, until candy thermometer gets to 260° or hardball stage. Beat egg whites in a small mixer bowl until stiff peaks form. Transfer to a large mixer bowl, continue beating while pouring hot syrup in a thin stream over egg whites. Add vanilla. Beat until very stiff. Fold in nuts. Drop by Tbsp. on to wax paper to set.

title: walnut crunchy grahams
directions: Melt butter; add sugar.
Bring to boil and simmer gently 2 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add nuts.
Pour and spread over squares which have been laid on cookie sheet with sides.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool in pan 10 minutes, then remove immediately!
(Delicious, no calories!)

title: furniture polish
directions: Mix and shake well.
Apply with soft cloth and wipe dry.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Add buttermilk and yeast together. Put in a lightly covered bowl and place in refrigerator until morning.
Roll out the amount you need and cut into biscuits. Bake at 425° until done.
The dough will keep in refrigerator for 1 week.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Mix together in large bowl.
Line salad bowl with large leaves of lettuce.
Pour bean mixture in.
Garnish with fresh parsley. Chill and serve.

title: hot sandwiches
directions: Put onion and meat in pan and brown.
Then mix relish, ketchup, salt, pepper and cheese.
Then wrap in foil and store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Warm oven at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve.

title: pineapple cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat eggs until they're light and fluffy.
Add pineapple undrained, flour, white and brown sugar and baking soda.
Mix all ingredients well by hand, then stir in walnuts and spread the contents of the bowl evenly in an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.

Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean. After the cake cools, cover it with Cream Cheese Ginger Frosting, then sprinkle some additional chopped walnuts on top.

title: escalloped chicken
directions: Pull chicken from bones.
Break bread as for dressing.
Warm broth and soup together.
Mix well and place in a greased casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions; drain.
Add remaining ingredients, mix well.
Add enough salad dressing to coat pasta (usually 1/4 to 1/2 cup).
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: fluffy fruit gelatin
directions: Blend fruit with syrup at high speed until smooth.
Pour pureed fruit back into measuring cup and add enough syrup or water to make 1 cup.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; pour into a bowl (deep enough to whip gelatin later).
Stir in fruit puree. Cool.
Refrigerate gelatin mixture until it piles softly, but is not firm.
With cold beaters, whip the gelatin until foamy and doubled in volume.
Refrigerate until firm.
Can use other fruits. For fluffy fruit, fold in 1 cup of whipped cream.

title: hot water gingerbread
directions: Add water to molasses.
Add dry ingredients. Mix well, then add butter and beat.
Fill 8 x 8-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: lime salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese, drained pineapple, dry Jell-O and nuts. Stir in Cool Whip.	Pour into 13 x 9-inch dish.
Refrigerate to set.
Serve.

title: cranberry apple punch
directions: Heat water and sugar until sugar dissolves.
Cool. Refrigerate all ingredients.
Just before serving, mix in large punch bowl.
Makes 40 servings.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Stir together sugar, flour, egg yolks, milk and butter. Cook in double boiler until thick. Stir well. Put in baked pie shell.

title: peanut butter rice krispies treats
directions: Melt butter in 5-quart pan.
Add marshmallows, stirring constantly to keep from scorching.
Add peanut butter, stirring until melted.
Add Rice Krispies.
Stir until all is blended. Spread onto a cookie sheet and let cool.
Cut into squares.

title: corn relish
directions: Cook corn in 1 1/2 pints vinegar and 1 cup sugar for 20 minutes. Add rest of ingredients and cook for 20 minutes more. Can and seal.

title: impossible egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs until they are of a lemon color.
Add 1/2 of the sugar and flour.
Beat, adding remaining sugar and flour.
Pour into greased pan and bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: greenbean and corn casserolegroves, texas
directions: Drain can goods.
Mix corn, greenbeans, water chestnuts, cheese and sour cream.
Melt butter and crush crackers and mix in butter. Top casserole with this mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: haluska
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions and drain.
Melt butter in deep skillet.
Slice cabbage into thin strips.
Cut onion into rings approximately 1/8 inch thick.
Fry cabbage and onion until cabbage just begins to brown.
Volume will reduce as it cooks; stir constantly.
Add noodles, salt and pepper. Continue stirring until noodles are heated.
Serve immediately.

title: farmhouse asparagus pie
directions: Arrange cooked asparagus in bottom of pie shell.
Top with meat.
Scatter with Swiss cheese.
Beat together the eggs, flour, salt and cream; pour over asparagus.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes, or until filling is set.
Let set 10 minutes before cutting.

title: scalloped spinach
directions: Press spinach through coarse sieve and add remaining ingredients except crumbs.
Mix and pour into greased 1-quart baking dish.
Cover spinach mixture with crumbs and bake in moderate oven (350°) about 20 minutes or until crumbs get golden brown.

title: beer-cheese triangles
directions: Stir together Bisquick and cheese.
Make a well in center; pour beer all at once and mix.
Knead gently on lightly floured surface.
Roll and pat dough into 1-inch circle.
Cut into 10 wedges.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: blueberry bread
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar. Add blueberries and nuts.
Add eggs, mixed with milk and shortening.
Stir slightly.
Pour into waxed paper lined 9 1/2 x 5 1/4 x 2 3/4-inch loaf pan.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water to cover in medium-size saucepan for 8 to 10 minutes or until fork-tender.
Drain. Transfer potatoes to medium-size bowl.
Mash until smooth.
Add salmon, green onion, egg, parsley and ginger.
Stir to mix well. Shape salmon mixture into 8 equal size oval logs, using about 1/3 cup for each.
Spoon flour onto wax paper. Roll croquettes in flour to coat.
Pour oil into medium-size skillet to depth of 1/2-inch.
Heat oil to hot, but not smoking.
Working in batches, fry croquettes, turning occasionally, until golden and crusty on all sides.

title: goofy bars
directions: Put dry white cake mix in a bowl.
Put 2 eggs in a cup and add enough water to make 2/3 cup.
Add this to cake mix.
Also add brown sugar.
Beat lightly and spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle on chips and marshmallows.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: squash delight
directions: Mix squash, cheese, onion, pepper and soup.
Put 1/2 margarine in crumbs; line baking dish with crumbs.
Pour mixture over crumbs.
Put more crumbs on top.
Bake in oven at 400° for 30 minutes or more.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Put hash browns in a 9 x 13-inch pan, then cut up margarine and put on top of hash browns, then cut up cheese on top.
Mix soup and milk together and pour over top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Add salt to egg whites.
Beat until stiff, then add sugar. Fold in nuts, corn flakes, coconut and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonful onto brown paper on cookie sheet two inches apart. Bake at 250° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Keep on paper until cool and they will hold shape and remove easily.

title: mexican mushroom soup
directions: Heat oil in large saucepan.
Add mushrooms, onion and garlic. Cover and cook 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir in cheese.
Serve with additional Pace picante sauce.
This is a very hot spicy soup.
Bill recommends Rolaids afterwards.

title: kraut chocolate cake
directions: Thoroughly cream margarine with sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients; add alternately with water to egg mixture.
Stir in kraut.
Put into greased and floured baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 2 (8-inch) round or square cakes.

title: corned beef hash casserole
directions: In a small skillet, cook green pepper and onion in butter until limp but not browned.
Add sour cream, mustard, cayenne and black pepper, mixing well.
Empty corned beef hash into a medium bowl.
Add sour cream mixture and blend thoroughly.
Add a dash of salt if desired.
Transfer mixture into large shallow casserole. Bake at 400° about 25 minutes until bubbly and lightly browned. Arrange egg slices on top.
Serves 4.

title: salmon and potato puff
directions: Drain fish, flake with fork and remove bones.
Saute celery and parsley in melted butter.
Combine with salmon, potatoes and seasonings; add beaten egg yolks and beat mixture until light. Fold in well beaten egg whites.
Pile into greased baking dish. Bake in 350° oven 1 hour or until set in center and lightly browned.
If baked in ramekins or custard cups, it will be light, fluffy and attractive for luncheon dish.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Brown sausage in frying pan; drain.
Mix sausage and cream cheese together in bowl.
Place mushroom caps in baking dish. Fill caps with sausage mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: In 2-quart casserole, add stuffing, squash, soup, onion, butter and sour cream.
Sprinkle some crumbs over top and bake at 350° until bubbly around the edges.

title: biscuits and stuffed olives
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients together until soft.
Make a ball in palm of hand, stick thumb in to make an indenture; put in a very large stuffed olive, work mix around to cover olive.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Serve hot.
(Freezes well before cooking.)

title: pie crust
directions: Sift flour and salt.
Cut in Crisco until crumbly, then stir in combined milk and vinegar.
Turn onto lightly floured board or pastry cloth.
Knead a few times.
Place in pie pan and flute with fingers.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Remove skin and large bones from salmon and mash.
Melt butter in milk.
Add bread crumbs and seasonings.
Combine with fish. Add well beaten eggs.
Pack into a well buttered baking dish. Place in pan of hot water.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Turn onto a platter and cover with white sauce.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Put fruit in bowl with a little flour just to coat fruit. Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten egg and vanilla; stir.
Add fruit and applesauce; stir.
Sift flour with all spices and baking soda (at least 3 times) and add; stir.
Grease and flour pan.
Bake at 350° in 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 Pyrex pan 30 to 40 minutes, or in 11 x 7-inch Pyrex pan for 40 to 45 minutes.
Stand at least one day before cutting.
My husband's favorite!

title: easy peach pie
directions: Pour both cans of peaches into a 9 x 13-inch pan, which has been greased.
Sprinkle jello evenly over peaches.
Spread cake mix over jello.
Pour water over cake mix and dot pats of margarine over the top.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Heat oil.
Mix and knead ingredients 12 times.
Fry 2 to 3 minutes.
Makes 12 wedges.

title: ham pinwheels
directions: Blend cream cheese, onion, horseradish and Worcestershire sauce until smooth.
Separate slices of ham and turkey; lay one slice of turkey on top of each slice of ham.
Spread with cheese mixture.
Roll and fasten with toothpicks.
Chill.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Makes about 50 pinwheels.

title: pecan crunch fudge
directions: Combine brown sugar, margarine and milk in a large saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick and at soft ball stage (238° on candy thermometer).
Remove from heat; stir in butterscotch morsels and marshmallow cream.
Beat until smooth and begins to cool.
Stir in chopped nuts, brickle chips and vanilla. Spread in buttered pan; cut in squares when cool.

title: candy kisses
directions: Beat the first 3 ingredients until fairly stiff and gradually add the sugar. Bake at 300° on brown paper or foil on cookie sheet for 55 minutes. Turn turn off oven and let set 2 hours or more.

title: tuna spread dip
directions: Combine all ingredients together in mixer.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Heat 1 1/4 cups water to boiling.
Set in a pan of ice until very cold.
Crumble 2 cakes (or 2 packages) yeast into 1/4 cup lukewarm water.
Stand 10 minutes.
Now add iced water.
Beat until blended:
sugar, salt, eggs and 3 cups flour.
Melt shortening (cool).
Stir in 3 more cups flour.
Knead.
Flatten dough out into a thin sheet.
Place between 2 towels.
Lay directly on refrigerator shelf.
Chill thoroughly.
Put dough in regular greased bowl.
Cover and store in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: citrus trifle(absolutely delicious!)
directions: Squeeze juice from lemons.
Grate peel and squeeze juice from orange.
Reserve 1 teaspoon grated orange peel for garnish.
In large bowl with mixer at low speed, beat cream cheese, confectioners sugar, lemon extract, lemon juice and remaining grated orange peel until blended.
In another large bowl, with mixer at medium speed, beat heavy or whipping cream until stiff peaks form.
With rubber spatula, fold whipped cream into cream cheese mixture.
With pastry brush, brush flat side of ladyfingers with orange juice.
Line bottom and side of 3-quart glass souffle dish or trifle bowl with half of ladyfingers so that rounded side of ladyfingers are against side of dish.
Spoon half of cream cheese filling into souffle dish.
Arrange remaining ladyfingers around side of souffle dish slightly overlapping bottom layer, if necessary.
Place any extra ladyfingers over filling.
Spoon remaining cream cheese filling into souffle dish.
To garnish, arrange 1 strawberry unsliced in center.
Slice remaining strawberries lengthwise in half.
Garnish as desired.
Sprinkle reserved orange peel over top.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours to blend flavors.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Grease casserole with butter.
Roll crackers into crumbs.
Put 1/2 of crackers into bottom of greased casserole. Add can of tuna; spread even over crackers.
Dot with butter; add about 1/2 of soup, then add remaining crackers and rest of soup.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle a little pepper on top.
Add enough milk to moisten crackers a little. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until top is nice and brown.

title: parmesan dijon chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix yogurt and mustard.
Spread on chicken pieces with brush (both sides).
Mix cheese and crumbs.
Dip chicken parts in crumb mixture.
Coat both sides.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake 1 hour.
Low-fat.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix instant vanilla pudding; spread over mixture.
Top with Cool Whip.
Garnish with chopped cherries and pecans.

title: pineapple chicken salad
directions: Place chicken breasts in pot; cover with broth.
Cover and simmer until tender, about 45 minutes.
Cool.
Save broth for future use or as soup.
Skin chicken and dice into bite-size pieces.
Toast almonds in 325° oven until golden; cool.
Combine chicken, fruit, almonds and mayonnaise.
Grind pepper over it. Mix well.
Refrigerate.
Makes about 2 1/4 quarts or nine 1 cup servings.

title: butterfinger homemade ice cream
directions: Beat candy with a hammer or process in food processor. Combine both milks and Cool Whip; stir in candy and add to churn, then fill to the fill line with chocolate milk.

title: casserole sauce mix(substitute for 1 can cream of chicken soup; low sodium, low-fat.)
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Store in airtight container and keep in refrigerator.
Makes 3 cups of mix = 9 cans of soup.

title: dumplings
directions: Measure flour, baking powder and salt into a bowl.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender until mixture looks like meal. Stir in the milk, sweet or buttermilk.
Drop or roll out dough and drop in boiling broth.

title: hot chocolate mix #2
directions: Use to taste in hot water.

title: hot cheese biscuits
directions: Cream butter; add flour, grated cheese and red pepper. (Mixture is very stiff and short.)
Chill.
Roll on waxed paper and cut.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: 4 layer butterscotch dessert
directions: Melt margarine and add brown sugar, flour and pecans. Press ingredients into 9 x 13 glass baking dish. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes. Let cool.

title: chicken and rice
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, stir the rice, onion soup mix, mushroom soup and water.
Dip chicken in milk and salt and place, skin side up, over rice mixture.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: strawberry cream cheese pie
directions: Arrange strawberries (whole) in bottom of
pie crust. Gradually add sugar to cream cheese in a bowl; beat well.
Add vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon into shell over strawberries. Chill at least 3 hours.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Drizzle with strawberry glaze.
Garnish with berries (optional).

title: beef burgundy
directions: Brown the round steak in oil.
Add the mushrooms, onion, broth, tomato paste and wine.
Simmer, covered, 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Cook noodles according to package.
Serve beef and sauce over the noodles.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix together with milk.
Drop into hot oil after making batter into small balls.
Add more milk if batter is too thick.

title: cheese ball
directions: Spread butter in a large bowl.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes and chopped pecans.
In another large bowl, mix together cheese, mayonnaise, cream cheese, rooster sauce, minced onion and adding last the whipped cream.
Roll mixture in buttered bowl to shape. Sprinkle more parsley flakes and chopped pecans on the ball.
Chill 2 hours.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain the grease.
Place in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Pour pizza sauce over meat.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Mix biscuit mix, milk and eggs together; pour over top of meat.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix, water, eggs and oleo, blending until smooth. Pour 1/2 of the batter into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan and bake at 350°
for 15 minutes.
Melt the caramels and milk over low heat.
Remove cake from oven.
Pour melted caramels over cake (do not spread to the edge).
Sprinkle with the chocolate chips and pecans.
Top with remaining batter.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and serve with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple and mix all together.
Pour in dish to freeze.

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; debone and dice.
Cook broccoli per package instructions; drain.
Place broccoli in baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Place diced chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, curry powder and cheese.
Pour over chicken.
Mix bread crumbs and melted butter.
Sprinkle over top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: lazy pie
directions: Melt oleo.
Set aside to cool; mix flour, sugar and milk. Pour mixture over butter.
Mix 2 1/2 cups fruit (fruit can be doubled).
Also add 1/2 teaspoon almond extract to the fruit. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: mexican party dip
directions: Spread refried beans on ovenproof plate and warm.
Mash avocado with a little salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Over beans, add in layers chopped onion, chopped tomato, avocado mixture, picante sauce, sour cream and top with Cheddar.
Serve with nachos or Doritos.

title: three day coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed.
Cool.
Split layers.
Mix coconut, sugar and sour cream; set aside 3/4 cup.
Use the remaining portion for filling between layers.
For frosting, add the 3/4 cup of coconut mixture to the Cool Whip.
Frost the entire cake. Cover loosely.
Place in refrigerator and leave for 3 days before cutting.

title: easy bread
directions: In large pan (Dutch oven) combine 3 c. flour, sugar, salt & yeast. Melt oleo in hot water, then add milk. Mix liquid mixture into flour mixture. Work in remaining 6 c. flour.
(do all kneading in the pan.) Set in oven that has been heated to 150° and turned off. Let rise to double in size.
Knead down and form into three loaves. Bake at 350°-375° for 25-30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Saute chicken tenders in frying pan; cook for about 20 minutes.
Set aside.
Mix other ingredients together; pour over chicken.
Let simmer over low heat for about 10 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Separate leaves from cabbage and preboil them in salt water. Mix all the ingredients except cabbage leaves in a large bowl. Line the bottom of a 9 x 9-inch pan with cabbage leaves.
Spoon a layer of the meat mixture onto the leaves, then layer again with cabbage leaves and meat mixture.
Top with cabbage leaves.
Cover the pan with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Tastes like cabbage rolls, but easier to prepare.

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add milk and flour alternately, mixing well.
Add flavoring and nuts.

title: babka
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Heat milk with butter and sugar. Add half the flour, eggs and vanilla.
Add rest of flour.
Let rise until double in quantity;
knead and let rise again.
Wash with milk and egg on top.
Bake at 375°
for 10 minutes; then at 325°
for 50 minutes.

title: curried pear and cheese salad
directions: Drain pears.
Arrange on lettuce.
Mix together remaining ingredients and drop by spoonfuls on pear halves.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: beef and potato casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion together.
Salt and pepper to taste. Layer beef and potatoes (raw) in a baking dish and cover with soup.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops in large skillet in small amount of oil.
Add rice, consomme and water.
Over each pork chop, place a slice of onion, a slice of tomato and a slice of pepper.
Cover; bring to a boil, then simmer about 40 minutes.
Uncover last 5 minutes.

title: lemon apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, sugar, oil and 1 cup apricot nectar according to package directions on mix.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake as directed.

title: potato dumplings
directions: Wash, peel and cook potatoes for about 30 minutes or until they are tender when pierced with a fork.
Drain.
Dry potatoes by shaking pan over low heat.
Mash potatoes thoroughly.
Set aside to cool completely.
Meanwhile, melt butter in a large heavy skillet on low heat.
Cut bread into 1/4 to 1/2 inch cubes.
Put cubes in skillet and stir until all sides are coated and browned.
Set aside.
Bring water and salt to boil in a large heavy saucepan. When potatoes are cool, whip egg in until fluffy; add a mixture of 1 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Add the cornstarch and half of the flour.
Add enough of the remaining flour to make a soft dough. Break off pieces of the dough and shape into balls about 1 inch in diameter.
Poke a bread cube into center of each ball.
Drop dumplings into the boiling water.
Cook only one layer of dumplings at a time.
Cook them 5 minutes, or until they rise to the waters surface.
Carefully remove them with a slotted spoon so they drain over the water.
Put dumplings into a warm serving dish and serve with melted butter.
Makes about 18 dumplings.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream together cream cheese, oleo and sugar.
Mix pudding mix with milk.
Mix cream cheese mixture and pudding mixture together. Fold in Cool Whip.
Process Oreo cookies in food processor. Layer mixture and then cookies in a glass bowl or flower pot until all gone, ending with cookies on top.
You can put gummy worms on top.

title: potato salad, my way
directions: Peel and chop potatoes.
Cook until tender; drain.
In a large bowl, combine potatoes with remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle top with paprika.
You can garnish with parsley and boiled egg slices. Serve while warm.

title: butternut pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light.
Add eggs.
Beat for 1 minute at high speed.
Add 1 cup of flour, beating for 1 minute. Add rest of flour alternately with milk.
Add flavoring.
Mix well. Bake 1 hour at 325° and then turn up heat to 350° for 10 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cheesy banana pepper roll-ups
directions: Split peppers and remove seeds.
Wash.
Melt cheese.
Mix cheese with rice; stuff each pepper with rice and cheese mix.
Roll each biscuit very thin (1 biscuit for large pepper, 1/4 biscuit for small pepper).
Wrap each up and place in greased baking dish. Pour tomatoes over and bake in 400° oven until biscuit is flaky.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and pumpkin.
Sift flour, spices and salt together and add to egg mixture.
Mix water and oil in and fold in nuts.
Bake in 1/2 loaf pan or coffee can, greased and floured at 325° for 1 hour or longer.
Makes 4 (1/2 loaf) pans.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook egg noodles.
Drain.
Add cream of chicken soup mix in chicken, salt and pepper.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix together all the ingredients above.
Spray muffin tins with Pam, filling 2/3 full.
Bake in a 450° preheated oven for 25 minutes or until done.
Makes 18 large muffins.

title: steak supper in a foil package
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Tear off 2 feet of heavy-duty aluminum foil 18-inches wide; lay in baking pan.
Place meat in center. Mix mushroom soup and onion soup mix; spread over meat.
Top with vegetables.
Sprinkle vegetables with water.
Fold foil over and seal securely to hold in juices.
Bake 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: quick company chicken
directions: Combine margarine and cracker crumbs, blending well.
Spoon 1/2 of crumbs into shallow 2-quart casserole.
Cover with chicken. Combine sour cream, soup and broth.
Add salt and pepper.
Blend well and pour over chicken.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Cover casserole and bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes. Yields 6 servings.

title: sugar cream pie
directions: Mix flour with sugar.
Pour cream over mixture.
Add butter on top.
Bake in an unbaked pie shell at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. This is an old recipe like we used to carry to school.

title: smokies
directions: Mix together in crock-pot and heat for about 30 minutes.
Great for parties.

title: aunt dorothy's vegetable soup
directions: Brown and break up meat.
Add the next 12 ingredients.
Cook until vegetables are partially done, then add remaining ingredients.
Cook until vegetables are at crispness you prefer. Sometimes instead of potatoes, you can add a handful of broken spaghetti, rice, barley or macaroni.
Cook in a large Dutch oven as full as it will go.
Goes great with corn muffins.

title: prune cake
directions: Blend sugar and oil.
Add eggs.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla, prunes and nuts last. Pour into greased 8-inch pans.
Bake 45 minutes at 300°.
Ice with Caramel Icing.

title: egg-in-a-hole
directions: Tear an egg size hole in the middle of the bread.
Grease the top of the hot tin-can stove with margarine.
Lay bread on the stove and break the egg into the hole of the bread.
Cook until egg begins to harden on the bottom and bread turns brown underneath. Insert pancake turner under to peek; put more margarine on the stove top.
Turn over the bread and egg to cook the other side. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Remove to a plate to eat.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Combine meat, rice, onion and seasoning.
Shape into small balls.
Mix tomato soup with water and heat.
Drop meatballs in and cover; cook slowly for about 60 minutes.
Serves 6 people.

title: venison soup
directions: Simmer meat in salted water for 2 1/2 hours, skimming every so often.
Let broth stand overnight until fat congeals.
Remove fat. Add vegetables, juice and seasonings.
Simmer slowly for about 2 hours.

title: bake while you sleep cookies(all night cookies)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium size bowl, with electric mixer at high speed, beat egg white and salt until soft peaks form.
Beat in sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time until stiff and glossy.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop mixture by rounded teaspoon onto foil covered cookie sheet.
Place in oven.
Close door.
Turn oven off.
Do not open door.
Leave cookies in oven overnight.
Remove from foil; store in airtight container.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: english muffin snacks
directions: Beat cheese spread, butter, salt and garlic powder until smooth.
Then add mayonnaise and crab meat.
Mix all very good. Cut muffins in half.
Spread mixture on the 12 halves.
Cut each half into 6 pieces like a pie.
You will have 72 small pieces. Freeze on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until they puff up and are a little brown.
Serve hot.
Kids like these.
Don't bake too long.

title: coffee and spice drops
directions: Combine shortening, brown sugar and eggs.
Stir in cold coffee.
Sift together the flour, soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon. Add to coffee mixture.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake until set, just until when touched lightly by finger.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: hawaiian beef
directions: Brown beef in shortening.
Add onion, garlic, salt, ginger. Drain pineapple.
Add water to juice to make 2 cups liquid.
Add 1/2 cup liquid to meat and simmer until tender.
Combine beef bouillon cube, molasses, brown sugar, cornstarch with remaining liquid.
Add to beef.
Simmer until thickened.
Arrange green beans and pineapple on top.
Serve with cooked rice.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into small cubes.
Cut onions into small pieces.
Melt bacon grease and pour over potatoes and onions.
Add salt and pepper and mix together.
Cook in microwave for 30 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: eggs and rice
directions: Mix well and cook 15 to 20 minutes on low heat. Serve hot. Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: tasty smelt
directions: Rinse cleaned smelts thoroughly; wipe dry.
Season the smelts with salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Cover; allow them to stand for 15 minutes.
Dip the smelts in cream or milk, then roll them in cornmeal.
Fry the smelts gently in butter, until the fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Place the cooked smelts on a platter.

title: quick and easy cheese cake
directions: Blend together thoroughly Cool Whip and cream cheese.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: fresh vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together and chill before serving with cauliflower, celery, carrot sticks, zucchini, cucumber slices or any other fresh vegetable of your choice.
Real good.

title: pineapple ham skewers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove outer skins from garlic head. Slice off tops where it comes to a point.
Melt butter and oil in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Remove from heat and add wine.
Add potatoes and garlic.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours, basting every 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: peach and pineapple conserve
directions: Combine ingredients and cook until mixture is thick and clear, stirring to prevent burning.
Pour into cans and seal.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill. Serve as a dressing for fruit salad or as a dip for raw fruit slices.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Salt and pepper chicken only.
Mix soup, water, mushrooms, onion soup mix and rice together.
Put chicken in baking pan and pour soup mixture over top.
Top with butter and almonds.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: almond joy type bar
directions: Line cavities with milk chocolate and allow to dry.
Place almond in mold and top with coconut paste.
Cap mold with chocolate.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Press rolls in ungreased pizza pan with points toward center. Top with sausage, potatoes, cheese and egg mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sweet red pepper crab bisque
directions: In a 6-quart saucepan, heat oil over medium heat.
Add next 8 ingredients; cook, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are tender.
Add tomatoes; stir until well blended.
Stir in cream, sherry and rum.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Stir in lemon juice and crab; cook 5 to 10 minutes longer or until crab is heated through.
Serve warm.
(Sherry is strong flavored; adjust to taste.)
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, Milnot, cocoa, butter and salt and boil 1 to 3 minutes.
Remove from fire.
Add coconut, peanut butter, nuts and dry oats.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper until set.

title: "they love it, but don't tell them it's cabbage"
directions: Chop or shred fine the cabbage; place it in a shallow casserole.
Pour milk over cabbage until most of the cabbage is covered.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, covered, and for 1/2 hour, uncovered.

title: cold chicken with herbed mayonnaise
directions: Pound the chicken breasts until thin.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Coat chicken with egg and cover with bread crumbs.
Place on waxed paper and let dry for about 20 minutes.
In a large frying pan, heat the oil and brown the chicken on both sides. Drain on paper towel and let chill.
Mix all other ingredients in a small bowl, except the lemon.
Season to taste.
Serve chicken finished with the sauce and garnished with lemon wedges.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Add hot water to onion soup mix.
Stir, add rice, butter, salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Place frozen broccoli in greased 2 qt. casserole dish.
Pour rice mixture over broccoli.
Cover with lid and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Boil raisins, water and 3/4 cup of sugar until raisins puff. Combine 1/4 cup of sugar, salt, cornstarch and beaten egg yolks. Add to raisin mixture and then mix in the sour cream.
Cook until thick.
Add vanilla and pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue and brown lightly.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Mix baking mix, milk and cheese until a soft dough. Beat vigorously for 30 seconds. Drop dough by spoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Heat oven to 450°.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Mix oleo and garlic powder and brush over warm biscuits before removing from cookie sheet. Serve warm. Makes 10 to 12 biscuits.

title: peach jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in pineapple juice.
Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: falafel
directions: Drain and mash chick peas (also known as garbanzo beans) and mix this with all other ingredients.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Heat 2 to 3 inches oil and drop mix by teaspoonfuls to light brown. Remove and drain.
Heap them into pita bread with salad or a generous garnish of salad dressing and tahini sauce.
You can also spear on toothpicks and dip in yogurt.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp, and stir in flour and blend.
Add onions, vinegar, salt, pepper, sugar and water.
Cook 5 minutes. Pour over hot potatoes and mix lightly.
Serve while warm.

title: hot pepper relish
directions: Chop peppers fine in a food processor.

title: coconut (philly) fudge balls
directions: Gradually add sugar to softened cream cheese, mixing until blended.
Stir in vanilla and salt.
Shape into balls and roll in shredded coconut.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Dice onion; simmer in water until dry.
Add hamburger; crumble as much as possible.
Cook until done.
Use fork and crumble hamburger as much as you can while cooking.
Drain all water off. Add salt, pepper, brown sugar and ketchup.
Cook a few minutes; taste to see if it needs more salt, pepper or ketchup.
Serve on hot dog and bun, or just eat on hamburger bun.

title: souper burgers
directions: Brown hamburger with onion in skillet.
Drain grease.
Add mustard, catsup and soup.
Stir together.
Heat until mixture bubbles.
Stir, reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Brown hamburger buns and top with souper burger mixture.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt and cocoa.
Add egg, milk and butter. Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Pour into a baked crust, cover with meringue and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: crustless coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Blend in sugar and flour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased pie pans.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30-4 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
It makes it own crust.

title: nutty o's
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease a jelly roll pan.
Heat sugar, syrup, oleo and salt until sugar is dissolved, about 5 minutes. Stir over cereal and nuts in a large bowl until well coated. Spread mixture in pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Loosen mixture with metal spatula.
Let stand until firm, about 1 hour. Store in airtight container.

title: coca-cola bing cherry dessert
directions: Drain fruit; reserve juice.
Measure juice, using 2 cups. Heat to boiling; dissolve Jell-O.
Use remaining juice and Coca-Cola to 2 cups.
Add; stir in.
Cool until syrupy.
Cut cherries when gelatin has begun to set.
Stir in fruit and nuts. Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip with beaters. Spread on set Jell-O.

title: many way meatballs(serves 4)
directions: Blend soup and water.
(If you use Cheddar cheese soup, it should be stirred to smooth first.)
Measure out 1/4 cup to combine with beef, bread crumbs, onion, parsley and egg.
Shape mixture into meatballs.
Brown meatballs; pour off excess drippings.
Add remaining soup mixture.
Cover; cook over low heat for 15 minutes.
Stir often.

title: tennessee potato salad
directions: Boil unpeeled potatoes; cool, peel and dice.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Add mayonnaise, salt and pepper to taste.

title: dad's rice pudding
directions: Combine water, milk, margarine and sugar in a 4-quart saucepan.
Bring to a low boil.
Add rice.
Adjust heat to maintain low boil for 40 to 45 minutes, stirring often.

title: apple pudding
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add beaten egg.
Mix well.
Stir in apples and all dry ingredients; add nuts.
Bake in buttered casserole at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve hot.
Top with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: barbecue cocktail franks
directions: Mix first four ingredients in slow cooker and add wieners to mixture. Heat on high in slow cooker until thoroughly heated, then cook on low until ready to serve.
(If you double the recipe, do not add more vinegar.)

title: marshmallow creme
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients to soft ball stage (almost 250°). While this is cooling, put the following in a large bowl:
1/2 cup Karo (at room temperature) and the egg whites; beat slowly until mixed, then beat hard until fluffy.
Beat in first mixture in a fine stream.
When all mixed, add the vanilla.
Beat hard for 3 minutes.
May add the jello (any flavor).

title: jambalaya
directions: Heat oleo; add sauteed onion and meats.
Add tomatoes.
Add rest of vegetables.
Add seasonings.
Mix well and cook slowly for 1 hour.

title: parmesan glazed walnuts(snack)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spread nuts in shallow baking pan and bake 10 minutes.
Mix butter and salt; toss lightly with nuts. Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake 3 to 4 minutes.

title: pickadillo
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Cover barely with water; simmer 30 minutes.
Add remainder of ingredients and cook down.
Serve warm with large Fritos or tortilla chips for dipping.

title: fabulous fondue
directions: Rub inside of fondue pot with garlic clove. Discard garlic. Set heat at simmer setting.
Melt butter. Add flour and stir until mixture thickens. Add milk gradually.
Stir constantly until thick. Add cayenne pepper and garlic salt.
Add cheese, 1/4 cup at a time.
Stir in a figure eight motion until cheese melts. Add wine and stir until blended.
Heat 10 minutes to blend flavors. French bread and you're ready to impress.
Happy eating.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Bake for 80 minutes in a 325° oven.
Use a large greased and floured Bundt pan.
I sometimes make six cupcakes and pour the rest in the Bundt pan.
Cupcakes cook in about 20 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Add yogurt and orange jello; stir well.
Add cottage cheese; mix well.
Chill.

title: country pasta with mozzarella
directions: Cook rigatoni according to package directions.
Drain. Meanwhile, in 10-inch skillet, cook bacon until browned.
Add broccoli and garlic.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until broccoli is crisply tender (4 to 5 minutes).
Add rigatoni and remaining ingredients, except parsley.
Continue cooking, until cheese is melted (3 to 5 minutes).
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: millionaire candy
directions: In a double boiler melt oleo and caramels; add vanilla and nuts.
When it is cool enough, butter hands and roll mixture into small balls.
Refrigerate until firm.
Dip balls into melted paraffin and Hershey bars.

title: jumbalia
directions: Mix all ingredients in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cover and cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Don't remove lid or stir while cooking. Add Tony Chachere's spice seasoning until salty.
Serve with salad and warm Italian bread.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat milk and pudding until it thickens.
Fold in sour cream and orange juice.
Chill before serving.
Use all your favorite fruits for dipping.
(Hint:
If you want to use apples, after slicing soak in any citrus juice.
This will keep them from turning brown for hours.)

title: old-fashioned caramel applesauce spice cake
directions: Butter sides and bottom of Dutch oven.
Mix all ingredients (except pineapple) in saucepan and cook until slightly thick.
Pour in bottom of Dutch oven evenly.
Place layer of pineapple on top of mixture.
Place cherry in center of each pineapple.

title: king crab dip
directions: Drain crab meat; slice fine.
Combine with all other ingredients.
Allow to chill for 1 hour.
Serve with chips or crackers.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: rhonda's nachos el grande
directions: Spread a layer of chips on an ovenproof platter.
Sprinkle some Cheddar cheese over the chips, then add the hamburger on top of that.
Have refried beans heated in a glass measuring cup (with some water added to make it a little soupier) and pour or spoon over the hamburger.
Add remaining cheese on top.
Place platter in oven on broil; watch until cheese is bubbly and chips turn light brown.
Remove; quickly sprinkle tomatoes and jalapenos evenly.
Dot the entire top with sour cream and guacamole.

title: ritz pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff, gradually adding sugar.
Add vanilla, nuts and Ritz crackers.
Bake in well-greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Cool and top with 1 cup unsweetened whipped cream.
Chill 3 hours.

title: honey bars
directions: Mix together and press into greased and floured oblong pan. Bake 20 minutes or until brown at 300°.

title: tamale balls
directions: Mix dry ingredients and garlic juice together and enough tomato juice to hold meat mixture together.
Roll into balls (1 1/2 inches).
Use remainder of tomato juice and make sauce in a large saucepot.
Bring to a boil and drop meat balls, one at a time, into sauce and simmer for 2 hours.
Yields 75 meat balls.

title: cranberry pie
directions: Layer first 3 ingredients into a deep-dish 9-inch pie pan greased with vegetable oil.
Beat eggs and 1 cup sugar.
Add flour gradually.
Add butter and vegetable oil; beat well.
Pour over berries.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes.

title: mississippi shortcake
directions: Combine biscuit mix and 2 tablespoons of the sugar in medium bowl.
Save rest of sugar for sprinkling over top.
Stir in milk, make according to box.
Turn out onto floured board, knead lightly, about 10 times.
Roll out not more than 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut out with 2-inch cutter.
Makes 30 to 36 rounds.

title: glazed fruit 'n' franks
directions: In medium saucepan, combine preserves, lemon juice, cornstarch and cinnamon.
Cook and stir until well blended and slightly thickened.
Stir in frankfurters and pineapple; heat through. Just before serving, stir in apple and orange.
Serve warm.
Makes about 3 1/2 cups.

title: turkey gumbo
directions: Saute onions in
salad oil until tender, but not brown. Add broth,
tomatoes,
okra,
turkey,
parsley	and
paprika. Simmer for 10
minutes.
Season to taste with salt and pepper. Serve over rice.

title: caramel chip brownies
directions: Melt caramels and 1/3 cup milk together over low heat. Mix cake mix, melted butter, milk and nuts by hand. Put 1/2 of batter in 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Bake at 350° for 6 minutes. Take from oven and pour caramel mixture over top.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over caramel. Dot top with the rest of cake mix mixture. As it cooks, it will form a top crust.
(Dot close together.)
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cut when cool.

title: passover carrot torte *
directions: Beat together egg yolks and sugar until thick; add carrots, walnuts and cake meal.
Gently fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Bake in spring-form pan 1 1/4 hours in preheated 300° oven.

title: frozen pink salad
directions: Soften cream cheese. Add mayonnaise and sugar. Blend well. Add pineapple, nuts and cranberries. Fold in whipped cream. Freeze in a Pyrex dish. Keep in freezer. Cut into squares and serve.

title: do ahead beef noodle bake
directions: Cook noodles according to label directions.
Drain well.
Brown chuck in skillet along with onions and green pepper.
Pour off excess fat.
Stir in tomato sauce and seasonings.
Blend cottage cheese and cream cheese until smooth.
Spoon 1/2 noodles into buttered dish 2-quart casserole.
Cover with cheese mix and add remaining noodles.
Pour meat sauce over noodles.
Place in refrigerator for 1 hour before meal time.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 6 to 8 persons.

title: sausage with peppers
directions: Cut sausage into 4-inch pieces.
Brown in oil.
Remove from pan.
Brown onion and pepper until tender.
Add puree and 1 can of water.
Add sausage and mushrooms.
Add 1 teaspoon dry mustard and 1 teaspoon of Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer all ingredients for 1 hour in saucepan.
Serve on small Hoagie buns.
Serves 4.

title: diet chili
directions: Add all of the ingredients except ground beef and bean sprouts.
Cook for 1/4 an hour.
Add beef and cook 1 hour.
Add bean sprouts (chopped fine).
Cook until heated through.

title: microwave lasagna
directions: Brown beef on High 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and water.
Combine Ricotta, egg and pepper.
Spoon 1/2 cup sauce.
Alternate layer of noodles and egg mix, Mozzarella and sauce.
Form 2 layers.
Microwave covered on High for 8 minutes. Microwave on 50% for 30 to 35 minutes or until noodles are tender. Top with Parmesan and let stand 15 minutes.

title: cheesecake cupcakes
directions: Blend together cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Place vanilla wafer in center of cupcake paper.
Add cheese mixture. Bake at 350° until slightly brown, 25 to 35 minutes.
Let cool. Top will form a well.
Fill indentation with pie filling.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Rinse and cut up vegetables.
Boil water.
Add vegetables.
Add sauces 20 minutes later.
Stir occasionally.
When soup is hot and thick enough, turn the stove off.
Cook soup on high.

title: deep dish pizza
directions: On lightly floured surface, let thawed dough stand for 1 hour. Brown meat; drain and add onions.
Cook until tender.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, Parmesan and seasonings.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Roll out dough to 15 x 11-inch rectangle.
Press into 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased pan and up 1-inch on sides.
Cover dough with cheese and meat.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: swedish tea cake
directions: Grease aluminum pie tin, 9-inch, and sugar it.
Mix and pour into tin.
Sprinkle chopped nuts and/or coconut on top and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Lightly sprinkle powdered sugar over top when slightly cool.
(Recipe can be doubled and put in pan and cut as for squares.)

title: shrimp and crab stuffing(used for redfish, flounder or mushroom stuffing)
