directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add shrimp and cook on medium heat until shrimp turn pink.
Lift out shrimp and set aside.
Heat butter and liquid on high about 2 minutes.
Add onion, celery, garlic, bay leaves, parsley, thyme and basil.
Cook about 3 minutes.
Stir in green onions, lemon juice, bouillon, crab boil, crab meat and shrimp.
Heat about 2 minutes.
Add beaten eggs. Mix, then stir in bread crumbs.
Remove from heat.
Can be frozen. Use about 1/2 to 1 cup per serving for redfish, trout or flounder. Use approximately 1 tablespoon for each large mushroom.

title: azars strawberry pie
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Cook until it starts to thicken.
Take off heat and add strawberry jello and red food coloring.
Pour over berries.
Put in refrigerator.
Cool.
Serve with Cool Whip or whipping cream.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil fryer and remove meat from bones.
Heat soup, broth and tomatoes in saucepan.
Place in baking dish in layers chicken, onions, Doritos and cheese.
Pour soup mix over layers and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage in a skillet over medium heat, stirring until it crumbles and is no longer pink; drain well.
Place bread cubes in a lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle bread evenly with cheese and top with sausage.
Whisk together eggs and remaining ingredients; pour evenly over sausage mixture. Cover and chill casserole for 8 hours.
Let stand at room temperature 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: batesville cheese and green chili pie
directions: Sprinkle Jack cheese and 1/2 the Cheddar in bottom of pie crust.
Distribute chillies over cheese.
Beat eggs and half and half, salt and cumin.
Pour over cheese in the pie crust. Sprinkle remaining cheese over pie filling.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes or until pie sets.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until fork-tender.
Peel and dice.
Blend remaining ingredients with potatoes in large bowl.
Cover and chill 1 hour before serving.
Serves 6.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine sugar and flour in saucepan.
Combine egg and fruit juices and blend into flour mixture.
Cook over low heat until mixture thickens, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add margarine and cool.
Fold in fruit.

title: pumpkin fruit bake
directions: *Pears, apples, peaches, Queen Anne cherries, pineapple chunks, apricots, etc.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together and then form into balls (meatball size).
Brown the meatballs in the butter in a large frying pan.
After browning, set aside while preparing the sauce.

title: sweetheart cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in egg yolks. Combine flour and baking powder. Add to cream mixture, alternating with milk. Beat well after each addition. Stir in vanilla. Pour batter into 2 greased and floured pans. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done. Cool and remove from pans.

title: tarte a la bouillie(custard pie)
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add eggs and beat well.
Bring milk to a boil, add egg mixture and cook over medium heat until thick. Cool and add vanilla.
Pour into unbaked Sweet Crust pie shell and top with lattice top crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: lucille's white icing
directions: Put all ingredients in top of double boiler over boiling water.
Beat with mixer 7 minutes or until icing is stiff enough to stand in peaks.
Remove from heat and frost cake.

title: chicken pasta salad
directions: Boil and dice chicken breast.
Chop remaining ingredients and mix with chicken and cooked pasta.
Mix dressing and mayonnaise until smooth.
Add to pasta mixture and stir thoroughly.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: no bake cookie balls
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and milk in pan; boil for 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients and roll in balls.
Eat.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place fruit in buttered 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Cut crust from bread slices and cut each slice into 5 fingers.
Place bread over fruit.
In a bowl, mix sugar, flour, egg and oleo.
Pour over bread and fruit.
Bake at 350°
for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: ice cream cookies
directions: Cream butter, margarine and sugar in bowl until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour and salt; mix well.
Beat in vanilla.
Chill, tightly covered, overnight.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Top with pecans.
Place 2 inches apart on foil-lined cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes or until light brown around edges.
Remove foil and cookies from cookie sheet immediately.
Cool on foil.
Store in airtight container.
Yield: 72 servings.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine in saucepan or double boiler the sugar, flour, cocoa and salt. Stir in milk. Beat and add lastly the egg yolks. Reserve whites for meringue.
Cook, stirring constantly, until well thickened. Remove from heat and add 2 tablespoons butter or margarine and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.

title: harvey wallbanger cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Generously grease 12-cup fluted tube pan. In large bowl, blend 2 clear cake mix packages and remaining ingredients until moistened. Beat 2 minutes at medium speed. Pour into prepared pan. Bake at 325° for 45 to 55 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean. Sprinkle topping packet over cooled cake. Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: aunt hettie's sponge cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together for 10 minutes.
Add flavoring. Add sifted dry ingredients and water.
Beat together thoroughly. Lightly grease 9 x 13-inch pan (bottom).
Bake at 325° to 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Spread with whipped cream and cut into serving size pieces.
Try other toppings like lemon, caramel or chocolate.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour with baking soda, baking powder, salt and spices; set aside.
Mix milk, vanilla and applesauce.
Cream butter until light.
Add sugar gradually, continuing to cream until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients alternately with applesauce mixture, beginning and ending with the dry and adding about 1/3 of the total at a time.
Beat just until smooth. Mix in raisins and nuts.
Spoon into an ungreased 9-inch pan lined with wax paper and bake 35 minutes until cake shrinks slightly from sides of pan and is springy to the touch.
Cool upright in pan on a wire rack 5 minutes, then invert on rack and peel off paper.
Turn right side up and cool completely.
Frost or not as desired.

title: quick and easy chili
directions: Brown beef and cook onion, chili powder and garlic until onion is tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes, stirring now and then.
Makes 4 servings.

title: 2 egg sponge cake
directions: In a large bowl, beat the yolks, flavoring and water until it looks like enough to make a quart.
Add one cup of sugar gradually and beat seven minutes.
Add flour, baking powder and salt, sifted together and beat just until mixed.
Finally, beat egg whites stiff and then add gradually the remaining 1/4 cup sugar and the cream of tartar and beat until very stiff.
Fold egg whites into batter.
Bake in an ungreased tube pan at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Invert pan and cool.
Delicious.
Frost or serve with strawberries and Cool Whip.

title: german slaw
directions: Shred cabbage, onion and pepper together.
Sprinkle sugar and salt on top.
Bring vinegar, celery seed, mustard and oil to boil and pour over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate 6 to 8 hours. Stir, then serve.
This keeps well for several days in the refrigerator.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Rinse berries; drain.
Place berries in bottom of 10 x 6-inch glass baking dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Mix next 4 ingredients with fork until mixture resembles corn meal.
Distribute flour mixture over berries.
Drizzle top with butter.
Combine cinnamon and sugar and sprinkle on top.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve with vanilla ice cream.

title: denver biscuits
directions: Mix yeast liquid and shortening to warmed milk.
Add sugar and 5 cups flour or enough to make dough the consistency of pancake batter.
Cover; let rise for 2 hours or double in bulk.
Add baking powder, soda, salt and flour until dough is consistency of regular dough.
Roll and cut biscuits.
Place on greased pans and put in freezer.
After frozen, store in plastic bags.
Take out what you want.
Let thaw and bake as usual.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar together in large bowl.
Bring oleo, cocoa, oil and water to a rapid boil and pour over dry mixture. Mix well.
Add buttermilk, eggs, vanilla and soda.
Mix well; batter will be thin.
Pour into greased pan (11 x 6-inch).
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: chocolate peanut clusters
directions: Melt almond bark and chocolate chips in the microwave.
Add peanuts and drop by teaspoons onto wax paper.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together and put into greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Combine cream cheese, margarine and confectioners sugar in bowl; mix well.
Combine pudding mix and milk in mixer bowl; beat for 2 minutes.
Add whipped topping; beat well.
Add pudding mixture to cream cheese mixture; mix well.
Reserve enough cookie crumbs for topping.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Blend all dry ingredients together in a large bowl. Add buttermilk, oil and eggs.
Blend until all ingredients are moistened. (Do not stir batter again.)
Mixture may be stored in the refrigerator for up to 6 weeks in covered nonmetal containers. Use as needed.
Bake in muffin tins at 400° for 10 to 20 minutes. Yields 4 dozen muffins.

title: gooey pecan bars
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and butter together and press into bottom of lightly greased 9 x 13 pan and set aside.

title: bourbon slush
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze.
Stir every 12 hours.
When frozen, scrape some into a glass and fill the glass with 7-Up. Insert straw and enjoy!

title: raisin bread
directions: Combine raisins and water.
Bring to boil and cool to room temperature.
Mix egg, sugar and oil.
Stir in raisins and water mixture. Add dry ingredients. Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake at 325° for 60 minutes or until done.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain grease and add undiluted soups.
Put in large foil pan or a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Drain green beans and layer over meat.
Layer cheese over green beans.
Line up Tater Tots over top of cheese.
Bake according to temperature on Tater Tot bag until hot and bubbly.

title: sausage balls(great for parties)
directions: Combine all ingredients and make into small balls (walnut size) or smaller.
Fry gently and drain on paper towel.
You can make ahead and freeze and finish cooking in sauce when needed.

title: tabouleh(middle east recipe)
directions: Pour boiling water over raw bulgur wheat or cracked wheat. Let stand 2 hours or until wheat is fluffy.
Drain well.
Mix with chickpeas, parsley, mint, scallions or onion, salt, tomatoes, lemon juice and oil.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Serve on lettuce. Serves 6 to 8.

title: microwave bread pudding
directions: Heat milk and oleo in 1 1/2-quart casserole on High 3 minutes. Stir in eggs, sugar, cinnamon, salt, vanilla and fruit.
Add torn bread to mixture.
If rather thick, may add additional 1/4 cup regular milk to thin out mixture.
Cook High 7 minutes covered. Serve warm.

title: one bowl chocolate cake
directions: Put ingredients in bowl in order given. But do not mix until last item has been added. Beat well and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: "bumpa" lernihan's short ribs of beef
directions: Put the corned beef in a large, heavy pot with sufficient cold water to cover it by 1-inch. Add the garlic and studded onion with cloves into the pot.
Bring to a boil and reduce the heat to low. (You should only see the tiniest little bubbles, not big bubbles in the simmering water.)
Cover and simmer gently for about 3 hours until the meat is tender but not falling apart.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine. Add whole kernel corn with juice, cream-style corn, sour cream, cheese and muffin mix. Stir until well blended. Place in an oblong baking dish (approximately 8 x 11) that has been sprayed with Pam. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt the chocolate and butter over low heat.
Add sugar.
Beat the eggs and add milk and cornstarch.
Add to chocolate mixture. Stir in vanilla, pecans and coconut.
Pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in flour and salt.
Gradually add chicken stock and cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Remove from heat and stir in Tabasco, cheese and cream.
Pour sauce over broccoli and chicken.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together peanut butter, Rice Krispies, powdered sugar and butter.
Make into balls.
In double boiler, mix chocolate chips, Hershey bar, vanilla and paraffin.
Dip first mixture in.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Saute chopped onions and celery with mushrooms in margarine. Cook and drain broccoli.
Mix soup, cheese and milk with onion mixture and simmer until cheese melts.
Mix mixture with rice, broccoli and chicken if used.
Bake in greased casserole dish in 350° oven until firm (about 1 hour).

title: hot spiced orange juice
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Combine orange and lemon juice with first mixture.
Serve in mugs and garnish with orange or lemon slices or cinnamon sticks.
Makes 12 servings.
Add extra water if stored for a period.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have all the cheese at room temperature.
Cream together, then blend in mayonnaise and remaining ingredients.
Chill and roll in chopped pecans.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix thoroughly the first 4 ingredients and let set until firm. Blend the next 4 ingredients and spread over gelatin mixture. Sprinkle with nuts.
This works well in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: knox blocks
directions: Pour Jell-O and gelatine into bowl; add boiling water and stir until dissolved.
Pour mixture into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares or use cookie cutters for other shapes.

title: strawberry angel torte
directions: Cut cake horizontally into 3 layers.
Place 1 cake layer on serving plate.
Stir crushed strawberries and milk into 1 1/2 cups of whipped topping in large bowl.
Spread 1/2 of strawberry mixture on cake layer.
Arrange 1/2 of the sliced strawberries on top of mixture.
Repeat layers, ending with cake.
Frost top and sides with remaining whipped topping.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour or until ready to serve.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar gradually, beating until thick.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into freezer and freeze.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook beef and sausage together; drain well.
Boil pasta noodles until tender, but not limp.
Drain and pour cool water over them.
After meat mixture is drained, add cream cheese, Ranch dressing and half of sharp cheese.
Pour 1/2 of jar of sauce into lasagna type pan, then stuff shells with meat mixture.
Place in pan.
After all are in pan, top
with remaining sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Serve with salad and bread.

title: louise's chicken salad
directions: Depending on taste and amount being made mix 1/4 to 1/2 of an avocado with the mayonnaise; set aside.
Cut grapes in half and remaining avocado into 1/4 to 1/2-inch pieces.
Mix all ingredients together and eat as a salad or as a sandwich.

title: french tarts
directions: Beat yolks until light and fluffy.
Gradually add sugar, then remaining ingredients.
Add beaten whites of eggs last.
Bake in shallow pan at 350°.
Cut in bars while warm and roll in confectioners sugar.

title: spinach salad and dressing
directions: Toss ingredients in large bowl and add dressing.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on cookie sheet or pizza pan.
Bake according to directions.
Allow to cool.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until tender; drain. Cook bacon in 8-inch skillet until crisp; remove bacon. Cook onion in bacon fat until tender. Stir in flour, sugar, salt, celery seed and pepper. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is bubbly; remove from heat. Stir in water and vinegar. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Boil and stir 1 minute; remove from heat. Crumble bacon into hot mixture, then slice in warm potatoes. Cook, stirring gently, to coat potato slices, until hot and bubbly. Makes 5 servings; 195 calories per serving.

title: garden salad bowl
directions: Rub salad bowl with cut clove of garlic.
Alternate layers of vegetables and olives in lettuce-lined bowl; sprinkle each layer with lemon juice; season with salt and pepper.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage for 10 minutes.
Drain.
Mix eggs, butter and milk together.
Place cabbage in greased casserole dish.
Pour ingredients over the cabbage.
Add the cheese, then the bread crumbs over the top of all.
Bake in oven for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix all together.
Layer alternately with bananas and vanilla wafers.

title: fat free roux
directions: Put about 1 to 1 1/2 inches flour in a cast-iron skillet.
Cook at 400° until dark brown.
Stir every 15 to 20 minutes.

title: okra fritters
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients well and drop by tablespoon into hot oil.
Cook until brown.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Put sugars, butter and eggs in bowl and mix well.
Then add syrup, oatmeal, coconut and milk.
Bake in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: swedish tea cakes
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, beat 1/2 cup powdered sugar, margarine and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Add flour, almonds and salt. Mix until dough holds together.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes or until set, but not browned.
Immediately remove.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer peas, lettuce, onion and bacon bits in deep bowl or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with mayonnaise, sprinkle with sugar and cheese.
Seal and refrigerate overnight.
Mix well before serving.

title: hobo casserole
directions: Press the ground beef into the bottom of a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with canned milk; salt and pepper to taste. Slice potatoes (raw) on meat; slice onions onto potatoes.
Cube the cheese onto onions and cover with mushroom soup.
Bake in a covered 2 1/2-quart dish for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hilda's sweetbread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; set aside.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and the rest of the ingredients, except milk. Add as needed.
Knead until dough is spongy.
Cover and set in warm place to rise until double.
Roll out in loaves or round ones.
Let rise again until double and bake in a 325° oven until done (about 30 to 45 minutes).

title: argentinian chimichurri marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients in a glass jar with a tight fitting lid.
Let stand at room temperature for 24 hours.

title: hot dog and hamburger chili
directions: Thoroughly mix hamburger and water before heating.
Add other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Turn to simmer and cook for about 2 hours.
This is ideal for cookouts and freezes well.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend sugar, brown sugar, shortening and salt together until creamy. Add eggs. Beat well. Stir in peanut butter, blending well. Sift flour and soda together. Add to creamed mixture. Drop batter by spoonfuls onto foil-lined cookie sheet; flatten cookies with glass bottom dipped in additional sugar. Bake at 425° for 7 minutes or until lightly brown. Yield: 100 cookies.

title: dill pickles
directions: Fill jar with cukes.
Add sugar, salt and vinegar.
Add dill and clove of garlic.
Fill remainder of jar with water and seal. Put jars in hot water bath slowly until pickles turn slightly yellow.
Remove from canner and cool.

title: cinnamon sour cream coffee cake(makes 1 cake)
directions: *To make sour milk, if you have no sour cream, put a small amount of vinegar in milk.

title: orange date cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, flour, milk and soda.
Mix well.
Mix remaining ingredients (which have been mixed with the 1/2 cup flour); fold this into the cake batter and mix well.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours in a tube pan.

title: bacon wrapped water chestnuts(appetizer)
directions: Cut water chestnuts in half.
Wrap 1/2 slice bacon and secure with toothpicks.
Bake at 275° for 30 minutes.
Combine ketchup and brown sugar.
Pour ketchup mixture over water chestnuts and bake for 30 minutes more.

title: oklahoma brown candy
directions: Pour 2 cups sugar into heavy aluminum or iron skillet and place over low heat.
Begin stirring with a wooden spoon.
Keep sugar moving so that it does not burn.
It will take approximately 1/2 hour to melt sugar completely.
At no time let it smoke or cook so fast that the sugar turns dark.
It should be the color of light brown sugar syrup.
As soon as you have the sugar starting to heat in the skillet, pour remaining 4 cups sugar and cream into a deep heavy kettle set over low heat, while stirring constantly.
The real secret to mixing these ingredients is to pour a very thin stream from the skillet.
Continue cooking and stirring until mixture forms a firm ball (245°) when dropped into cold water.

title: scalloped corn(aunt mildred's)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in an 8 x 8-inch square pan. Dot with butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: hawaiian pineapple cake
directions: Mix the flour, sugar, baking soda, eggs, pineapple and juice, nuts and coconut by hand and spread in a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Ice with cream cheese frosting.

title: chili mac
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Pour excess.
Add 1/2 sweet chopped onion and 1 chopped green pepper.
Cook on low simmer. Add 1/2 chili seasoning to hamburger and other contents in skillet.
Prepare pot of tomato juice and kidney beans, cooking on medium high.
Place ground beef and other contents from skillet into pot of tomato juice.
After cooking for 35 minutes, add 1/2 box of cooked elbow macaroni.
Cook for 10 to 15 minutes, adding chili powder to taste.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in shallow baking dish.

title: mahogany cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add beaten egg yolks.
Dissolve soda in milk and add alternately with sifted flour.
Mix cocoa and milk to make custard; add to cake mixture, then add beaten egg whites. Pour into well greased pan.
Bake in moderate oven 35 minutes.

title: sicilian style string beans
directions: Use snap and string beans; boil beans in salted water until tender.
Drain.
Saute garlic (and onion if used) in olive oil until golden brown.
Add beans.
Combine bread crumbs and cheese; add to beans.
Cook 5 minutes on low heat and serve hot.
Yields 6 servings.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well with mixer. Pour in shell. Chill at least 1 hour. May be frozen.

title: chocolate fudge pound cake
directions: Heavily grease a 12-cup Bundt pan; set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Place both chocolates in top of a double boiler simmering over water or in a microwave. Stir until melted and smooth.
Set aside to cool slightly.
In a large mixing bowl, with an electric mixer, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Mix in one egg at a time, blending after each addition.
Mix in chocolate, vanilla and water.

title: custard pie
directions: Preheat oven and bake crust at 400° for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add sugar and salt to beaten eggs.
Scald milk; cool slightly.
Add milk slowly to egg and milk mixture.
Add vanilla.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Pour filling into prebaked crust; bake at 350° until set.

title: hashbrown potatoes
directions: Cook the hashbrown potatoes according to the package directions in the oven and add seasonings and onions to taste

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Put chicken breast pieces in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place cheese slices on top.
Spread can of soup over top.
Mix Stove Top as directed (do not cook).
Spread over chicken, cheese and soup. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: perfect pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: japanese hamburger
directions: Saute almonds in butter in skillet until lightly browned. Remove from pan and set aside.
Brown ground beef well in butter remaining in skillet leaving meat in chunks.
Stir in water and salt and bring to boil.
Stir in noodles.
Cover and simmer for 2 minutes.
Add vegetables.
Bring to full boil over medium heat, separating vegetables with fork and stirring frequently.
Cover and simmer for 3 minutes.
Stir in soy sauce and sprinkle with almonds.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Thaw the pastry sheets and roll them out into long strips. Place sausages, end-to-end, on each pastry sheet.
Fold over, pinching the edges together (but not the ends) with a fork.
Cut each sheet into sausage-length pieces.
Cut two slits in the top of each pastry-wrapped sausage and brush the top with beaten egg. Bake in 400° oven for 25 minutes.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Beat well and add cooled jello.
Beat again and pour into greased pan (angel food pan or similar).
Bundt pan is especially good.

title: shrimp remoulade
directions: Steam shrimp until done (about 5 minutes, until they are bright pink).
Cool and peel.
Mix remaining ingredients and blend well.
Pour over shrimp and refrigerate for at least one hour, stirring occasionally.
Mound shrimp on lettuce leaves and pour remaining sauce over.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sausage-sauce casserole
directions: In 2-quart saucepan cook sausage, onion and green pepper until vegetables are tender.
Drain off excess fat.
Add water, tomato sauce, tomato paste, parsley, sugar, garlic salt and oregano. Cover and simmer 15 minutes; stirring once or twice.
Cook cabbage wedges in a small amount of water until tender; about 10 minutes. Remove from skillet and drain.
Arrange cabbage and pour sauce over it.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add unbeaten eggs, blackberries with juice and spices.
Mix soda with buttermilk.
Set aside and sift and measure flour.
Stir flour and buttermilk mixture alternately into creamed mixture.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes.
Frost with Caramel Frosting.

title: sausage and sauerkraut
directions: Cut the sausage into 1-inch slices.
Saute until fully cooked and brown.
Drain.
Add sauerkraut, tomatoes with liquid, onion, green pepper, brown sugar and seasonings.
Mix well.
Cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve.

title: easy coffee buttercream frosting
directions: Dissolve instant coffee in water.
Blend into frosting.

title: pizza perfect
directions: Measure water and sprinkle over yeast.
Stir until dissolved. Stir in sugar, salt and olive oil.
Add 4 cups sifted flour and beat until smooth.
Add rest of flour and turn out on floured board, kneading until smooth and elastic.
Place dough in large greased bowl and grease slightly all over.
Cover and let rise until double (approximately 45 minutes).

title: lulas' molasses cookies
directions: Soften lard and mix well with sugar and molasses. Sift in rest of ingredients.

title: pineapple carrot bread
directions: Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Yield: 16 slices per loaf, 2 loaves.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Boil 3 cups water, bouillon cubes and broccoli.
Set aside. Cook onion in butter until soft, then add flour, pepper and milk. Slowly add cheese.
Mix together with broccoli and simmer.

title: quick hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger in oil.
Put potatoes in greased casserole dish.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add carrots.
Cover with 1/2 cup rice.
Place hamburger in dish and top with onion and 2 cans of tomato soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: baked or grilled vidalia onions
directions: Core onions and fill middle with butter, salt and pepper. Wrap in foil and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Do not overcook.
These may be grilled also.
However, when grilling, remember to start cooking onions prior to grilling meat, as it takes onions longer to cook.
This is a delicious side dish with grilled steaks or pork chops.

title: no cook ice cream
directions: Beat together eggs and sugar.
Whip cream until just thick. Add milk to egg mixture.
Add cream to this mixture and then add vanilla and salt.
Mix together and pour into freezer.

title: sweet potato apple casserole
directions: In a pot with a tight-fitting lid, steam sweet potatoes in 1/2 cup water until tender, 15 to 20 minutes.
Peel and slice them lengthwise in 1/2 inch thick slices.
Layer them in a casserole. Peel and core apples, slicing them 1/2 inch thick.
Layer apple slices on top of sweet potatoes.
Heat apple juice to the boiling point.
Combine cornstarch and water and add to juice, cooking until sauce is clear and thickened.
Add honey.
Spoon sauce over apples, then top with wheat germ.
Bake in a 350° oven until apples are tender, 30 minutes to an hour.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Saute sausage and ground meat in oil until no longer pink. Pour off excess oil and remove from fire.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Add at least 2 cans water.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Stir about every 20 minutes until rice is absorbed.
(You might have to add a little more water to make sure the rice gets done.)
Serves 8 to 10.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix together the shortening and sugar.
Add 1 egg, applesauce and flour.
Sift together baking powder, cloves, cinnamon, nutmeg, raisins and nuts.
Put in sack with flour and shake.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 350°.

title: praline ice cream sauce
directions: Spread pecans on a baking sheet.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes. Set aside.
Melt butter in medium saucepan.
Add sugar, corn syrup and flour, stirring well.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, stirring constantly, 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and let cool to lukewarm.
Gradually stir in milk and pecans.
Serve warm over ice cream.
Yields 3 cups.

title: corn bread(japanese)
directions: Blend butter and sugar; add rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a 9-inch square pan or 9 x 11 x 2-inch pan that has been buttered and floured.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: quick chocolate one egg cake
directions: Mix and sift flour, baking powder and soda.
Cook 2 Tbsp. sugar, water and cocoa together.
Cream shortening and remaining sugar together, add egg; beat well.
Add sifted flour, baking powder and soda.
Add chocolate mixture, milk and vanilla.
Bake in 350 degree oven for 20 minutes for layer cake or 30 minutes for loaf cake.

title: old fashioned coleslaw
directions: Combine all ingredients; refrigerate until time to serve. Makes 1 quart.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine all ingredients; beat at high speed for 1 minute. Pour into greased pie tin.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: grandpa dick's great guacamole
directions: You will need a garlic press, spoon, fork, cutting board and knife.
First, chop the onion and tomato.
Next, scoop the insides of the avocados into a bowl and mash up with a fork.
Put the garlic in mashed avocados.
Add the chopped tomatoes, onion and the lemon juice.
Add a pinch of salt.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Warm butter to room temperature. Cream butter, sugar and flour together. Add nuts and vanilla and work batter with hands. Roll out little balls about 1/2-inch each. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 20 minutes in 370° oven. Roll in powdered sugar when done. Sprinkle sugar on top of cookies.

title: tortilla cheese snacks
directions: Spread one tortilla with taco sauce to within 1/2-inch of edge.
Add a layer of Jack cheese.
Customize as desired or leave plain.
Top with 2nd tortilla.
Spread with melted butter.
Place on foil lined cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes or until cheese melts and top is bubbly and light brown.
Cut with pizza cutter into 4 pieces or smaller for hors d'oeuvres.

title: pistachio delight
directions: Drain pineapple.
Add juice to pudding. Beat until fluffy, about 2 minutes. Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Chill before serving, if desired.

title: wild rice with oysters(delicious with duck)
directions: Cover wild rice with water and soak overnight.
In the morning, drain and cook rice in a double boiler, covered, for 10 minutes.
Saute onion in butter until clear.
Add rice and oysters, nuts and seasonings.
Brown well, stirring constantly until liquid is absorbed.
Cover and set aside to keep hot until serving.
Serves 8.

title: cold slaw
directions: Bring last 6 ingredients to a boil and pour over the first 2 ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.
Will keep several days.

title: breaded pork cutlets
directions: Wipe cutlets with damp paper towels.
Pound very thin, about 1/8-inch, with mallet or edge of plate.
Dip cutlets into egg, then into bread crumbs to coat well.

title: cheese sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together by hand.
Preheat oven to 350°. Roll into bite size balls.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: stay krisp salad
directions: Mix shredded cabbage, carrots, green pepper and onion. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup cold water.
Chill.
Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water.
Mix sugar, vinegar, celery seed, salt and pepper in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in softened gelatine.
Cool until slightly thickened.
Beat well.
Gradually beat in salad oil.
Drain vegetables.
Pour dressing over top.
Mix lightly until all vegetables are coated with dressing.
May be served immediately.
Stir just before serving to separate pieces.

title: pineapple-turkey salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except pineapple and lettuce; chill. Before serving, stir in pineapple.
Serve in lettuce cups.
Serves 6.

title: instant cocoa mix
directions: Mix thoroughly in a very large container and store in a coffee can.
To fix a cup, heat water and add 2 or 3 generous tablespoons of mix to each cup.
Pour boiling water over mix.
Stir and serve.

title: german apple cake
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add oil and sugar; stir until sugar dissolves.
Add salt, soda and cinnamon to flour; mix thoroughly. Add apple slices, nuts and vanilla; stir until mixed in.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Place mixture in a greased and floured sheet cake pan and bake for 45 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Bake in baking dish at 375° to 400° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: dilly casserole bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into 9 x 5-inch bread pan. Cover and let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down.
Let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown. Brush with butter and salt.

title: jalapeno grits casserole
directions: Generously butter deep 2-quart baking dish.
Place basic grits in a large bowl.
Add cheese and butter; beat until smooth.
Stir in beaten eggs and jalapeno peppers.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Pour mixture into prepared baking dish.
Bake at 350° until grits are set and top is lightly browned, about 35 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: can't fail divinity
directions: Boil sugar, water and salt until it forms a hard ball in cold water.
Place cream in mixing bowl and stir in hot syrup. Continue stirring until slightly stiff or holds peak.
Fold in nuts and add vanilla.
Drop from spoon on wax paper.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in their skins; peel and slice.
Fry bacon until crisp; remove.
Brown onion in bacon fat.
Add vinegar, salt, pepper and sour cream.
Add potatoes and bacon.
Serve hot.

title: "sweet and sour" green beans
directions: Fry bacon and set aside.
Place drained green beans in bacon grease in skillet.
Add sugar and vinegar; bring to a boil and simmer.
Crumble bacon on top and serve hot.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook onion in oil until it colors slightly.
Add rice and cook, stirring, over low heat 2 to 3 minutes, then add meat and water chestnuts (slivered or chopped).
Sliced or chopped mushrooms may be added with any of the ingredients or used alone. Mix well, then add soy sauce, eggs and seasonings to taste.
Cook, stirring, over low heat until the eggs are cooked (this will take only 2 or 3 minutes).
Trim with sliced green onions or more of same meat, slivered, that is used in the rice.
Makes 6 main dish servings or more as a side dish.

title: blueberry-orange bread
directions: Melt butter in boiling water.
Add 1/2 cup orange juice and 3 tablespoons orange rind.
Beat egg with sugar.
Add mixed dry ingredients alternately with orange juice mixture.
Fold in berries.
Bake in buttered 1 1/2-quart loaf pan at 325° about 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Turn out rack over foil.
Spoon mixture of remaining 2 tablespoons orange juice, 1 teaspoon rind and the honey over hot loaf.
Can be frozen.

title: crispy carrot casserole
directions: Cook the carrots in small amount of water until tender-crisp; drain.
Put the carrots in a greased casserole.
Dot with butter; stir in the onion.
Sprinkle with cheese; top with chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves six to eight.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together in bowl, then mold in a mound in a baking dish and add catsup on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: marie's pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs slightly in a 2-quart bowl. Stir in sugar, corn syrup, melted butter, vanilla and pecans. Pour in a pie shell.
Cook 35 to 40 minutes or until firm.

title: mushroom caps
directions: Saute fresh mushrooms in butter or oil.
Separate caps and stems.
Toast white bread; cut in squares.
Place mixture on bread and place mushroom cap on bread.

title: katie's chicken
directions: Cut chicken in 1 inch pieces. Soak chicken in the batter for 1 hour.
Mix the egg and milk.
Dip chicken in bread crumbs.
Brown chicken in frying pan.
Layer chicken, mushrooms and cheese in casserole.
Dissolve 1 bouillon cube in 1 cup hot water.
Pour over casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Remove cover and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: boston baked beans(a 3 generation recipe)
directions: Wash beans and soak overnight. Cook until just tender. Drain, reserving liquid. Combine beans and all other ingredients in a bean pot or 2-quart casserole. Cover with bean liquid. Cover and bake 6 to 8 hours at 250°. Add more liquid as necessary, stirring occasionally.

title: new year's day bean soup
directions: Wash beans and place in a large kettle.
Cover with 2-inches of water.
Add 1 tablespoon salt and soak overnight.

title: hot ryes
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except bread.
Spread on party rye or pumpernickel.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes or until browned.
Makes 36 hors d'oeuvres.

title: top of stove mac and cheese
directions: Cook pasta in large sauce pan, drain and set aside. Melt butter in same pan over medium heat. Remove. Whisk in milk, eggs, mustard, salt and pepper. Return pasta to pan and stir in cheese. Mix well. Cook over low heat for 4 to 5 minutes. Stir continually until cheese melts. Serve immediately.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Brown meat and onions.
Add sauces, paste and seasonings to taste.
Simmer then add noodles.
Layer in baking dish with meat, cheese and pepperoni.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° covered for 30 minutes.

title: milk shake
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and blend for about 30 seconds.
Fruit may be added such as peaches, strawberries or pineapple.
Makes 1 serving.

title: rhubarb swirls
directions: Add sugar, water, candies and coloring in saucepan and boil 10 minutes or until candies are dissolved.
Pour in 13 x 9 x 2 pan to cool.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Mix flour and spices.
Set aside.
Cream margarine and sugar. Mix well.
Add eggs.
Add flour until well blended.
Add fruit cake mix, dates and nuts.
Add water and soda mixed together. Stir until all are blended.
Drop 1 teaspoon at a time on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while hot.
Keep in tightly closed container for freshness.

title: cream cheese omelet
directions: Whip eggs with a little milk until frothy.
Add 7 lumps of cream cheese and mix in lightly.
Pour into frying pan containing sizzling butter or margarine.
Stir lightly while cooking until egg mixture is soft and cream cheese is melted into eggs.
Do not overcook.
Place on large plate.
Add salt, pepper and ketchup to taste.
Serves 3 or 4.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Bake layers as directed on box.

title: all around cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients and drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: "almost" fat-free chicken
directions: Spray large frying pan with cooking spray. Brown chicken breasts and put in about 1/2 to 1 c. water. Cover and simmer to steam chicken for about 15 minutes. Add soup and water (use one soup can full). Cook until soup cooks down and is a little thickened. Garnish with parsley and serve.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Bake yellow cake mix in sheet cake pan.
In large glass bowl, crumble 1/2 of the sheet cake.
Cover with instant vanilla pudding (made according to directions).
Add 1/2 of crushed pineapple.
Add 1/2 the Cool Whip.
Add 1/2 of cherries and pecans.
Repeat with another layer of each ingredient.
Great for a party.

title: uova con pepperoni salsiccia(eggs, peppers and sausage)
directions: Cut peppers lengthwise after cleaned and seeded.
Heat oil in large frying pan and add peppers and garlic.
Add sausage when hot and cook meat and peppers until brown.
Lower heat, cover pan and saute slowly for 10 minutes.
Beat eggs.
Fold in beaten eggs. Stir gently until eggs are cooked to your desire.
Good on Italian bread or rolls.
Serves many.

title: hungarian chicken-n-dumplings
directions: In a large pot, add chopped onion to vegetable oil, then add chicken.
Cook slowly until onion is almost done, then add enough water to almost cover chicken.
Also add paprika and salt and pepper to taste.
(Don't worry about paprika, it is very mild. May add more or less to taste.)
Bring to a boil and then turn down on low.
Cook until chicken is done.
Add water, if needed. Don't let chicken cook dry.

title: the best pumpkin pie you ever ate
directions: *Do not use pumpkin pie filling.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute beef until browned in a nonstick skillet.
Add onion and mushrooms and continue cooking until onion and mushrooms are tender and excess liquid has evaporated.

title: sweet cream porridge(rommegrot)
directions: Put cream in a heavy saucepan and boil for 10 minutes; sift flour into cream very slowly to prevent lumps from forming. Continue cooking over medium heat, stirring to bring out butterfat; remove butter as soon as it forms and put into a small pan to keep warm.
Add a little more flour to the grot and when mixed well, add scalded milk gradually, stirring until mixture is smooth.
Add salt and sugar and cook for about 10 minutes more. Serve hot with the drawn butterfat, sugar and cinnamon.

title: sheath cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Bring water to a boil; pour over flour and sugar.
Add softened butter, soda and vanilla.
Mix well with all the ingredients left.
Pour into cake pan; bake for 20 minutes.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Mix milk and vinegar together.
Set aside.
Cream together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add to the milk mixture and mix well.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Stir sugar into kraut.
Let stand 1/2 hour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill at least 12 hours before serving.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into bake pie shell.
Bake for about 45 minutes in 325° oven.

title: cheese sticks
directions: Grate cheese, cut up butter and beat together with beater.
Use part flour with beater, then rest of flour with hand.
Make into sticks and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until slightly brown.

title: quiche with crabmeat
directions: Blend mayonnaise, milk, eggs and cornstarch until smooth. Stir in crabmeat, cheese, onion and pepper.
Turn into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until browned.

title: willie mai yeast rolls
directions: Mix yeast, sugar, salt, egg and oil.
Add water.
Dissolve and mix well.
Add flour until sticky.
Let rise until double.
Roll out on floured board about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut out.
Brush with melted oleo, fold.
Lay in pie pan that is greased with Pam. Brush top with oleo.
Let rise.
Bake 6 to 7 minutes at 400°.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Beat egg, then add sugar and flour.
Mix and add rhubarb. Bake in unbaked pie shell at 425° for 10 minutes, then reduce to 350° and bake until done and pie shell golden brown.

title: in a hurry pie
directions: Combine with mixer until thick.
Pour into crust. Refrigerate.

title: mexican dip plate
directions: Put lettuce around sides of bowl for garnish.
Cold ground beef may be used for main dish.
May be left out for hours.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers, blended with 1/2 stick of butter.
Bake at 350° in oven for 45 minutes or until browned.

title: oriental salad
directions: Toast almonds and sesame seeds. Cool. Toss cabbage, onions, chicken, almonds and sesame seeds. Combine sugar, vinegar, oil and flavor packets from Ramen noodle soup. Toss with cabbage mixture.

title: ham ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and form into a ball. Refrigerate and serve with crackers.

title: oregano chicken and potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In roasting pan combine all ingredients, except chicken and potatoes.
Add chicken and potatoes and toss to coat.
Arrange chicken, skin side up.
Bake 50 minutes; stir occasionally.

title: mac mac's asparagus dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Drain and chop asparagus. Add to remaining ingredients and mix. Pour into baking dish. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes until bubbly and lightly browned. Remove from oven and sprinkle with cheese. Serve with toasted French bread rounds.

title: gugelhopf
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients with electric mixer 15 minutes or by hand 30 minutes.
Add flour sifted with mace and baking powder, alternately with milk.
Add juice and rind of lemon, then vanilla, the 4 egg whites (beaten stiff), nuts and raisins.
Bake in your beautiful Gugelhopf pan at 400° for 15 minutes, then 350° for 1 hour.
It's so good!!!

title: prune cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spray pan with Pam.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes in an 11 x 12-inch pan.

title: new york beef stew
directions: Shake beef in paper bag with flour to coat.
Brown in large pan in hot oil.
Add onions and cook until soft.
Add water to cover meat; bring to boil and add rest of the seasonings.
Adjust to your taste.
This stew should be a little spicy, but you decide.
Simmer, covered, until meat is tender.
Peel whole carrots, cut into serving pieces, add to stew and cook until tender.
Top with dumplings.

title: best ever sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Beat butter, sugar, egg and flavoring until creamy.
Add sour cream and flour mixture. Beat at low speed 2 1/2 minutes.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Roll dough on floured surface to 1/4-inch thick.
Sprinkle with sugar and roll in lightly.
Bake on greased cookie sheet.
Can put nuts, raisins or cherries in middle; or Chris' favorite is to cut out with cookie cutters.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes.

title: green chile chicken casserole
directions: Make sauce by combining soup, milk, chiles and chicken.
Stir on medium heat until soup and milk have smoothed out.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch dripper pan.
Layer quartered tortillas, sauce and cheese, alternating.
You should have 3 or 4 layers.
Cover with layer of cheese.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
It's better if you make this dish ahead and let it set up for 2 hours.
Serve over bed of lettuce with sour cream and salsa.

title: easter casserole
directions: Line 13 x 9-inch pan (or larger) with bread slices.
Cover with cheese slices.
Add eggs with milk mixed with ham, green pepper and mushrooms.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or longer.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: traditional salad
directions: Dissolve lemon	jello
in
hot	water.	Take juice from crushed pineapple;	add
water
to	make
2 cups and stir into jello.
Put
mixture
into	refrigerator until just set.
Whip until frothy.
Add crushed pineapple, walnuts, cheese and Cool Whip.
Mix together; put in refrigerator until set.

title: party mix
directions: Fry meat and drain.
Add cheese and melt.
Spread on Pepperidge Farm rye or Onion party slices.
Place on cookie sheet to bake now or freeze.
Store in freezer bag and remove as many as needed at the time.
Bake until hot at 350°.
Makes about 5-6 dozen.
Also good on English Muffins.

title: banana slush punch
directions: Combine the ingredients (bananas, lemon and orange juice) in blender.
The rest, put in a large container, then mix well.
Pour into Tupperware container or 1/2 gallon milk carton.
Freeze. When ready to serve, set out of freezer until thawed to slush (3 hours or so, depending on weather).
Add 4 quarts of ginger ale. Makes 50 servings.
Can be colored with food coloring to match color scheme.
Can be frozen in 4-pint container, if you choose.

title: veal brisket
directions: Put veal brisket in shallow baking pan; pour soup mixture over and add 3/4 cup water.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.
Take veal out.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Slice thin; lay slices in juice and cook covered 1/2 hour.
Serve with buttered noodles.

title: special green beans
directions: Put water, bouillon and sliced onions in heavy kettle.
Cover. Bring to boil.
Add frozen beans and sliced mushrooms.
Bring to a boil again and simmer 5 to 10 minutes until beans are tender.

title: * chili *
directions: Cut bacon fine.
Saute bacon, onion and garlic together in skillet.
Add meat to this; sprinkle with flour and cook until meat is brown.
Put this mixture into large pot.
Add 1 can of tomato paste, the chili powder, the cumin and the oregano.
Add a quart of water and simmer until meat is tender, about 1 hour.
Add can of beans and continue cooking about 20 to 30 minutes longer, stirring occasionally, to prevent burning.

title: dirty rice
directions: Boil rice.
In a separate pan, boil the livers and gizzards. Drain rice and use the juice from the chicken parts to pour over the rice.
Fry onions, pepper and celery in butter.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake for 30 minutes on low heat.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: ham barbecue
directions: Brown ham in butter until lightly brown.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until flavor is blended.
Serve on hamburger rolls.

title: blackberry pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat until well mixed.
Bake in a tube pan for 45 to 50 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: crab struedel
directions: Melt 2 Tbsp. butter in pan and stir in flour to a smooth paste.
Add the half and half and heat gently, while stirring on a low heat.
When reaches a simmer remove from heat and add the dijon mustard.
Keep stirring and bring back to a simmer to slightly thickened.
Remove, cover and chill in fridge for two hours.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan for first layer.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix next 3 ingredients and spread over first layer.
Mix pudding and milk; spread over second layer.
Top with remaining cup of Cool Whip and nuts.

title: white bread
directions: Combine all ingredients except flour and yeast in a large pan. Stir until lukewarm.
Add yeast and about 4 cups flour.
Mix with electric mixer at least 5 minutes.
Add more flour if mixer can handle it.
Stir in about 1/2 cup of flour at a time until dough is smooth and elastic.
Cover with a wet towel until double in bulk.
Shape into 4 loaves.
Place in greased bread pans.
Cover. When pan feels light, bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes.
Brush bread with margarine.

title: chocolate graham cracker crust
directions: Blend graham cracker crumbs with sugar, nutmeg, butter and chocolate.
Press into a 9-inch pie pan.
Chill until firm.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown onion, carrots and celery in butter or oil.
Brown sausage.
Boil water.
Add dry soup, rice and peas.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Cook raisins in 2 cups water for 15 minutes.
Add 1 cup cold water, melted lard, soda, sugar, cinnamon, salt and flour; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: southern buttermilk corn bread
directions: Preheat well-greased 8 or 10-inch heavy skillet in 425° oven. Blend all ingredients and pour into skillet.
Cook for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: spiced tea
directions: Serve hot; it is a great holiday party drink.

title: chocolate kiss surprise
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place rack in center of oven.
Cream butter until fluffy.
Add 1/2 of powdered sugar.
Stir in vanilla and salt.
Stir in flour and nuts until blended.
Press scant teaspoon dough in palm of hand.
Use thumb to make flat dish. Place chocolate kiss in center.
Bring edges of dough up to completely cover chocolate kisses.
Roll to form ball.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 10 to 12 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar once when warm, and again when cooled.

title: shrimp egg foo yong patties
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put oil in pan; heat moderately.
Spoon mixture into pan.
Shape like little pancakes.
Turn over; brown on both sides.

title: jambalaya
directions: Melt butter in skillet on medium heat.
Add onion, pepper and beef.
Cook until meat is brown.
Drain off excess fat.
Drain tomatoes, measuring juice.
Add water to juice to make 2 cups.
Add juice, tomatoes, sugar, salt, thyme and bay leaf.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes, then add rice.
Simmer 5 more minutes.
Discard bay leaf.
Serves 4.

title: steamed clams
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large kettle with lid.
Cover and cook over high heat for approximately 7 minutes or until clams open.
Shake pot occasionally like you would popcorn.
Serve with pasta and garlic bread.

title: pineapple vegetable salad
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients; pour in an 8 x 12-inch dish. Cool.
Mix jello into the remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate to set.
Serve in squares on lettuce.
Yields 4 servings.

title: ann landers' meat loaf
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cabbage patch soup(our favorite)
directions: Brown meat and onions; add celery and cabbage.
Cook vegetables until clear or wilted.
Add water and seasonings.
Stir well.
Add tomatoes and beans.
Simmer for 1/2 hour.

title: guacamole
directions: Mix all together and serve.

title: eggplant appetizer
directions: In large saucepan, combine eggplant, mushrooms, green pepper, garlic and oil.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add onion, green and black olives, capers, pine nuts, tomato paste, water, vinegar, salt, pepper, oregano and honey.
Simmer, covered, for 25 minutes. Eggplant should not be too soft.
Refrigerate and serve with pita wedges.

title: mixed fruits
directions: Mix Tang and instant pudding.
Add to fruit and mix well. Chill.

title: hamburger helper without the box
directions: Brown meat and add seasonings and cheese and mix in cooked pasta.
Serves 2 children.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash.
Drain.
Season with salt, pepper and 4 tablespoons oleo.
Mix soup, sour cream, onion, carrots and pimento.
Place half of dressing in bottom of casserole.
Put squash mixture in middle. Use other half of dressing mix on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: minnie's chili
directions: Brown beef and onion together.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 2 hours.

title: german potato salad
directions: In skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove and crumble.
Cook onion in drippings until tender.
Blend in soup, water, vinegar, sugar and pepper.
Add potatoes, parsley and bacon.
Heat.
Stir constantly, but gentle.

title: mee-ma's chicken pie
directions: Place cut up chicken in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Mix soups together; spoon soup over chicken.
For crust, mix Bix-Mix, milk and baking powder together with wire whisk until well mixed.
Spoon over chicken and soup.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Mixed vegetables may be added before baking.

title: baked crabmeat and shrimp supreme
directions: Combine all ingredients together, except crumbs.
Put in a Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle top with the buttered crumbs and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
May be prepared ahead of time and refrigerated.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: brown bread
directions: Combine milk, brown sugar, oil, honey and salt.
Heat until just warm.
Combine yeast, 2 cups flour, whole wheat flour and rye flour.
Add liquid mixture to dry mixture.
Beat at low speed in electric mixer for 3 minutes, scraping constantly.
Beat 5 minutes at high speed.
Stir in additional 4 1/2 cups flour.
Knead 8 to 10 minutes.
Let rise until double.
Punch down.
Let rise 10 minutes. Shape into 4 loaves.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: chop suey
directions: Cut up meat into small chunks.
Brown meat in a deep kettle in either bacon fat or oil.
When meat is browned, add water to cover above meat and about 1/2 cup of soy sauce.
Bring to boil and turn down until meat is tender (about 1 hour).
Add chopped onion after adding water.
When meat is done, take out some liquid and add flour to thicken.
Pour back into pot and stir.
Continue to add flour until as thick as you would like.
Add can of vegetables and cooked fresh mushrooms, if desired.
Add remaining 1/2 cup soy sauce.
Serve over rice and/or oriental noodles.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar. Add vanilla, then eggs, beating after each one. Mix in 1/2 of the flour, then 1/2 milk, another 1/2 of flour and rest of milk. Drop by spoonful onto baking sheet. Bake about 10 to 12 minutes at 375°. Makes about 5 dozen.

title: karen's garden microwave casserole
directions: Clean beans; bias-cut into 1-inch pieces.
Thinly bias-slice carrots.
Cut corn from cobs.
In large (1 1/2-quart) microwave-safe casserole dish, combine beans and water.
Cook on High for 4 minutes (6 minutes in low wattage oven).
Stir once. Add carrots and corn; cook, covered, on High 5 minutes more (7 minutes for low wattage oven).
Stir once.
Stir in 3/4 cup cheese, couscous, milk, salt and pepper.
Cook, covered, on High for 3 to 4 minutes (4 to 5 minutes on low wattage oven), or until heated through and all vegetables are crisp and tender, stirring once.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup cheese on top.
Makes 6 servings.

title: gazpacho ally
directions: I use a food processor.
Coarsely chop tomatoes*.
Core, seed and coarsely chop peppers.
Peel and coarsely chop onion.
Peel, seed and coarsely chop cucumber.
Combine in bowl with cilantro, parsley, vinegar, olive oil, V-8 juice and salt and pepper to taste.
Chill overnight to ripen flavors.
Serves 8 to 10 in chilled soup bowls with toasted croutons.

title: rosamarina salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on box.
Drain and save juice from pineapple and oranges.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar, salt, flour and juice from fruits.
Stir until blended.
Then cook until thick. Cool.
Mix with macaroni.
Let stand overnight.
Add fruit and Cool Whip next day and serve.

title: stuffed artichokes
directions: Cut stems from artichokes and 1 inch from top of bulb.
Peel away first row of leaves from bottom of choke.
Bang artichoke against sink to loosen leaves.
Spread leaves slightly apart while washing under cold water.
Leave upside-down to drain.
Combine all dry ingredients and fill into the artichokes.
Place stuffed chokes in a pot large enough so all chokes are standing up side by side, one layer only.
Add water (enough to cover chokes halfway). Sprinkle oil on top of chokes; add a little water.
Add pinch of salt to water.
Bring to a boil; lower flame to simmer.
Cover and cook for 45 minutes.
Every 10 minutes, add water so level remains halfway on chokes.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Combine in large kettle and heat until sugar is dissolved. Cool and reheat.
Flavor is best if prepared the day before. Serve hot in mugs.

title: special k peanut butter cookies
directions: Bring dark and white syrups and sugar to a boil in 2-quart saucepan. Boil to full rolling boil, then remove from heat.
Add salt, vanilla and peanut butter. Mix until smooth. Add cereal and stir thoroughly until all cereal is coated.
Spoon onto waxed paper or foil. Serve when cooled.

title: meat loaf for large party
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Divide into 3 large (14 x 10-inch) Pyrex dishes.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serve hot.
Should serve 25 to 30 people.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Cream the cheese and salad dressing, thinned out with a little milk (not too much).
Add the rest of the ingredients; stir until well blended.

title: party punch
directions: Place 1 cherry in each square of ice cube tray.
Fill with water and freeze.
Soften juice; add ice cream.
Add sherbet, ginger ale and ice cubes.

title: nut cups
directions: To make dough, cut cream cheese and butter in flour and cream. Mix brown sugar, butter, vanilla, salt and nuts together for filling.
Place dough in the small miniature muffin pans shaping dough to sides.
Add the mix 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix cocoa and powdered sugar.
Cut oleo into pieces and place them on top of the mixture.
Add evaporated milk.
Microwave on High power for 2 minutes.
Stir in vanilla.
Mix well. Refrigerate before serving.

title: nonie's meat pies
directions: Brown ground meat slightly.
Add next five ingredients until onion looks clear.
Put in a 9-inch deep dish pie crust and put pie crust on top.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: oatmeal bars
directions: Combine flour, oats, brown sugar and nutmeg in mixing bowl. Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Press half of mixture into bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake 5 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread apple pie filling mixed with cinnamon over crust.
Sprinkle with remaining oat mixture, pat lightly.
Continue baking 25 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool and cut into bars.
Makes 24 servings.
Freezes well.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam. Spread the nuts on the bottom of pan and then layer the coconut. Mix cake according to the directions on box and pour over the coconut. Melt the butter and add in the cream cheese; blend it until it is fluffy. Add the powdered sugar slowly and continue blending. (I use a small electric mixer on low speed.) Pour this on top of the cake mix and spread it around slightly, mixing into the cake. Bake for 45 minutes. It will have craters in it when done. Cool and enjoy.

title: cinnamon cookies
directions: Beat eggs and water until light and fluffy.
Beat in sugar replacement and cinnamon.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt in sifter; sift half of the dry ingredients over egg mixture.
Fold to completely blend.
Repeat with remaining dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets, 2 to 3-inches (1 cm) apart.
Bake at 375°F (190°C) for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yield: 20 cookies.

title: antipasto salad
directions: In a large bowl, stir together the corn oil, vinegar, garlic, salt and red pepper.
Add warm macaroni and Parmesan cheese; toss to coat well.
Cover.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Add broccoli, pepperoni and tomatoes; toss until well mixed.
Serve on lettuce-lined platter.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
If desired, garnish with red onion rings.
Makes 6 servings.

title: orange cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put in greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Top with topping.

title: old-fashioned bran muffins
directions: Combine cereal and milk; let stand until most of moisture is taken up.
Add egg and shortening; beat well.
Sift together remaining ingredients; add to cereal mixture, stirring only until combined.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake in 400° oven about 25 minutes.
Makes about 9 muffins.

title: chocolate pixies
directions: In large saucepan over low heat, melt margarine and chocolate, stirring constantly until smooth.
Remove from heat; cool slightly.
Stir in flour, sugar, nuts, baking powder, salt and eggs; mix well.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Heat oven to 300°.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll in powdered sugar, coating heavily.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 300° for 13 to 18 minutes, or until set.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet.
Cool completely.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: red cherry dream squares
directions: In large bowl combine cake mix, six tablespoons margarine and one cup oats until crumbly. Reserve one cup of this mix for topping. To remaining mix add egg, then pat into bottom of greased 9x13 pan. Pour cherry mixture on crust. To reserved topping mix add last two tablespoons margarine, 1/4 cup oats, nuts and brown sugar. Mix well and sprinkle over cherries. Bake at 350 degrees about 35 minutes. Cool and serve with whipped cream. What a treat!

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Place crescent rolls on greased pizza pan and bring up sides as you would for pizza.
Sprinkle sausage and bacon that have been browned and cut into small pieces on crust.
Beat eggs and pour on top and cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Buy it at the store.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Spread rolls in pizza pan with points toward center.
Seal edges.
Cook meat and drain.
Sprinkle on crust.
Sprinkle hash browns over meat.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.
For crispier crust, bake 5 to 10 minutes first.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish that has a cover.
Mix in all ingredients.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except shrimp. The night before serving, add shrimp before serving.	Serve with crackers.

title: chilled lentil salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except parsley.
Cover and refrigerate about 3 hours, until chilled.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: In a medium skillet, heat oil over medium heat.
Add garlic and chili powder; cook 30 seconds.
Add drained and rinsed beans and cook, mashing slightly with back of wooden spoon.
Stir in 1/4 cup water and cook over low heat 5 minutes.

title: fluffy fruit dip
directions: In a small bowl, combine sour cream and preserves or marmalade. Cut up any large pieces of fruit and walnuts.
Mix well.
Stir in enough milk to make mixture of dipping consistency.
Chill.

title: southern fried fish
directions: Mix fish, corn meal and seasoning.
Heat oil until hot.
Cook fish until golden brown.
Serve with baked beans, cole slaw, French fries, hush puppies or rolls.

title: jello surprise
directions: Make Jell-O with hot water. Add all other ingredients except sour cream. Put half in an 11-inch flat pan and add the rest in a bowl. Refrigerate for 2 hours. Spread sour cream over flat bed of Jell-O. Add rest of Jell-O mixture. Smooth out and serve.

title: chicken with tokay grape sauce
directions: Slice green pepper and onion in thin slices and brown slightly in butter.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon of brown sugar.
Thin 1 cup chili sauce with 1/2 cup cider vinegar.
Add to onion mixture and bring to a boil.
Last 5 minutes, add grapes, split and deseeded. Allow to cool and store in refrigerator.
Bake chicken pieces and last 15 minutes, add sauce and finish cooking.

title: drunken chicken
directions: Remove excess fat from chicken breasts.
Pierce breasts with a fork on both sides.
Place chicken in a frying pan.
Fill pan with wine up to the halfway mark of chicken.
Poach chicken for approximately 7 minutes on each side.
Add wine if it falls below the halfway mark during poaching.
Remove chicken and place on a bed of noodles.

title: pecan tea cakes
directions: On a piece of wax paper, combine flour and salt.
Set aside. In a large mixing bowl, with electric mixer, beat margarine until fluffy.
Add powdered sugar and vanilla, beating until well blended.
Gradually add flour mixture and beat well. Stir in pecans.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Combine
sugar,
butter,
syrup
and
salt.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Beat in soda and stir.
Stir in nuts.
Place popcorn in large
shallow
pan;
pour sugar mixture over corn.
Stir. Bake at 200° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes or until done. When done, popcorn will no longer be sticky.
Time of preparation: 1 hour.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion, celery and pepper in 1 tablespoon butter. Add rest of ingredients and slowly cook for about 1 hour or until thickened.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese, potato chips and almonds.
Place in a large rectangular dish.
Top with cheese, potato chips and almonds.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator. Bake in 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: baked caramel popcorn
directions: Stir margarine, sugar and syrup over medium heat until it boils.
Let boil 5 minutes without stirring.
Remove from heat and stir in 1 teaspoon vanilla, 1/2 teaspoon soda and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Slowly pour over corn, which is in large pan.
Stir until well coated.
Bake in shallow pans at 200° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool completely and break apart.
Store in tightly covered containers lined with plastic bags.
Will keep as long as sealed.

title: all night cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat egg whites to hold stiff peaks. Add sugar, beating all the time.
Add cream of tartar, salt and vanilla.
Fold in chocolate chips, not melted, and pecans.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheets.
Put in oven and turn off heat.
Leave overnight or 6 hours.
Makes about 50.

title: carrot loaf
directions: Cook carrots in boiling salted water; mash.
Make white sauce by heating 1 cup milk in double boiler and add thickening.
Add 2 teaspoons butter.
Cook until thick.
Mix all together; put into buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° until set.

title: boneless chicken breast with stuffing
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Lay breast pieces in bottom of pan.
Cover chicken well with Swiss cheese.
Cover cheese with stuffing mix.
Shake any seasoning left on top of dry mix.
Melt oleo and drizzle on top of stuffing mix.
Pour about 1/2 to 3/4 of broth just in the corners of pan, but not over top of stuffing. Cover with foil and bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.

title: french mustard dressing
directions: Save empty Grey Poupon jar.
Put all ingredients in jar. Shake well.
Store in refrigerator.

title: mama's pound cake
directions: Whip butter and sugar with mixer.
Using mixer, add one egg at a time.
Continue to beat with mixer while adding small amounts of unwhipped cream and flour alternately with each egg.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla or lemon flavoring or both.
Grease and flour tube pan; shake out excess flour.
Pour cake into pan and place in cold oven.
Set at 325° and cook for 1 hour.

title: easy brunswick stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 5-quart slow cooker.
Cook, covered, at high for 6 hours and 30 minutes.
Yields 14 cups.

title: crock-pot beef stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot. Cook 8 to 10 hours.

title: kentucky corn pudding
directions: Measure 1 quart of shelled corn.
Soak overnight in hot water. In the morning, put it in an iron or granite kettle with warm water to cover.
For each quart of corn, add 1 tablespoon of baking soda and boil until the husks come off readily.

title: salad delight
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, dissolve jello in boiling water.
Cool. Save out 1/2 cup apricot nectar.
Add rest of can of nectar and drained pineapple to jello.
Cover top with marshmallows and let set in refrigerator.
Cook saved 1/2 cup apricot nectar, pineapple juice with water added to equal 1/2 cup, flour, sugar, margarine and beaten egg until thick.
Cool.
Whip whipping cream and fold into cooked mixture.
Spread on jelled part.
Sprinkle on grated cheese.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients with Miracle Whip.
Refrigerate overnight.
The cheese can be added if you want.

title: cheese soup
directions: Combine potatoes, carrots, celery, onions, butter and broth. Cook 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Mix milk, flour and parsley.
Add to vegetables and let thicken a little.
Then add Cheez Whiz and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and serve.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown meat and onion. Add other ingredients. Bring to a boil. Put in baking dish and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Cut cake into small squares and line bottom of dish.
Thaw strawberries.
Mix strawberries and jello together and let stand for few minutes.
Prepare pudding according to the directions on the box.
Pour strawberry mixture over cake.
Pour pudding over strawberry mixture.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar to eggs gradually, continuing to beat. Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour into gallon freezer.

title: potato rolls
directions: Measure water in mixing bowl.
Add yeast and dissolve.
Stir in sugar, salt, shortening, eggs and potatoes.
Mix in flour with hands until dough is easy to handle.
Turn onto lightly floured board and knead until smooth.
Place in greased bowl and cover with damp cloth.
Let rise in refrigerator for 6 to 8 hours.
Use as needed.
Take out of refrigerator and let rise amount that is needed.
Bake at 425° until brown.
You don't have to roll these out.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into greased casserole.
Bake 25 minutes or until firm.
Top with grated cheese or almonds.

title: bacon-wrapped shrimp with creamy horseradish sauce
directions: Wrap 1 shrimp around 1 water chestnut.
Wrap in 1 bacon piece and secure with toothpick.
Repeat with remaining shrimp, water chestnuts and bacon.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter in heavy large skillet over high heat.
Add half of shrimp and cook until bacon browns, about 2 1/2 minutes per side.
Transfer to large gratin dish.
Repeat with remaining butter and shrimp.
Preheat broiler. Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and beat until blended.
Spoon sauce over shrimp.
Broil until top is golden brown.
Divide shrimp among plates and serve.

title: easy biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients.
Roll out on floured surface.
Roll out small biscuits.

title: no cook fruit dessert
directions: Drain first 3 ingredients.
Stir in strawberries, then add banana, sliced.

title: date balls
directions: Cook together the dates, sugar, beaten egg and margarine; boil gently for 10 minutes.
Stir constantly, as it burns easily.
Let cool about 10 minutes, then add the vanilla, Rice Krispies and nuts.
Roll into small balls, then dip in coconut.

title: date bars
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients until light thickness.
Mix together. In middle add 1/2 cup walnuts (cut small).
Mix in dry ingredients. Add 1 1/2 squares margarine or butter.
Mix by hand.
Pour 2/3 of this preparation in square pan, about 9-inch square or 6 x 10-inches.
Add dates on oatmeal preparation.
Press evenly and add walnuts cut in pieces; press also.
Add rest of mix on top.
Press again.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Let cool.
Cut into bars.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine and egg and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then blend with mixer, cream cheese, sugar and 2 eggs. Spread over first mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: snowballs
directions: Cream butter and honey.
Mix well with flour, salt and vanilla.
Add nuts and form into small (3/4-inch) balls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm and again when cool.
Flavor improves with age.

title: italian pizzelles
directions: Beat eggs and sugar, add cooled melted butter or margarine, add anise oil.
Sift flour and baking powder, add to egg
mixture. Batter will be stiff enough to be dropped by spoon onto hot pizzelle maker.
These pizzelles are light and crisp and very thin.
To keep them crisp, store in an airtight container.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: french onion soup
directions: Cook onions in butter and oil, covered, over low heat for 15 minutes.
Uncover, increase to moderate heat.
Add sugar and salt. Cook 30 to 40 minutes, stirring often.
Blend in flour; stir three minutes until smooth.
Stir in bouillon and one can of water.
Boil remaining two cans water and add to mixture along with vermouth, salt and pepper. Simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Toast French bread on both sides.
Top with cheese and broil until it melts.
Pour soup in bowls and top with a slice of bread.

title: sour cream yeast rolls
directions: Combine 3 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast in large bowl of electric mixer.
Heat sour cream, water and butter until warm.
Add to flour mixture and beat on low speed of mixer.
Add eggs; continue beating.
Add remaining 1 cup flour to make soft dough. Place dough in large greased bowl.
Cover with plastic wrap and allow to rise until double in bulk, about 1 1/2 hours.
Turn dough out onto floured pastry cloth or board.
Knead slightly to coat with flour for easier handling.
Shape dough into 24 balls and place in well-greased muffin cups.
Brush tops of dough with melted butter.
Let rise until doubled.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken fruit salad(this recipe is great for a meeting luncheon.)
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Serve on 6 to 8 lettuce leaves. Garnish with apple quarters, if desired.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: milk 'n honey cake
directions: Mix together in mixing bowl until creamy the sugar and butter or margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.

title: pork chops and potatoes
directions: Alternate layers of potatoes with mixture (water, soup and sour cream).
Top with chops.
Bake at 375° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: sunday roasts
directions: *Allow at least 1/4 pound meat per serving.
Choose for example,
a beef rump and a pork shoulder roaster of approximately the same weight.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Combine meat, onion and water.
Cook until meat is no longer pink.
Break meat apart while cooking so that the meat particles will be small.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer several hours.
May be simmered in a crock-pot.

title: instant sorbet
directions: Peel bananas, wrap tightly in plastic wrap and freeze for 4 to 6 hours or overnight.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes; drain well.
Mix other ingredients.
Add broccoli and pour into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with buttered Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm in center.
Serves 8 to 10.
Recipe can easily be halved.

title: snow ice cream
directions: Combine milk, sugar and vanilla.
