Quickly beat in snow or crushed ice until consistency is similar to ice cream.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and dry ingredients and soda mixture.
Mix well and add fruits and nuts.
The dough is very stiff; use hands to mix.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Keep stored in airtight container. Also can be frozen.

title: cheesy pineapple spread
directions: Place cheeses, pineapple and pecans in work bowl of food processor, or in a small mixing bowl.
Process or mix until combined.

title: peanut butter eggs
directions: In mixer bowl, cream butter.
Add peanut butter, Marshmallow Creme and vanilla.
Mix well.
Gradually add sugar, adding more or less for an easily shaped dough.
Mix well.
Knead dough a few minutes by hand or with a kneading attachment to mixer.
Mold dough by hand into egg shapes or balls and place on wax paper. Melt chocolate in double boiler or in microwave oven.
Dip eggs, one at a time.
Place on wax paper.
Freeze 1 hour.
Store in refrigerator or freezer.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Pressure cook chicken until it falls off of the bone.
Remove chicken from bones and place shredded chicken in a buttered 12-inch casserole dish.
Top with the undiluted soup.
Prepare Stove Top stuffing as directed except substitute juice from cooking chicken for the water.
Spoon over soup and gently pour milk over all. Cover and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: mom's cranberry relish
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in boiling water.
Chill until beginning to thicken.
Put orange (peels and all), apple, celery, lemon and nuts into blender.
Blend until fairly small.
Add to Jell-O.
Pour into mold and let set.

title: sausage - cheese balls
directions: Mix ingredients and form into small balls and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Can be made up and put on cookie sheet and frozen, then bagged.
To reheat, put in 300° oven for 15 minutes.
Can also be frozen after initial baking.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Add beaten egg, chopped onion, mayo, undiluted soup, cheese and salt.
Mix well and place in greased casserole (1 1/2-quart).
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Freezable.

title: ceci salad
directions: Drain beans and marinate at least 1 hour in Ranch and Italian dressing combined.
Sprinkle with dill weed, salt and pepper to taste.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Combine sugar, salt, butter, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder and nuts.
Blend well.
Spread in 15 x 11-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake 45 minutes in 375° oven.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Heat oil in heavy skillet.
Saute garlic, green pepper and onion until transparent.
Add meat and cook until brown.
Add other ingredients.
Saute mushrooms and add last.
Simmer slowly all day, stirring occasionally.

title: crisp golden chicken
directions: Dip chicken in milk and egg.
Then roll in flour mixture. Bake 45 minutes on one side, then 45 minutes on other side.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix gently together and place in buttered casserole.
Top with 1 cup grated cheese and sprinkle with 1 cup cracker crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: artichoke chicken
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Cook garlic in butter 1 minute. Add chicken.
Cook until light brown.
In medium bowl, combine sour cream, soup, cheese and wine.
Remove chicken and cut into chunks, bigger than a bite.
Return to skillet.
Add mixture to chicken. Cook over medium-low until chicken is done and tender.
Stir sauce. Add artichokes (can cut into smaller pieces if desired).
Cook a few more minutes.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In large mixing bowl, cream together butter, oil, sugar, salt, eggs, vanilla and water.
Sift together remaining dry ingredients.
Add to liquid ingredients and mix well.
Add grated zucchini and stir until blended.
Pour into prepared pan and bake 40 to 45 minutes or until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool and frost with favorite icing.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Mix well. Add eggs one at a time.
Beat mixture after adding each egg.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Add flour mixture to the chocolate mixture.
Chill dough thoroughly.
Form small balls of dough.
Roll balls in 4X powdered sugar.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: no bake chocolate bars
directions: Combine first
ingredients
and
heat until slightly thick. Add next
ingredients
and
spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Chill.
Mix butter, powdered sugar and milk; spread over first mixture and
chill.
Melt
chocolate bar and spread over the other layers.
Mark into squares before it cools.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Put layer of crushed potato chips in greased baking dish.
Mix the chicken, celery, onion, salad dressing, cream of chicken soup and water chestnuts; pour mixture over potato chips.
Top with cheese.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together; blend well. Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes or until well done.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Combine margarine, flour, sugar and 1/4 cup pecans.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; cool.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate cheese and mix with other ingredients.
Cook at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: zucchini relish(makes 8 pints)
directions: Put the first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Sprinkle with canning salt.
Drain well.
Let stand overnight.
In large kettle, mix remaining ingredients.
Add vegetables.
Bring to a boil.
Put in pint jars.
Process 20 minutes.

title: white chili
directions: Combine beans, chicken broth, garlic and half of the onions in a large soup pot.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until beans are soft, 3 hours or more.
Add more chicken broth if needed.
In a skillet, saute remaining onions in oil until tender. Add chilies and seasonings; mix thoroughly.
Add to bean mixture. Add chicken and simmer 1 hour.
Serve topped with grated cheese. Serve with cornbread.

title: turtles
directions: Melt caramels in milk in saucepan.
Add pecans.
Spoon by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Melt enough chocolate chips to cover pecan candies.
I also add a little paraffin wax to the chocolate so it covers better.
Cool chocolate-covered candies for a couple hours before serving. Yields about 5 dozen.

title: vicki's carrot cake
directions: In mixing bowl, combine dry ingredients. Add oil and eggs, mix on low speed until well blended. Stir in carrots and nuts. Pour into three (3) 9in or (2) 12in. greased and floured pans. Bake at 325 degrees for 45 min. or until done.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes.
Cut potatoes into thin slices, but do not go all the way through.
Put in a baking dish, sprinkle with salt and put butter and the different herbs on the potatoes.
Bake at 425° for about 50 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with cheeses and put back into oven for another 10 to 15 minutes until lightly browned or until the cheeses are melted.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add onion and celery.
Saute until tender.
Add soups and cooked noodles.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven and add a medium bottle of sliced stuffed olives (optional).
Bake 15 minutes longer.
Serves 12.

title: dandelion coffee
directions: Wash and peel roots.
Roast in a low temperature oven for 4 hours or until roots are brittle.
Grind like coffee beans.
Use as ground coffee, except a slightly smaller amount of ground dandelion roots is required to equal the strength of coffee.

title: cajun potato salad
directions: Wash potatoes, do not peel.
Cut into large cubes.
Cook, and drain well.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to potatoes. Toss until potatoes are well coated with mixture.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: quick cupcake cones(after school delights!)
directions: You will need 1 empty plastic foam egg carton.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Put blueberries and pineapple with juice into 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar on top.
Melt margarine and drizzle on top of cake mix.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar on top of that.
Sprinkle pecans on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: guadalupe river dessert
directions: Mix together and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate pies
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa well.
Then mix all ingredients together and bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Bake in 4 pie crusts.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar and oil.
Beat well.
Add the remaining ingredients and blend well.
Grease and flour 2 large or 3 small loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: yum-yum coffee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Pour half of batter into an 8 x 12-inch pan.
Cover with half of nut mixture.
Pour rest of batter in the pan and cover with remaining Nut Mixture.

title: lime pie
directions: Mix together the Eagle Brand milk and lime juice.
Add Cool Whip and coloring.
Pour into pie shell and refrigerate.
You can use 2 regular baked pie shells.
Garnish with kiwi slice and arrange over top of pie, if desired.

title: rice casserole
directions: Season meat and pile in the center of a greased casserole. Mix eggs, milk, rice, margarine and seasonings.
Pour over the meat.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
A good way to use up that dab of leftover meat.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Set oven on 350° before starting.
Beat egg whites and salt until stiff.
Add sugar, beat.
Add vanilla, chips, and pecans. Line cookie sheet with foil, shiny side up.
Drop by teaspoons full onto cookie sheet.
Turn oven off and put cookies in.
Leave in oven until oven turns cool.

title: low-fat chili
directions: Fry hamburger; drain fat.
Rinse under hot water to remove excess fat.
Combine all ingredients; simmer 4 to 7 minutes.
This makes a very thick chili, so you may want to add more tomato juice or water.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix apricot nectar, orange juice and sugar and bring to a boil.
Add	orange	jello.	Let
congeal.
Then
top
with Philadelphia
cream
cheese
and pineapple mixed with nuts and put on top of jello.
Sprinkle some nuts on top.

title: bread pudding with vanilla sauce
directions: In a large bowl combine bread cubes and raisins. In a medium saucepan combine milk and 1/4 cup butter. Heat stirring occasionally until milk is steaming and butter is almost melted. pour hot milk mixture over bread and raisins. Let stand for 10 minutes. Meanwhile grease a 1 1/2 quart casserole dish and set aside. In a small bowl slightly beat eggs. Stir in 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon, vanilla and nutmeg. Stir the egg

mixture into the bread mixture. Pour it in the casserole dish. Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 50 to 55 minutes or until the surface is puffed and a knife inserted near center comes out clean. Cool slightly.

title: spaghetti carbonara
directions: Boil water for pasta.
Cook bacon; crumble.
Save 2 tablespoons grease and saute onion in it.
Combine last 4 ingredients.
Add bacon and onion.
Pour over cooked pasta. Makes 4 servings.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt butter and add brown sugar. Beat in eggs. Mix in flour, baking powder, vanilla and nuts. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 10-15 minutes until lightly browned.

title: ham casserole(a good way to use leftover ham)
directions: Early in the day, butter and lightly toast bread.
Cube and place in bottom of a buttered 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Arrange diced ham on top.
Over this, put the cubed cheese.
Mix together flour, dry mustard, salt and pepper.
Spread evenly over top. Pour melted butter over this.
Beat together eggs and milk and pour over all.
Cover the dish and let set in the refrigerator a few hours.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour (covered) and serve.

title: cold broccoli salad
directions: Mix together and set aside the vinegar, mayonnaise and sugar. Mix broccoli, onion, bacon and cheese.
Pour in the liquid mixture. Refrigerate overnight.

title: coconut cake
directions: Sprinkle 6 ounces (frozen) coconut on greased 9 x 13-inch or 12-inch square pan.
Mix a box of (yellow) cake mix according to directions on box.
Pour on top of coconut.
Bake according to directions on box.
Heat 2 cups milk, 1 cup sugar and vanilla until sugar dissolves and pretty hot.
Prick the cake while warm and spoon "milk and sugar" over cake.
Let this cool.
Spread 9 ounces Cool Whip over top.
Sprinkle another 6 ounces coconut on top.

title: pesto potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes (unpeeled) until tender.
Drain and slice in half.
Place remaining ingredients in blender jar and puree.
Toss potatoes gently with dressing.
Let stand at least 1 hour before serving.

title: two minute pimento cheese spread
directions: Drain pimentos and combine all ingredients except milk.
Mix well.
Slowly add milk to desired consistency.
Cover and refrigerate for up to 2 weeks.
You can add additional Miracle Whip to make creamier.

title: crab meat mousse
directions: In a heatproof bowl, sprinkle the gelatin over 1/4 cup of cold water and let it soften for 5 minutes.
Set the bowl over a pan of simmering water and stir the mixture until the gelatin is dissolved.
In a bowl, whisk together the gelatin, mayonnaise, lime and lemon juices, parsley, chives, mustard, salt and white pepper. Stir in the cream and the crab meat.
Spoon the mousse into a buttered 1-quart ring mold and chill it, covered with plastic wrap, for at least 2 hours and up to 24 hours.
Run a thin knife around the edge of the mold.
Dip the mold briefly in hot water and invert the mousse onto a serving plate.
Pour dressing over the mold.

title: glazed onions
directions: Peel onions; add water to cover and cook until tender and drain.
Melt butter and sugar in heavy skillet.
Add onions and cook over low heat 15 minutes or until golden brown, stirring occasionally.
Serves 6.

title: chicken delicious
directions: In an 8-inch square dish, place salted chicken breasts on 2 slices of chipped beef.
Place bacon pieces on top of chicken. Mix soup and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Cover and cook 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Uncover and cook until bacon browns (may turn on broiler briefly).
Eight or 10 chicken breasts may be used.

title: german rum cake(marble)
directions: Cream the Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well. Alternately add the vanilla, rum and milk with the cake flour and baking powder.
Mix well, then pour 3/4 of the batter into a greased Bundt or angel food pan.

title: baked rattlesnake
directions: Cut the snake into 3-inch pieces and place in a baking dish.

title: mini quiches
directions: Grease 2 dozen 1 3/4-inch muffin pans.
Separate each roll in half and press into pans to make a shell.
Place one shrimp in each shell.
Combine egg, cream, brandy, salt and pepper.
Divide evenly among shells, using about 2 teaspoons for each .
Slice cheese into 24 small triangles and place on top of filling.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: cow patties(school fudge)
directions: In saucepan, over medium heat, melt butter.
Add sugar, milk, cocoa and salt.
Let boil 1 minute; cut off.
Stir in peanut butter until blended.
Stir in oatmeal; mix well.
Add vanilla. Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet forming patties or put in greased pan and cut into squares after being refrigerated.

title: salmon salad sandwiches
directions: Combine salmon, cucumber, mayonnaise and dressing; blend well. Spread margarine on buns.
Place 1/4 cup salmon mixture on half of each bun; top with other half.
Enjoy.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients; place in greased loaf pan.
Bake one hour at 350°.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic powder.
Add tomato sauce, paste and spices.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Boil noodles.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease Dutch oven.
Spread a small amount of sauce over the bottom.
Layer noodles, sauce and cheese three times.
Bake uncovered for 30 minutes.

title: potato cheese puffs
directions: Combine ingredients, except oil; mix well.
Pour about 2 inches of oil into a saucepan or frying pan and heat to 375°. Drop batter by tablespoons, 4 or 5 at a time, into the oil.
Fry 3 to 4 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve immediately.

title: crabcakes(cook now in deep fat fryer or freezes well.)
directions: Sprinkle crabmeat with lemon juice and set aside.
Remove crusty ends from bread and break into small pieces.
Place in large bowl.
Add eggs.
Mix eggs and bread.
Add Worcestershire, mayonnaise, salt, pepper, mustard and paprika.
Form into cakes. Makes approximately 7 crabcakes per pound of crabmeat.
Flash freeze on cookie sheets and store in freezer in plastic freezer bags.
This way you can take out only as many as needed and they won't stick together.
Thaw before cooking and the center will be done when the crabcakes are golden brown.
This recipe makes approximately 3 dozen.

title: ryals pound cake
directions: Beat together at room temperature the butter, Crisco, flavoring, sugar and eggs; beat well.
Then add flour and milk. Grease and flour pan (Bundt or cake).
Bake 1 hour and 45 minutes at 325°.

title: cherry salad supreme
directions: Dissolve raspberry jello in water, then add pie filling.
Put in a 7 x 13-inch Pyrex dish. Chill until thick.

title: grilled jalapeno dove
directions: Marinate dove in dressing overnight.
Cut jalapeno peppers in half.
Stuff each dove with pepper.
Wrap bacon around dove and secure with a toothpick.
Cook over hot coals until bacon is brown and dove is done.
Baste, while cooking, with marinade.

title: peggy's hash browns
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
After done, top with cornflakes and 1 stick of butter.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix ingredients with mayonnaise and refrigerate.
Add 1 medium-sized bag of shoestring potatoes just before serving (tuna can be substituted).
This recipe can be used to serve a large group by just increasing all ingredients and by adding the shoestring potatoes to it.

title: raspberry bake cake
directions: Mix all together and beat well at high speed on mixer.
Bake at 375° in 13 x 9-inch pan until done.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Disjoint wings; discard tips.
Stir together all marinade ingredients.
Put wings in heavy plastic bag or marinating container.
Cover with marinade.
Marinate at least 2 hours. Overnight is best.
To cook, place in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 10 to 12 or less.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Blend in sour cream and 1/2 Cool Whip. Layer vanilla wafers and bananas.
Put some pudding over; keep layering until all used up.
Spread Cool Whip on top and garnish with cookie crumbs.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients. Put into greased casserole. Cover with topping.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut steak in serving size pieces.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Beat the flour into the steak.
Brown steak quickly in hot shortening.
Put steak in Dutch oven or roaster.
Add sliced onion and celery and cover with tomato juice.
Cook covered until tender in oven at 350°.

title: barbecued chicken wings or thighs or spareribs
directions: Combine everything but wings.
Pour over chicken in a baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours, turning occasionally.

title: 4 step gooey butter cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, 2 eggs and melted butter.
Spread in greased 9 x 13 Pyrex dish.
Mix cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar together.
Spread over cake mix and bake for 50 minutes at 325 degrees.

title: arliss's salsa sauce
directions: Mix together and bring to a boil in heavy pan.
Boil slowly to desired thickness, about 25 to 30 minutes.
Put in jars and process in water bath for 20 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 pints.

title: angel crisp cookies
directions: Cream sugars, shortening, egg, and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to sugar mixture.
Form into walnut sized balls.
Dip top half in water, then in sugar.
Place on greased sheet and press down in center with finger.
Bake at 400° for 8-20 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening until fluffy.
Add sugars, then eggs.
Beat. Blend in peanut butter.
Add flour.
Roll into balls.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: fire and ice
directions: Place onions, tomatoes and bell pepper in a bowl.
In saucepan, bring all remaining ingredients to a boil.
Boil one minute only.
While still hot, pour over vegetables.
Chill. Serves 6.
Great with steak or peas.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Melt oleo and cheese.
Cook broccoli as directed, drain and chop.
Add to cheese.
Mix well.

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread thinly on flour shells and roll up.
Cover with plastic wrap and chill overnight.
Slice and serve with salsa dip.
Will make 5 to 6 rolls.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Blend sugar and butter.
Add eggs and almond extract.
Add flour and mix.
Stir in cranberries.
Pour into 13 x 9 pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: fried chicken
directions: Season with salt and pepper; toss chicken in flour.
Let dry for 10 minutes.
Pour milk into a shallow bowl and dip chicken in milk, then coat
the chicken again in flour (save the rest for the gravy).
Fill the skillet with shortening; brown chicken on both sides.

title: sweet corn pone
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a heavy baking dish which has been greased and coated with corn meal.
Bake for 1 hour in a 400° oven.

title: chicken and mushrooms
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
In small bowl, combine soup and sour cream, then stir in mushrooms.
Spoon this on top of chicken. Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: cookie twists(koulourakia)
directions: Flour as
much as it takes to shape cookies.
Cream oil and butter.
Add
sugar, eggs (one at a time), juice, milk and vanilla;
beat
well.
Mix	flour
and
baking
powder; add to creamed mixture.
Roll small pieces of dough by hand and shape into cookie twist.	Small piece of dough (5-inches) in length. Bring together
the
ends overlapping and form a circle and close.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° or 375° until golden brown.

title: chocolate peanut butter crispy rice bars
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large saucepan, melt margarine and marshmallows over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; stir in cereal, peanut butter chips and peanuts until well coated.
Press mixture into prepared pan.
Cool.
Cut into bars. Makes 36 bars.

title: chocolate e'clair dessert
directions: Line oblong dish with graham crackers.	Mix milk with instant pudding.
After this thickens, fold in whipped topping and beat thoroughly.
Alternate pudding mixture with layers of crackers and end up with crackers on top.
(You may not need the whole box of graham crackers.)

title: chess cake
directions: Mix well the first 3 ingredients and press into the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then mix the 4 remaining ingredients together and pour on top of other mix.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.
Cake needs to be a light golden brown.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Heat flour in mixing bowl.
While flour is heating, dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water with the honey.
Dissolve molasses in 1 cup warm water.
Add yeast and honey to flour (after flour is heated).
Add salt to warm water.
Mixture should be gooey.
Put in pans.
Fill pans between 1/3 and 1/2 full of dough.
Let rise about 1 hour.
Put in oven (375°) for 45 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 3 loaves, 4 inches to 8 inches.

title: filled brownies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, salt, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Line baking pan with greased waxed paper.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Remove from pan; peel off waxed paper.
Cut in half.

title: spinach salad
directions: Toss ingredients together and serve with dressing.

title: peaches and cream cheese cake
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients in mixing bowl; beat at medium speed until smooth.
Pour mixture into greased 8-inch round cake pan.
Drain peaches, reserving 3 tablespoons of liquid; set aside. Arrange peaches over batter.
Combine cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and reserved peach juice; beat for 2 minutes at medium speed. Spoon mixture over peaches in center of cake, leaving a 1-inch border around edge of pan.
Combine 1 1/2 teaspoons sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over cream cheese filling.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove; cool and chill.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Mix stuffing according to directions on box.
Press into a casserole pan.
Mix soups, chicken and broccoli.
Pour over stuffing.
Top with grated cheese and crushed crackers.
Pour melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
tags: Stove Top chicken flavor stuffing mix

title: stir-fry chicken and broccoli
directions: In a large frying pan or wok, heat over medium-high heat.
Add chicken cubes and stir-fry 3 minutes, until chicken becomes opaque.
Remove with a slotted spoon and set aside.
Add broccoli; stir-fry 1 to 2 minutes.
Add mushrooms, scallions, soy sauce, sherry, ginger and sesame oil.
Stir-fry 2 more minutes.
Add dissolved cornstarch and reserved chicken.
Cook until heated through and sauce has thickened.
Serve over rice.

title: pineapple dump cake
directions: Spray a 13 x 9-inch pan with Mazola nonstick corn oil spray. Layer pineapple, coconut, cake mix and walnuts in the pan in the order given.
Sliver butter on top of the cake.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: orange jello
directions: In small bowl, combine jello, water, and orange juice. Set aside to chill until slightly firm. In large bowl, combine cream cheese and Dream Whip.
Beat until combined.
Fold in jello and drained oranges. Pour into jello mold and chill.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: hot bean salad
directions: Mix all together and simmer about 20 minutes.

title: pizza twists
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Separate and unroll breadsticks.
Place 3 pepperoni slices in single layer over one-half of each breadstick. Fold remaining half of breakstick over top; seal end and twist. Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Combine cheese, Italian seasoning and garlic powder.
Sprinkle evenly over each breadstick.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown. While pizza twists are in the oven, heat the pizza sauce in a small saucepan over low heat.
Dip pizza twists in pizza sauce and enjoy! Makes 8 pizza twists.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix sugar and egg.
Add the rest of the ingredients; mix well. Pour into greased and floured bread pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes, or until done.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together until well blended.
Add butter, corn syrup, salt, vanilla and chopped pecans and mix thoroughly. Pour into prepared unbaked pie shell.
Bake until filling is set. Bake about 1 1/4 hours at 350°.
Use 10 1/2-inch pie plate.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Mix well.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: scotch-a-rue's
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter until smooth.
Stir in Rice Krispies until well coated. Spread in a 13 x 9-inch buttered pan.

title: golden cheddar broccoli bake
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons margarine; stir in flour and salt.
Add milk gradually, mixing until smooth.
Cook until mixture boils, stirring constantly.
Add cheese, stirring until melted.
Add 1/4 cup corn flake crumbs and corn.
Arrange broccoli in an 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Pour cheese sauce over broccoli.
Toss remaining crumbs with 2 tablespoons margarine; sprinkle over casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: spirited eggnog(not for the minors at your table!)
directions: Beat the egg yolks in a large bowl with an electric mixer, gradually adding the sugar until the mixture is pale yellow. Set aside. Place the cream in another bowl and beat until it holds soft peaks. Stir milk into reserved egg yolk mixture. Then, using a large rubber spatula, fold in the whipped cream. Shortly before serving, gently stir in the bourbon and cognac.
Transfer to a punch bowl.

title: pecan crisp cookies
directions: Mix well and form into balls about the size of a quarter.
Dip a smooth bottom glass into a small amount of oil, then into a small amount of sugar.
Press ball thin and brush with egg white. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: squash dressing
directions: Cook squash; drain and mash.
Combine with bread crumbs. Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Mix with bread crumbs and squash.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well and pour into 8-inch greased square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
(Good with any kind of meat.)

title: grilled calypso chicken
directions: Gently loosen skin from chicken, using fingers, to form pocket between skin and meat.
Place 1 slice bacon in each pocket. Arrange chicken, skin sides up and thickest parts to outside edges, in 3-quart microwavable casserole.
Arrange potatoes around chicken.
Cover with plastic wrap, folding back one corner to vent. Microwave on High 10 to 12 minutes, rotating dish 1/2 turn after 5 minutes, until edges of chicken begin to cook; drain.
Stir red pepper into sauce.

title: ham and egg quiche
directions: One-half pound cooked sausage can be substituted for ground ham.

title: drop sand tarts
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Chill in refrigerator until stiff.
Place 1 teaspoon dough on ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: miss welsh's coconut cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt together. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine dry ingredients in large bowl. Make a well in the center.
In separate small bowl, mix remaining 5 ingredients together (mash strawberries).
Pour fruit mixture into well and gently stir by hand.
Pour into pans (two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans, greased and floured).
Bake 1 hour; let cool before slicing.

title: glazed ham loaf
directions: In medium bowl with fork, mix well first 7 ingredients. Grease 11 x 7-inch baking pan.
In pan, shape ham mixture into loaf.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Into 1-quart saucepan, drain the pineapple juice and reserve the pineapple slices.
Into pineapple juice, stir brown sugar and cornstarch until completely smooth.
Over medium heat, stir the mixture until thickened and boiling.
Remove from heat; stir in butter and lemon juice until well blended.
Remove ham loaf from oven; with a pastry brush, brush the meat loaf with pineapple and lemon juice glaze.
Overlap pineapple slices on top.
Bake 30 minutes longer, brushing occasionally with glaze.
Let stand 5 minutes for easier slicing.

title: fruit pie
directions: Put margarine in baking dish; let it melt.
Mix together flour, milk and sugar.
Pour over margarine and add drained fruit. Bake at 350° until done.

title: rice pudding
directions: Melt butter in loaf pan or cooking dish.
Mix in all the rest of the ingredients, saving the milk and vanilla until last.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes (uncovered).

title: chocolate yum-yum
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Press into 9 x 13-inch baking dish and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Allow to cool before adding.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Slice tops from whole red peppers; remove seeds.
Saute chopped red pepper, onion, mushrooms and wine in saucepan until tender.
Remove from heat.
Add 2 tablespoons wheat germ, corn, rice, cheese, garlic powder, rosemary and parsley; mix well. Spoon vegetable mixture into whole peppers.
Place in baking pan; top each with 1/2 teaspoon wheat germ.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt
butter
in electric skillet.
Add brown sugar and spread evenly
over
bottom
of skillet.
Drain pineapple and cherries. Arrange
fruit
on
butter and sugar mixture.
Pour cake batter, mixed according to directions on box, over fruit. Bake for approximately 25 minutes with vent closed, the last 5 minutes open
vent
for
steam to escape.
Immediately invert cake
out of
frypan
onto a serving platter.
Serve hot with whipped cream.

title: ham and scalloped potatoes casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl combine all ingredients. Mix well.
Spoon into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: corn fritters
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Stir in milk/juice mixture and egg.
Fry in hot oil, turning as needed until browned (3 to 4 minutes).
Serve with syrup or honey.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; add pineapple juice and cool. Pour sugar over cranberries and let stand while jello cools.
When jello begins to thicken, add cranberries, pineapple, celery and nut meats.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Add enough water to measure 1/2 cup.
Add syrup, orange juice and seasonings to cream cheese. Stir over low heat until smooth.
Add sweet potatoes, pineapple and 1/4 cup nuts; mix lightly.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole; sprinkle with additional nuts.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until hot.
Serves 6.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownies with pecans by directions.
Let cool in refrigerator.
Make pudding by directions.
Break up frozen candy bars in package with mallet until in small pieces.

title: butterfinger torte
directions: Cut angel food cake into pieces.
Place half in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix butter, yolks, vanilla and cream.
Spread half of this mixture over cake.
Sprinkle half of candy bars over the cream mixture.
Repeat layers and refrigerate.

title: spicy perk-a-punch
directions: Combine fruit juices and water in bottom of 30-cup electric percolator.
Place remaining ingredients in basket.
Percolate about 30 minutes.
Serve from percolator.
Makes 28 servings or 5 quarts.

title: raisin and pecan loaf
directions: Mix brown sugar, spices, salt and baking powder.
Beat eggs, add honey, cooking oil and flour.
Stir until it is a smooth batter, then add raisins and chopped pecans.
Pour into two loaf pans and bake at 325° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender until mixed thoroughly.
Pour into 10-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until top is brown.

title: eggplant fritters
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brush eggplant slices with olive oil, place on baking sheet and bake 20 minutes or until golden and tender.
Chop slices finely and combine in a bowl with egg, garlic, parsley, bread crumbs, Parmesan and Feta.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Let mix stand for 20 minutes.
If it looks very sloppy, add more bread crumbs.

title: blue cheese ball
directions: Blend cheeses.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Wrap in foil. Refrigerate.

title: baked beans for 25
directions: In large Dutch oven, brown beef over medium heat.
Drain off fat.
Add onion and celery and cook until tender.
Stir in soup, paste and catsup.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Add green, lima and wax beans that have been drained and all of the chili and pork and beans.
Stir well and put in kettle or roaster.
Add rest of ingredients.
Stir again.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix in order named and bake 20 to 30 minutes in a moderate oven at 350°.

title: stuffed snow pea pods
directions: Pour boiling water over fresh pea pods.
Let stand 1 minute. Drain and cut small incision about 1-inch along the lower side of pod.
Allow to cool.
Fill with mixture using a pastry bag. Yields about 24 to 36 pea pods.

title: oven crusted chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine butter, flour, salt, thyme, rosemary and marjoram.
Place crushed cereal in shallow dish.
Dip chicken in butter.
Roll in cereal.
Place on shallow rack in oven.
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: lorse's ham soup
directions: Boil ham hocks in water until tender.
Make sure there is 3 to 3 1/2 cups juice left, if not, add water.
Bring juice to a boil. Put in rice.
Cook 20 minutes on medium heat.
Add tomatoes.
Cook 5 to 7 minutes or until blended well.

title: pound cake
directions: Start with a cold oven.
Do not preheat oven. Cream margarine, shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing thoroughly after each addition.
Add flour and milk alternately, again mixing well after each addition.
Add flavorings.
Pour batter into a well greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: vanilla cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt well.
Add to hot milk.
Bring to boil and boil 2 minutes.
Add beaten egg yolk, return to heat and boil 2 more minutes, remove from heat and add butter and vanilla. Pour into pie crust.
Top with meringue.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Sift flour.
Add salt, baking powder and cocoa; sift again.
Add eggs, one at a time, to the butter and sugar mixture.
Add dry ingredients, alternating with the milk and vanilla.
After all ingredients are mixed, beat for 3 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into a 10-inch greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: mom's chicken soup
directions: Boil chicken, onions and oregano until chicken is well done. Remove chicken from bone and replace in broth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook slowly until vegetables are tender.

title: steak diane
directions: On cutting board, pound steaks until about 1/4-inch thick. Sprinkle lightly with salt.
In 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, in hot butter, cook steaks until browned, turning steaks once.
Stir in shallots and cook, stirring until tender.
Add sherry and heat.
Pour brandy over steaks.
With a match, set aflame; turn steaks once or twice until flaming stops.
Serve immediately.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix
all together. Pour into baking dish and sprinkle with cinnamon. Dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix ingredients together in order given and chill before serving.

title: sopa caliente
directions: Heat oil; add tomatoes and green pepper and cook until soft. Add chilies, tomatoes and green chilies and chicken broth.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in milk, cheese and salt, making sure the soup does not boil.
Serve as soon as cheese melts.
Top with sour cream, more chopped green chilies and toasted sunflower seeds. Serves 4.

title: zucchini oatmeal muffins
directions: Grease muffin pan.
Preheat oven to 400°.

title: chicken vegetable soup
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
In a large pot, brown chicken in just enough olive oil to cover bottom of pot (approximately 2 tablespoons).
Add onion and garlic.
Stir until onion is clear.
Do not have fire too high as olive oil burns easily.
Drain any excess oil.
Fill pot at least half full of water and add rest of ingredients except for canned items.
Simmer for 30 minutes or until carrots are tender.
Add canned items near end of cooking time.
Serve with cornbread!

title: toffee
directions: Butter an 8 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 of the chopped pecans over the bottom of the pan.
Mix the butter or margarine with the brown sugar; bring to a boil.
Cook exactly 8 minutes, stirring constantly.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Layer broken tortillas.
Brown hamburger meat with onion, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Layer hamburger mixture, Ranch Style beans, Velveeta cheese, then more tortillas.
Blend chicken soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes; pour over casserole.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes.

title: scotch oat bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter an 8-inch pan. Combine butter and sugar.
Heat.
Stir until butter melts. Stir in oats, baking powder, vanilla and salt. Blend thoroughly.
Spread evenly over bottom of pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until edges are lightly browned. Remove from oven.
Let cool about 3 minutes. Sprinkle with chocolate chips. When melted, spread evenly over top. Cool and cut into bars.
Makes 28 (1 x 2-inch) bars.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in a 2 1/2-quart saucepan. Bring to a full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling 5 to 6 minutes over medium heat.
Stir constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate until melted.
Add Marshmallow Fluff, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature.
Makes approximately 3 pounds.

title: regina's irish soda bread
directions: Mix all together.
If using a mixer, fold in raisins.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Check at 50 minutes.
Use a well-greased loaf pan.
Great for St.
Patrick's Day.

title: stuffed tuna salad green peppers
directions: Prepare peppers.
Cook in salted water 5 minutes; drain. Sprinkle lightly with salt.
Have rice prepared.
Combine rice with tuna, celery, onions and pimento.
Blend in mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Toss together with other ingredients.
Spoon mixture into green pepper halves.
Sprinkle with crushed potato chips. Place in baking dish.
Put about 1/3 cup water in baking dish. Bake at 350° for about 35 to 45 minutes.

title: surprise cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients all together and add egg and coconut flavor.
Mix and make into balls the size of a walnut.
Grease cookie sheet and space on sheet enough for cookies to spread. Bake at 350° for 9 to 10 minutes.

title: italian meatballs nibbles
directions: Combine all ingredients, except Parmesan cheese; mix well. Form mixture into 1-inch balls and place in a lightly greased baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until looks done, turning occasionally.
Roll each meatball in Parmesan cheese. Serve warm.
Yields about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil spaghetti noodles in chicken broth (don't drain).
Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Mix chicken and celery mixture with the three cans of soup, the mushrooms, the cheese and the noodles.
Put into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with more Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 375° until cheese is melted and spaghetti bubbles.

title: fannie's grape-nut pudding
directions: Blend milk, eggs, sugar and vanilla in mixer; pour into dish. Add Grape-Nuts, nutmeg and butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 1/4 hours, until knife comes out clean with testing.

title: pork barbecue sauce
directions: Cook ketchup, pork broth, vinegar, mustard and apple jelly about 30 minutes.
Add diced or sliced pork.

title: hamburger cheese loaf
directions: Mix hamburger, onion, egg, ketchup, oats, salt and pepper. Make into hamburger patties.
Fold in cheese.
Slice and make into balls.
Bake until brown in 350° oven.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Stir altogether the peas, cream of mushroom soup, pimento, chopped onion and water chestnuts.
Grate cheese on top after putting in a casserole dish.
Crush Ritz crackers on top and pour 1 stick melted margarine over that.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: mississippi mud cake iii
directions: Mix the first 10 ingredients and pour in sheet pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven. Spread the Marshmallow Creme over cake while hot.
Mix the powdered sugar, milk, butter, cocoa and vanilla and spread over cake and marshmallow after cake is completely cool.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients except muffin mix.
Stir in muffin mix. Pour batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: chicken zucchini bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Arrange zucchini in 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with chicken.
Mix soup and milk, spread over chicken. Mix Bisquick, cheese and egg until crumbly.
Sprinkle over soup mixture.
Sprinkle with parsley, drizzle with margarine.
Bake until golden brown, about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: ginger chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg, molasses, flour, baking soda, cinnamon, ginger, cloves and salt.
Blend until smooth dough forms.
Stir in semi-sweet chocolate pieces.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Pour half of mixture in pan.
Sprinkle with cheese over that, then add the rest of batter. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix well.
Make in small balls.
Take fork and flatten.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Bake pie shell for 8 minutes at 350°.
In large skillet, saute pepper and onion in small amount of oil.
Add meat and cook until brown.
Pour off fat; add cheese and stir until melted.
Remove from heat and stir in eggs and tomato sauce.
Turn into pie shell and bake 25 minutes.
Remove from oven; arrange additional cheese slices and onion rings on top.
Bake 2 minutes longer.

title: tipsy carrots
directions: Combine carrots, rum and water in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 10 to 12 minutes or until carrots are crisp-tender.
Add remaining ingredients; toss gently until butter melts.

title: cranberry congealed salad
directions: Combine gelatin and boiling water. Stir until gelatin dissolves. Add cranberry sauce, stirring until blended. Chill until the consistency of unbeaten egg whites. Fold in oranges, apples and pecans. Cover and refrigerate until firm.

title: rice 'n beef hot dish
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Combine beef and other ingredients. Place in a large greased casserole dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir once midway.

title: carrot and zucchini bars
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, baking powder, ginger and baking soda.
In another large mixing bowl, stir together eggs, carrot, zucchini, raisins, walnuts, oil, honey and vanilla.
Add carrot mixture to flour mixture, stirring just until combined.
Spread batter in an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack. Frost with Citrus Cream Cheese Frosting.
Store, covered, in refrigerator.
Makes 36 bars.

title: yellow cake
directions: While cake is hot, punch holes in it with the end of a wooden spoon.
Pour the Hot Caramel Icing on the cake and let it run down in the holes.
You can leave it in the pan or put it on a cake serving dish.
Serve while hot.

title: salsa
directions: Chill for at least 1 hour.
Can add about 1/2 can (large) stewed tomatoes.

title: no peek stew
directions: Put in roaster, cover and bake at 275° for 3 1/2 hours.
Do not peek!
Great with hot biscuits.

title: mulligan stew
directions: Brown stew beef in Dutch oven.
Add salt, tomato soup and water.
Cover tightly and cook slowly for 1 1/2 hours.
Add carrots, potatoes and onion and cook another 30 minutes.
If too thick, add some water.
May also be cooked in a crock-pot by adding all ingredients and cook on slow for 8 hours.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Place breasts in 9 x 13-inch dish; top each piece with 1/2 cheese slice.
Thin soup with 1/2 cup water and pour over chicken. Mix stuffing and melted butter.
Sprinkle over chicken.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°, covered with foil.
Then push dressing into mixture and bake 1/2 hour, uncovered, to brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken cutlet roll-up
directions: Pound cutlets until thin or get thin sliced cutlets; combine crushed garlic and 1/2 stick margarine.
Spread each chicken breast with garlic mixture and place one slice turkey pastrami.
Tuck in sides and roll up.
Melt one stick margarine; roll chicken in melted margarine and roll in seasoned bread crumbs.
Place in shallow baking dish and bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: italian clam sauce(makes 6 servings)
directions: Heat oil.
Saute onion and garlic until onion is transparent. Add clams with juice.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add pepper flakes, parsley and Parmesan cheese.
Mix well and simmer 1 minute.
Serve with favorite pasta.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together except the last two.
Place in a pan.
Spread out.
On top, spread evenly with 1 cup of crushed corn flakes mixed with 1/4 cup of melted butter.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until the potatoes are done.

title: family salad
directions: Prepare the first 5 ingredients for salad.
Place bacon and garlic in skillet.
Cook until bacon is crisp; remove garlic. Crumble bacon over greens.
Add to fat in pan the remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling; pour over salad ingredients and toss well.
Add more salt and pepper if desired.
Add toasted cubes of bread (croutons) and mix lightly.
Serve at once.
Serves 6.

title: gumbo
directions: Brown chicken in oil in large pot.
Remove chicken and cook onions for 5 minutes.
Add flour, stirring, until flour is browned.
Add ham, chicken and tomatoes.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add chicken broth, rice, green pepper and seasonings. Cover and cook for 20 minutes.
Do not stir.
Add shrimp and simmer until hot.

title: hash brown potato
directions: Mix 1/2 stick of melted margarine with corn flakes; set aside. Mix rest of ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with corn flake mixture.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix together flour and sugar.
Bring to a rapid boil the butter, oil, water and cocoa.
Pour over flour mixture and blend well.
Stir in eggs, vanilla, cinnamon, soda and buttermilk. Pour batter into ungreased cookie sheet with narrow rim.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: caesar salad
directions: Dressing:
Combine minced garlic, lemon juice, anchovy paste, salt and pepper.
Coddle egg.
Add to mixture and whisk.
Slowly add oil and whisk until smooth.

title: italian vegetable toss
directions: Combine broccoli, cauliflower, carrots, mushrooms, artichoke hearts, olives and green onions.
Toss with salad dressing. Cover and chill several hours. Just before serving, add avocados and tomatoes.

title: pistachio surprise
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Remember, do not drain pineapple juice.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serves 5.

title: party salad
directions: Cut marshmallows into quarters.
Drain pineapple and cherries. Cut into small pieces.
Chop nuts.
Mix marshmallows, fruit, nuts and add lemon juice.

title: picnic fruit basket
directions: Cut approximately 1 1/2-inches off top of watermelon and save. Spoon out meat of melon.
Remove seed and cut into bite-size pieces.
Cut all other fruit in bite-size pieces.
Mix all fruit in bowl.
Add Fruit-Fresh as directed.
Apply Fruit-Fresh to inside of melon.
Fill melon bowl with fruit and pin down top with toothpicks.
Chill and serve.
Mix and match any fruit you would like.
This one's easy.

title: pink cloud salad
directions: Fold all together and chill.

title: new york cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In bowl, place crumbs, butter and 2 tablespoons of sugar (from the 1 cup).
Blend well.
Reserve 2 tablespoons of crumbs for garnish.
Press remaining mixture on bottom and sides of a greased 9-inch spring-form pan.
Chill in freezer.

title: peach flip
directions: Any kind of preserves can be used.

title: two star christmas cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add egg and beat until light and fluffy.
Stir in milk.
Sift together dry ingredients and blend into creamed mixture.
Divide dough in half and chill for 1 hour.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat with onion.
Add mustard, vinegar and chili sauce. Heat to boil.
Serve on buns.

title: honey orange carrots
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large saucepan.
Cover.
Cook 5 minutes.
Uncover and cook 10 to 15 minutes until carrots are crisp and tender.
Yields 10 servings.

title: chicken enchilada
directions: Saute onions and green chilies in oil.
Add everything else but cheese and tortillas.
Make layers of tortillas, chicken and cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Large casserole.

title: spinach pie
directions: Cook onion slowly until light brown in nonstick frypan.
Add chopped spinach; if frozen, cook a few minutes.
Add bread; squeeze and crumble.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add to mixture with cheese.
Cook in a well-oiled frypan slowly (as for scrambled eggs).
When dry, put mixture in a nonstick frypan and cook on top of stove slowly.
When a brown crust forms, turn over and cook other side. (Place a plate on pie and turn mixture over.
Slowly put back in pan to cook other side.)

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Divide dough in half.
Roll dough into rectangle to about 1/2-inch thickness.
Melt 1 stick margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour over dough, leaving some in pan.
Spread generous amount of brown sugar on top of dough.
Sprinkle on cinnamon.
Roll up into jelly roll.
Slice into 1-inch rolls and place into pan.
Let rise in warm place until doubles in bulk.
Bake at 400° until brown. Make glaze of 1 cup powdered sugar and milk.
Drizzle on hot rolls.

title: pepper steak
directions: Saute steak, pepper and onion in the margarine. Add mushroom soup, 1/2 can water, mushrooms and pimentos. Bring to boil, then cover and simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Serve over hot rice.

title: tuna ball
directions: Cream softened cream cheese with can of drained tuna.
Add finely chopped onion and hot sauce.
Mix together.
Chill 1 hour. Serve with crackers.

title: granny bill's heath bar coffee cake
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients until crumbly. Save 1 cup for topping. Add egg, milk and soda.
Mix well. Pour into greased 9 x 12-inch baking dish/pan. Add walnuts and Heath bar candy pieces to topping mix.
Sprinkle on top and bake at 350° approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour or until done.
Do not overbake!

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a medium bowl; mix until smooth.
Pour filling into unbaked shell.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes or until center is set.
Cool at least 1 hour before cutting.

title: curried chicken soup
directions: Cook chicken breasts until done.
Reserve broth.
Shred chicken breasts and put back in broth.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 2 to 3 hours.
(The longer it cooks, the better it is.)
Serves 4 or more.
Start temperature at high and then lower to low heat.
Cooking time is 3 hours (slow).

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Put yeast in warm water; add slightly beaten eggs, 1/2 cup Crisco, sugar, salt and cooled milk.
Sift 3 cups flour and stir. Sift more flour to make a stiff dough.
Turn out on floured board and knead about 2 minutes.
Knead in enough flour until it isn't sticky.
Let rise until double.
Roll out dough on floured board 1/2-inch thick.
Melt 1/2 stick butter and put on rolled out dough.
Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar on top of this.
Roll up and cut rolls out 3/4-inch thick and put in greased pans.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Frost with icing.

title: sauerkraut cake
directions: Cream together margarine, eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour.
Add alternately with water.
Beat well.
Drain and rinse kraut.
Fold into batter.
Grease and flour pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Test at 25 minutes.
Don't overbake.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Mix together.
Put in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: date nut balls
directions: Cook egg, butter, sugar, vanilla, nuts, and dates slowly until bubbly.
When cool, stir in Rice Krispies.
Mix well.
Roll into bite-size balls and then roll into coconut.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Add oil to boiling water.
Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain and return to pan.
Add butter, cheese and milk (enough so it's not dry).
Simmer about 5 minutes.

title: cool and easy pie
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin in bowl 2 minutes or until dissolved.
Mix water and ice to make 1 1/4 cups.
Stir into gelatin until slightly thickened.
Remove any remaining ice.
Stir in whipped topping until smooth.
Refrigerate 10 minutes or until mixture will mound.
Spoon into crust.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until firm.
Garnish with additional whipped topping.
Makes 8 servings.

title: carrot pennies
directions: Place carrots, onion and green pepper in bowl with lid.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over vegetables.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator.

title: presbyterian muffins
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Add alternately with buttermilk.
Fold in nuts.
Bake at 350° in well greased muffin pans.
Bake for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Butter the bottom of an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Place peaches in the bottom of the dish.
Trim brown edges from bread; slice bread in 4 even strips.
Place strips on top of peaches.
Combine margarine, sugar, egg and flour; pour over top of bread and peaches.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes until brown at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: a good mexican dip
directions: Melt cheese and add all ingredients. Mix well and keep warm until ready to serve.

title: hot water bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pat into thin cakes and fry in hot grease until brown on both sides.

title: chicken dijon
directions: Place chicken between 2 sheets of wax paper.
With meat mallet, pound to 1/8-inch thick.
In medium bowl, combine flour and dash each of salt and pepper.
Add chicken; toss to coat.
In a 10-inch skillet, heat butter and oil over medium heat.
Add chicken.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes on each side until cooked and browned.
Preheat broiler.
Place chicken on rack of broiler pan. Top with ham, then cheese.
Broil 2 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a heavy saucepan; gradually add milks, stirring until blended.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and comes to a boil.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Gradually stir about 1/4 of hot mixture into yolks; add to remaining hot mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook over medium heat, continuously stirring 1 minute. Remove from heat; stir in butter and next 2 ingredients.
Spoon mixture into pastry shell.

title: peanut butter and jelly fudge
directions: In a large bowl, combine confectioners sugar, cracker crumbs, peanut butter and butter.
Stir until well blended.
Line a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with a double layer of aluminum foil, extending foil over ends of pan.
Grease foil.
Press mixture into pan.

title: pickled beets
directions: Add all ingredients except beets.
Bring to a hard boil.
Add beets.
Boil hard 5 minutes.
Fill hot jars and seal.

title: sweet and sour balls
directions: Mix sausage, bread crumbs and eggs.
Form into walnut size balls.
Saute in frying pan. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over sausage balls.
Put in chafing dish to reheat for 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Can be frozen.

title: vegetable jello mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add juice of pineapple and let jell until partially set.
Whip in Miracle Whip.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour in mold and refrigerate until set.

title: pot roast
directions: Put the roast in a conventional oven at 350° for 2 hours. Potatoes take 1 hour, carrots and onions need 1/2 hour.
(Use a roaster to accommodate everything.)
When this pot roast is done cooking, remove from roaster onto large serving plate, then enjoy. Should serve 3 to 5 people.

title: chili bake
directions: Brown beef. Add onions, salt and pepper. Combine rice, chili powder, tomato sauce, cream of chicken soup and half of the cheese and water.
Mix well. Add browned beef.
Put in baking dish. Top with remaining cheese. Sprinkle top with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Prepare
peppers
by cutting off tops and removing core and seeds.
Cook
in
lightly
salted
water
for
5 minutes. Sprinkle the insides with salt.
Mix the beef with the pepper, onion, soup, rice, crumbs, oregano and salt.
Blend thoroughly and
spoon lightly into the peppers.
To the remaining 1/2 cup of soup, add 1/2 cup of water and Worcestershire sauce.
Blend this
together and
pour over the peppers.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Put the halved slices of cheese on the peppers and return to the oven until the cheese melts.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Place in fridge for 2 or 3 hours or overnight and keeps for several days.

title: frozen dumplings
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil.
Remove from heat and add flour.
Stir into ball.
Roll into thickness of 1/4 inch when cool enough to handle.
Cut in pieces.
Freeze on cookie sheet.
After frozen place in plastic bag.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix yogurt and Cool Whip with spoon until fluffy.
Add dry jello.
Continue to mix to taste.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: russian tea balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, roll into small balls and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400 degrees for 10 minutes; immediately roll in powdered sugar.
Let cool.
Roll in powdered sugar one more time.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook hamburg, onion and pepper.
Drain fat.
Add tomatoes, water, salt, pepper, sugar, rice and bay leaf until rice is cooked.

title: quick and easy baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir well.
Microwave on High for approximately 15 minutes in a large cooking dish, rotating every 5 minutes.

title: blackberry shortbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Beat in the egg yolk. Stir in flour and pecans. Press 3/4 dough in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Spread preserves on the top. Crumble the remaining dough on top (the dough shouldn't completely cover the preserves). Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes about 24 (2 x 2 inch) squares.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Layer on large round plate:
bean dip; avocados mashed with lemon juice; sour cream mixed with taco seasoning; tomatoes; green onions; black olives and shredded cheese.
Chill for 2 hours. Serve with nacho Doritos.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt butter in medium saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Add cocoa, sugar, eggs, flour, vanilla and nuts.
Beat well.
Pour into well-greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: e-z red beans and rice
directions: You will also need a 4-quart pot.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Cut chicken into 1/4-inch pieces.
Use white meat (no skins). Fry in a pan until done.
Add some barbecue sauce over the chicken until heated.
Serve just like that!

title: new potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes; do not peel.
Cook in boiling salted water for 10 minutes; drain.
Melt butter in a saucepan, large enough to hold potatoes.
Add the herbs, garlic and shallots.
Add the partially-cooked potatoes and shake the pan to coat them with the herb mixture.
Sprinkle lightly with salt, cover and cook over medium heat, shaking pan occasionally so potatoes won't stick, about 20 minutes more.
Serve hot with ground pepper.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill several hours before serving.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef; add taco seasoning and set aside to cool. Mix all remaining ingredients.
Add meat and toss lightly.
Pour on Catalina dressing.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Grease baking dish.
Melt butter and toss crumbs with it. Layer ingredients in baking dish as follows:
1/3 butter crumbs, 1/2 oysters, dash salt, pepper, parsley, 1/3 butter crumbs, 1/2 oysters, 1/3 butter crumbs, dash salt, pepper and parsley.
Pour milk over top; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Brown onions and celery in butter.
Add soup, water, Cheez Whiz and salt.
Stir until blended and Cheez Whiz is melted.
Put rice and broccoli in buttered casserole dish.
Pour heated mixture over rice and broccoli, then stir until mixed.
Bake in 350° oven, uncovered, for 20 minutes.

title: log cabin molasses sugar cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add molasses and egg; beat well.
Add the next five ingredients.
Mix all together.
Chill. Form in 1-inch balls, roll in granulated sugar and place on greased cookie sheets.
Bake in a 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Add rice to boiling water and cover; simmer until all water is gone (approximately 30 minutes).
During waiting period, beat eggs with sugar and add condensed milk and vanilla; beat well. Add mixture to rice.
Turn burner up.
When rice starts to boil, stir and turn down.
Simmer, uncovered, for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: old-fashioned macaroni and cheese
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place cooked macaroni, cheese, pepper and tomatoes in alternating layers in a buttered, oblong or Corning Ware dish, ending with a layer of cheese on top.
Pour 1 cup milk and 1 cup juice from the tomatoes over the top.
Sprinkle with paprika over entire top.
Serve right from baking dish.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mexican taco dip pie
directions: Layer in large pie plate, combining sour cream and dried seasoning.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chicken olivia
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish.
Mix together 1 stick melted oleo and 2 cups corn flakes.
Put on top of chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate layer dessert
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: deli salad
directions: Combine pasta shells, ham, cheese and celery in salad bowl.
In blender, combine oil, yogurt, green onions, lemon juice, corn syrup, mustard, tarragon, salt and pepper.
Pour over salad. Marinate one hour.

title: corned beef ball
directions: Combine all ingredients well.
Grease dish with 1 pound margarine.
Sprinkle parsley flakes generously around inside. Put mix into bowl.
Cover and refrigerate several hours.
Turn out onto platter ring with firm crackers to serve.

title: fruit cocktail cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Mix all of the ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes on greased cookie sheets.

title: pat's neighborly pie
directions: Mix raspberries and sugar together. Pour over berries. Stir gently. Let stand 10 minutes. Put berry mixture in crust. Top with 1 1/2 teaspoons butter pats. Vent top crust. Bake at 425° for 35 to 45 minutes. Great topped with vanilla ice cream.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Rinse broccoli.
Cut or break up into small trees.
Mix all remaining ingredients (except bacon) listed.
Sprinkle with bacon for topping.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add fruit cocktail with juice.
Sift together flour, sugar and baking soda.
Add to fruit mixture. Blend and pour into 10 x 10-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: devil's food cake(makes 2 layers)
directions: Cook for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: steak marinade
directions: Method 1:
Slice London Broil steak thinly.
Marinate 1 to 2 hours.
Panfry in small amount of butter.
Add enough marinade to cover and heat until warm.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Saute onions, celery and mushrooms in butter until onions are transparent.
Mix together with the soup and mayonnaise and add the rest of the ingredients.
Place in a buttered casserole dish. Cover with buttered crackers and potato chips and sprinkle cheese and paprika over top.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: coffee cordial
directions: Combine brown sugar, granulated sugar and water in a medium size saucepan.
Bring to boiling, stirring constantly.
Lower heat.
Simmer 5 minutes.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion in greased 10-inch pie plate. Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 1 minute.
Pour into plate.
Bake for approximately 30 minutes at 400°.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: bagels
directions: Combine yeast and 1 3/4 cups of flour.
Combine water, sugar and salt and add to yeast mixture.
Beat with electric mixer. Stir in remaining flour by hand.
Turn on floured board and knead 5 to 8 minutes.
Cut into 12 portions and shape into balls; put hole in the middle.
Cover and let rise 20 minutes.
Boil 1 gallon of water with 1 tablespoon of sugar.
Simmer 7 minutes; drain. Place on baking sheet and bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix dry pudding with crushed pineapple (and juice) for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add Cool Whip, nuts and marshmallows.
Mix and pour in serving bowl.
Delicious.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie shell with pastry and chill. Combine ingredients and beat until smooth.
Pour into shell and bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Reduce to 350° and bake 35 minutes.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: In medium bowl, combine margarine, brown, sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Mix well by hand.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour batter into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan and spread evenly. Sprinkle top with chocolate chips.
Bake in 350° oven for about 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut into bars after letting cool slightly.

title: smoked oysters
directions: Pull apart biscuits.
Place 1 smoked oyster on biscuit.
Roll. Bake at 375° until brown.

title: hot turkey-broccoli salad
directions: Combine turkey, onion, chicken broth, mayonnaise, sour cream and mustard in large bowl.
Mix thoroughly.
Mix in cheese and half the broccoli.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold gently into turkey mixture.
Spoon mixture into 4 to 6 ramekins or small baking dishes.
Arrange remaining broccoli around edges.
Bake in preheated 375° oven 25 to 30 minutes or until golden.
Sprinkle with toasted almonds.

title: new england baked beans and pork(175 year old recipe)
directions: Soak 1 quart beans overnight in cold water to cover.
Place in bean pot in morning, adding molasses, mustard mixed with molasses and a little hot water.
Pour over beans.
Put salt pork in center of beans, well down into pot.
Cover with boiling water.
Bake slow all day, adding boiling water when necessary.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium speed with electric mixer or blender.
Add eggs; mix well.
Pour into crust. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool, then refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.
Then add favorite topping (cherry, pineapple, blueberry).

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil and eggs; stir well.
Add pineapple and mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased large cookie sheet with sides.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
While still warm, top with icing.

title: flaky meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place on perforated rack in a baking pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: indiana picnic cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and take out 1/2 cup to use later to sprinkle over top of Picnic Cake.
To remaining mixture, add remaining ingredients.

Add all the latter group of ingredients at once and mix until smooth (can be slightly lumpy). Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan that has been oiled and floured. Sprinkle the 1/2 cup of sugar topping that has been retained over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
May be done at 30 minutes.

title: pastel (jewish eggroll from cochin, india)
directions: Chop the chicken breast, and chop all the vegetables.
Heat 1/2 cup oil in a big frying pan and add the chicken breast; mix until the meat becomes white and add all chopped vegetables.
Cook for 20 minutes while mixing occasionally.
Add the spices, nuts and mushrooms.
Cook for another 30 minutes while mixing occasionally. Chop eggs and add to filling.
Fry the filling in the shell as per directions on the bag.
Fry in deep frying pan until the shell is gold.

title: microwave peanut butter fudge
directions: In a microwave-safe bowl, melt peanut butter and butter on High 2 to 4 minutes.
Add cocoa and vanilla and mix well.
Add the powdered sugar.
Mix with your hands until well blended.
Be careful; it may still be hot! Press into an 8 x 8-inch or 8 x 10-inch pan and refrigerate 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Store in the refrigerator.

title: cranberry cream mold(makes 8 to 10 servings)
directions: Heat orange juice to boiling.
Empty package of orange flavor into a large bowl.
Add boiling orange juice to gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Break up jelly with a fork and stir it into the dissolved gelatin.
Add 1/4 cup cold water, salt and lemon juice.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Whip heavy cream and fold lightly into the thickened gelatin mixture.
Pour into 1-quart mold.
Chill until firm.
Turn out and decorate with holly leaves.
For the holly berries, select a few cranberries from a can of whole cranberry sauce or use fresh cranberries.

title: apple crunch
directions: Cream 1 cup of margarine, 1 1/2 cup white sugar (13 seconds in microwave) and add eggs.
Mix well.
Add 2 cups flour.
Mix well. Spread in 12 x 18-inch pan.
Place apples in pan.

title: apricot casserole
directions: In a baking dish, put layers of apricots, sugar and cracker crumbs and then pat butter on top.
Bake at 300° for about 1 hour. If dry, add apricot juice.

title: raisin crisp cookies
directions: Combine oats and brown sugar.
Stir in oil, egg and flavoring. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to oat mixture, blending well.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hershey brownies
directions: Combine 1/2 cup margarine, eggs, 1 cup sugar, flour, syrup and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: english pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together with mayonnaise.

title: homemade potato soup
directions: Peel potatoes; cut into small pieces and cover with water.
Add salt, garlic and pepper.
Also onions and celery.
Cook until done, about 30 to 45 minutes.
Drain most of the water; add milk and thicken with a flour and water mixture to the thickness desired.

title: easy ground beef lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef in saucepan, stirring until crumbly; drain. Add spaghetti sauce, water and seasonings; mix well.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Mix cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese, eggs and half the Parmesan cheese in bowl.
Layer 1 cup sauce, 3 uncooked noodles, 1 1/2 cups sauce and half the cheese mixture in 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Repeat layers.
Top with remaining sauce and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
Cover with plastic wrap, turning back edge to vent.
Microwave on High for 25 minutes, turning once.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: mexican party dip
directions: Chop tomatoes.
Combine tomatoes, sour cream, green chiles and party dip mix.
Stir to blend.
Chill for at least 1 hour.
Enjoy with chips and vegetables.
Makes about 3 1/2 cups.

title: sage cornbread muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line muffin tin with paper muffin cups (or butter and lightly flour the pan).
Combine cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in a mixing bowl.
Make a well in the center of the dry ingredients and add the eggs, buttermilk and melted butter.
Stir all ingredients together until just combined. Fold creamed corn and sage into the batter.
Fill muffin cups halfway with batter.
Bake for 20 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Yield:
16 muffins, 123 calories each and 4 grams fat.

title: microwave caramel popcorn
directions: Microwave brown sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt. Microwave on High for 2 1/2 minutes.
Stir and microwave 2 1/2 minutes more.
Then add baking soda.
Stir, will be thick.
Mix with popcorn.
Put in brown grocery bag.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes more.

title: fudge
directions: Butter an 8 x 3-inch dish or small oblong bread pan about the same size.
Put cocoa and sugar in boiler and stir together well. Add milk and stir.
Bring mixture to boil.
Boil for 20 to 25 minutes, stirring often so mixture will not stick to pan.
Add vanilla and butter; stir rapidly for 3 to 4 minutes.
Pour in buttered dish.
Cut when cool.

title: super subs
directions: First take the French bread and cut the top off shaped as a U. Then take the Mozzarella slices and put as many as you want, but leave some for the top.
Next take the pizza sauce and put on top of the cheese.
Smooth it with a knife.
Next take the pepperoni and put as many as you want on top of sauce.
Next take ham and put as many as you want on top of the pepperoni.
Next put bacon on top of ham.
Last put on the rest of the Mozzarella slices.

title: evelyn's cheese bread
directions: Heat sour cream over very low heat in a nonstick saucepan. Stir in sugar, salt and butter.
Sit aside and cool until lukewarm.
In large bowl, sprinkle yeast over warm water, stirring until completely dissolved.
Add sour cream mixture, eggs and flour.
Mix well until a mound forms in the bottom of the bowl. Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.
The next day, go on to steps 2 and 3.

title: amaretto bundt cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Lightly brown almonds in oleo. Sprinkle over bottom of prepared pan.
Set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients in bowl and beat for 2 minutes.
Pour batter over nuts.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: pears punjab(must be prepared ahead of time.)
directions: Beat eggs until light in color. Add sugar. Continue to beat until mixture is very stiff. Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly. Pour into can and freeze. Freezer should be about 3/4 full as ice cream will expand.

title: cotton candy cake
directions: Add a few drops of red food coloring to container of Cool Whip for pink coloring.
Mix red pop with cake mix (instead of water) and bake in ungreased angel food cake pan as directed on box.
When cake is cooled, frost with Cool Whip.

title: hot bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle crumbs on top just before baking.
Bake in a 450° oven for 10 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: breaded tomatoes
directions: In a large saucepan, saute onion in margarine until tender; stir in flour until blended.
Add the tomatoes, sugar, oil, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Stir in toast cubes.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: yummy yams
directions: Mix all well and pour in buttered casserole or pyrex dish.

title: freezing collards
directions: You will need Ziploc bags (gallon size).

title: nachos
directions: Brown ground round and prepare according to taco seasoning package. Slowly melt Velveeta with Ro-Tel tomatoes in microwave or crock-pot. Arrange chips and lettuce on plates. Top with seasoning meat and melted cheese mixture. Add tomatoes, green chilies, sour cream and black olives as desired.

title: apple-date slices(watschke's fruit appetizer)
directions: Core, but don't peel, the apples, then brush both sides of each slice with lemon juice.
Combine and blend the remaining ingredients.
Spread the cream cheese mixture on each apple slice.

title: marinated slaw #1
directions: Heat first 3 ingredients until sugar melts.
Set aside to cool.
Pour liquid over slaw.
Mix well.
Refrigerate 12 hours before using.

title: easy chicken and rice
directions: Sprinkle rice over bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Pour onion soup over rice.
Add water, salt and pepper.
Wash chicken and place chicken on rice.
Spread cream of celery soup over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
