Add water if necessary.

title: gingerbread cookie dough
directions: On waxed paper, combine flour, cinnamon, ginger, cloves and salt.
In large bowl, with electric mixer, beat shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in molasses and egg.
Stir in flour mixture to make a stiff dough.
Divide dough into thirds; wrap with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour or up to 3 days before using.

title: davy's shrimp
directions: Arrange shrimp in bottom of casserole dish and sprinkle lime juice on top.
In heavy pan, melt butter, cream cheese and Bleu cheese.
Pour over shrimp.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Serve over pasta or brown rice.

title: broccoli rice whiz
directions: Cook rice until tender, saute onion and celery in butter, season and peppers.
Spoon into greased baking dish and add the rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Prepare Creamettes according to package directions.
Drain. Saute celery, green pepper and onions in butter until tender.
Add soup, milk and cheese.
Stir until cheese melts.
Combine macaroni-cheese mixture, tuna, pimento, salt and nutmeg.
Pour into 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or 35 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: decorator icing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add flavoring and beat or stir until fluffy.

title: hamburger cupcakes
directions: Brown hamburger in frying pan, then add taco mix according to package directions.
Let simmer.
Grease 2 cupcake pans; line the pockets of the cupcake pans with biscuit dough.
Spoon in hamburger; fill to top.
Top with cheese.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Brown ground beef; drain. Stir in tomato sauce. Boil rice. Drain water. Add to ground beef.
Mix in 2 eggs.
Stuff peppers with mix. Sprinkle cheese over top.
Cook at 350° for about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: sarma (cabbage rolls) with sauerkraut
directions: In a large pan of boiling water, place cabbage with core removed; shut off heat.
Remove cabbage leaves in 10 minutes and drain.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Pour into unbaked 8-inch pie shell. Top with pats of butter and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes until set.
Increase quantities for larger pie.

title: spice muffins
directions: Cook either in small muffin tins or drop from spoon on cookie pan.
Cover with powdered sugar.

title: beef stew
directions: Cut carrots, potatoes, onion and celery into chunks.
Crush garlic.
Finely chop parsley and basil.
Clean and slice mushrooms.

title: chocolate mint ice cream
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat eggs on high speed of electric mixer until light (about 4 minutes).
Add whipping cream, milk, sugar, light corn syrup, vanilla and salt.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add creme de menthe and food coloring.
Stir until blended.
Pour in 1 gallon ice cream freezer and freeze.
Remove dasher.
Stir in chocolate.
Pack with additional salt and ice (1 part to 4 parts).
Let "ripen" 3 hours.
Makes 5 cups.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll into 2-inch balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until golden brown.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Peel and cook potatoes in water until soft.
Mash and let cool.
Form mashed sweet potatoes around marshmallows.
Dip in honey and roll in crushed nuts.
Place on cookie sheet and bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: strawberry delight fat-free spread
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients.
Whisk until smooth.
Keep refrigerated.
Use as a spread on toast, bagels, muffins or crackers.
Fat free; only 5 calories per serving.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix dry Jell-O with Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
Mix well, then add oranges.
You may also add coconut and nuts to salad.

title: best deer burgers
directions: Mix deer burger, beef burger, soup mixes and water by hand until thoroughly combined.
Shape into very thin patties.
Top half of patties with 1/2 slice of bacon.
Cover this with remainder of patties and seal edges.
Grill over hot coals or gas grill until done.
Serve on warm buns with mustard and sliced onion.
While burgers are cooking, sprinkle meat with Worcestershire sauce.

title: party chicken bites
directions: Cut bacon in half vertically.
Cut chicken livers into bite size pieces.
Place liver at end of bacon strip and roll.
Secure end underneath.
Place on broiler pan.
Cover with foil.
Cook at 400° until livers are almost done.
Remove foil and place under broiler until bacon is crisp.
Turn and broil until other side of bacon is crisp.
Remove to paper towels.

title: stuffed swiss chard
directions: Quickly blanch Swiss chard in boiling water.
Mix beef, rice, onion, parsley, salt and pepper.
Lay out leaves. Cut off stems. Stuff one leaf at a time and roll.
Put stems on bottom of pan, then put rolls on top. Add tomato sauce and water. Cook for 1 hour on slow heat. Serve with boiled rice or potatoes. Delicious topped with plain yogurt.

title: ellen's chocolate pudding cake
directions: Mix together (will be stiff).
Spray 8 x 8-inch dish with Pam. Spread batter in dish.

title: layered taco supreme
directions: Spread chili in a ceramic pie dish.
Layer salsa, cream cheese, scallions, olives and Cheddar cheese on top.
Microwave on High one minute or until cheese melts.
Serve with taco or tortilla chips.
Easy!

title: fried rice
directions: In a large skillet, heat 1 tablespoon oil over medium heat. Add eggs and cook, without stirring, until set.
Remove eggs and cut into short, narrow strips.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and let stand, then mix.
Mix the rest of the ingredients until crumbly.
Set aside 1 cup crumbs. Mix remaining crumbs with liquid mixture.
Pour in cake pan. Sprinkle the cup of crumbs over cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, cheese and sugar.
Add flour and flavoring. Add 1 egg at a time.
Bake in large tube pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: crunchy fudge sandwich
directions: Melt butterscotch chips and peanut butter in heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring, until blended.
Stir in Rice Krispies. Press 1/2 of mixture into buttered 8-inch square pan and chill. Over hot water, melt chocolate chips, sugar, butter and water. Spread over chilled mixture.
Top with reserved cereal mixture. Chill.
Cut into squares after 10 minutes in refrigerator.
Double recipe will fit 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Prepare pudding mix with milk.
Stir until thick.
Fold Cool Whip with pudding.
Pour 1/2 mixture over crackers.
Put another layer of crackers.
Cover with remaining mixture.
Put another layer of crackers and cover with the chocolate icing.

title: creamy dressing for tossed salad
directions: Whisk all together until smooth and cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Toss with greens and vegetables.

title: pretzels
directions: Mix together popcorn oil, Ranch dressing, dill weed and garlic powder, making sure salad dressing is completely dissolved.
Pour evenly over the pretzels.
Bake for 1 hour at 200°.
With large spoon, mix or turn pretzels every 10 minutes to make sure all pretzels are coated with oil mixture.

title: banana walnut cake
directions: In a
mixing bowl mix together mashed banana and butter until creamy.
Add
eggs and water; beat well.
Stir in flour, baking powder, baking soda and
cinnamon.	Beat
until smooth. Add chopped nuts.
Spoon batter into oiled
and
floured
x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cake tests done. Cool and cut into squares.

title: "chicken julie"
directions: Brown chicken in Crisco. Saute garlic and onions. Add flour and brown lightly. Add bouillon, water, thyme and bay leaves. Combine all and cook slowly 1 hour or more. Near end of cooking, add olives and sherry.

title: 7 layer jello salad
directions: Dissolve 1 box Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Place 1/2 cup in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Take other half of Jell-O and mix with 1/2 cup of sour cream.
Mix with fork or wire whisk.
Let first layer jell.
Put on sour cream layer and jell.
Allow 30 minutes between layers.
Repeat this for remainder of 6 boxes of Jell-O.

title: crab-stuffed mushrooms
directions: Brush mushroom caps with butter; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Fill caps.
Place on broiler pan.
Broil about 5 minutes.

title: sunlight sipper
directions: Combine all ingredients in glass.
Makes 1 serving.

title: hamburger soup
directions: In large pot cook ground beef until browned.
Drain off fat. Stir in remaining ingredients and 5 cups water.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Remove bay leaf.
Serves 8.

title: corn bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the dry ingredients.
Mix well. Combine in another bowl the oil, egg and milk.
Mix well and stir into dry ingredients until blended.
Pour into a well buttered 8-inch square pan and bake for 25 minutes.
(One half cup sharp Cheddar cheese may be added.)

title: vegetable soup(in honor of rev. wiggins)
directions: Cover meat with water; cook until tender (1 to 1 1/2 hours). Salt meat.
Cook other vegetables until tender (15 to 20 minutes). Mix meat and vegetables (keep all juice).
Add bouillon cubes and V-8 juice.
Let simmer for about 20 minutes.

title: veal parmigiana
directions: Saute onion and garlic in 2 tablespoons oil until tender; stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, salt, basil and oregano.
Simmer, uncovered, stirring often for 45 minutes, until thickened.
Dip veal in egg, then in crumbs and fry in oil until golden.
Drain on paper towels.
Layer 1/2 of tomato sauce, then veal and then rest of sauce and Mozzarella cheese in 12-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: dumplings
directions: Cut shortening into flour, parsley, baking powder and salt in medium bowl.
Stir in milk.
Drop dough by 10 spoonfuls onto hot meat or vegetables in boiling stew.
Cook, uncovered, 10 minutes. Cover and cook 10 minutes longer.

title: chocolate chip crunchy balls
directions: Melt margarine in a saucepan over low heat or in microwave oven for 30 seconds.
Add marshmallows; heat until melted and smooth, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cereal until well coated.
With buttered fingers and palms of hands, roll sticky cereal and several chocolate chips into 1 1/2-inch balls. Let set on wax paper.
Store in airtight container.
Makes approximately 48 balls.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook macaroni as package label directs; drain.
In 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish, alternate macaroni (in 2 layers) with 1 1/2 cups cheese (2 layers); set aside.

title: dick's complete california eggs
directions: Brown mushrooms in butter in large baking dish.
Add chives to mushrooms.
Mix eggs and cream and add to cooled mushrooms.
Slice avocado and shallots.
Distribute evenly over egg mixture. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over mixture to cover.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Arrange asparagus, cheese, almonds and eggs in layers in casserole dish.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Dip chicken in melted butter and roll in mixture of crushed flakes and garlic salt.
Place coated chicken on a foil-lined baking sheet and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: peach jam
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients together for 15 minutes.
Add the Jell-O; heat until dissolved.
Put into cans and seal.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Set oven at 450°.
Line a 9-inch pie pan with plain pastry. Mix all ingredients well.
Spoon into the pie shell and bake until brown (30 minutes).

title: jello ribbon salad
directions: Use Tupperware 9 x 13-inch dish; cake pan isn't large enough. Mix all but jello and sour cream.
Cook on medium until sugar is dissolved.
Cool.
Add sour cream.
Mix 1 package jello with 3/4 cup hot and 3/4 cup cold water.
Put in pan.
Set until tacky (not firm) approximately 20 minutes.

title: cheesy onion burger buns
directions: In
a
large
mixing bowl, combine 2 cups flour, sugar, salt, yeast
and
butter.
Gradually
add
hot
water.
With electric mixer,
beat
minutes at medium speed.
Add 1 cup flour
and mix on high speed 2 minutes.
Stir in cheese, onion and
enough of the remaining flour to form a soft dough.
Turn out
onto
a floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic, about
6 to 8 minutes.
Place dough in a greased bowl, turning once to
grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled,
about
1 hour.
Punch dough down and turn out onto a lightly
floured surface.
Divide dough into 20 equal pieces; shape
into
smooth balls and place on greased baking sheets. Cover
and
let
rise in a warm place until doubled, about 45 minutes.
Bake
at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from the pans
and
cool on wire racks.
Yield:
20 delicious hamburger buns.
This recipe also makes good breadsticks.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Melt butter.
Add wine and garlic in frying pan.
Add shrimp. Cook until shrimp turn pink, approximately 3 minutes.
Serve with remaining sauce.

title: candied orange peel
directions: Score peel of 2 large oranges into quarters; remove peel. Heat peel and 6 cups water to boiling.
Simmer 30 minutes; drain and repeat cooking peel into another 6 cups water.
Gently scrape off remaining white membrane from peel.
Cut peel lengthwise into 1/4-inch strips.

title: guacamole me gusto
directions: Shortly before serving, into a medium bowl, peel and dice the avocados into 1/2 inch cubes.
Add lemon juice, onion, garlic, chili powder, Tabasco, cilantro, salt and olive oil.
Toss together gently.
Peel, seed and chop tomatoes.
Fold into avocado mixture.
Chill briefly to blend flavors.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: crisp zucchini sticks
directions: Wash and trim
zucchini.
Cut
in long strips, 1/2-inch thick, 2 1/2-inches
long.
Coat strips with mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Dip strips in mixture of slightly beaten egg and lemon juice; coat with bread crumbs.
Fry in melted butter or margarine. Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot.
Serves 4.

title: crabbies
directions: Split each English muffin into 2 round pieces.
Mix all other ingredients together and spread on English muffin pieces.
Put in freezer.
Just before serving, cut muffin round into 8 pieces. Place under broiler and bake until bubbly.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Cook molasses, water, sugar and salt until it forms a hard ball.
Add vanilla and shortening and stir only to mix.
Pour over popped corn and make into balls.

title: crunchy turkey casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except noodles.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap; fold back a small corner of wrap to allow steam to escape.
Microwave at High 12 to 15 minutes, or until thoroughly heated, stirring after 6 minutes.
Sprinkle with Chinese noodles and serve immediately.
Yields 6 servings.

title: spam casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cook macaroni.
Cook and stir onion and green pepper in margarine until onion is tender.
Stir in macaroni and remaining ingredients.
Bake in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish; cover.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Bake in an 8 x 12 x 2-inch Pyrex dish, well buttered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: angel lush
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple in medium bowl.
Gently stir in Cool Whip.
Cut cake horizontally in 3 layers.
Place bottom cake layer, cut side up, on serving plate.
Spread 1 1/3 cups of pudding mixture onto cake layer.
Cover with middle cake layer.
Spread 1 cup of the pudding mixture onto middle cake layer.
Top with remaining cake layer.
Spread with remaining pudding mixture. Refrigerate at least 1 hour or until ready to serve.
You can also put strawberries on top for extra color.

title: easy fudge(microwave)
directions: Microwave chocolate and milk 2 to 3 minutes on High.
Stir in vanilla and walnuts.
Spread in pan and refrigerate 2 hours.
Cut into squares.

title: oat wheat bread
directions: Place the margarine, salt, oatmeal, powdered milk and most of the molasses in a large bowl.
Add 4 cups of boiling water.
Stir until the margarine has melted.
Add yeast to remaining 1/2 cup of cooled water (105° to 155°) to which a small amount of the molasses has been added.
Add yeast mixture to oatmeal mixture.
Stir in whole wheat and white flours.
Add flour until dough is no longer sticky.
Cover with towel.
Let rise until doubled.
Knead and shape into pans.
Cover and let double again.
Bake at 375° for about 40 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: green rice
directions: Cook broccoli in salt water, drain and chop over low heat. Mix butter, soup and Cheez Whiz; add rice and broccoli.
Pour in casserole dish.
Cook until bubbly.
Cook at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: crabmeat au gratin #1
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Place in a baking dish. Sprinkle with grated cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: lemon pepper chicken
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients together.
Place chicken in plastic bag or shallow baking dish.
Pour marinade over chicken and marinate for up to 4 hours.

title: romaine garlic dressing
directions: Beat 2 eggs until foamy and lemon colored.
Slowly add the salad oil.
Beat until thick.
Add other ingredients, except for the cheese, and mix well.
Lightly stir in the cheese.
Serve over romaine lettuce.

title: meat loaf italiano
directions: Combine beef, pork, soup mix, bread crumbs, onion, egg and 1/2 of pizza sauce; mix well.
Press in 9-inch skillet with heat resistant handle or 9-inch pie plate.
Bake in 375° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.
Drain off fat.
Spread remaining pizza sauce over meat.
Arrange cheese on top.
Bake 5 minutes longer. Cut into wedges; serve with vegetables.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken creole("heart smart")
directions: Cut chicken into 2 inch cubes. Heat oil in large skillet; saute onion. Add mushrooms and cook until liquid evaporates. Add garlic, celery and spices; cook 1 minute.
Add peppers; cook 2 minutes. Stir in tomatoes; cook 5 minutes. Add wine, lemon juice and hot pepper; set aside.

In another skillet, heat half the margarine; add chicken and sprinkle with black pepper. Cook on high; stir constantly until browned. Repeat with rest of chicken. Combine with Creole Sauce and simmer 2 minutes.

title: antipasto
directions: Bring ingredients, except green peppers, to a rapid boil.
Add green peppers and boil until done to your taste, about 10 minutes. Stir constantly while boiling. Fill hot jars and seal.
Pressure cook 10 minutes at 10 pound pressure.
Serve with crackers.

title: a man's cake
directions: Bake in tube pan.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Remove Starter mixture from refrigerator and feed as directed.
Let mixture stand at room temperature 8 to 10 hours or all day.
On this evening, mix 1 cup Starter mix (return remaining Starter to refrigerator), the sugar, oil, salt, water and flour. Mix with a wooden spoon (finish with hands).
Cover top of dough with vegetable oil; cover bowl with towel and let rise overnight.

title: fast peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend together.
Drop by spoons onto cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with a little sugar and bake in 350° oven for
8 minutes.
Take from oven.
Let set 1 minute before removing from cookie sheet.

title: oodle of noodle dinner
directions: Cook noodles as directed (let water cook down some).
Brown ground beef in skillet, then mix with noodles.
Drain fat, then serve.

title: bettijane's wedding punch
directions: Mix together and enjoy!
Serves 100 people.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until almost done. Take away from heat, add pieces of butter on top of the broccoli. Cover broccoli completely with cheese. Moisten crackers up with butter and put on top of cheese. Bake at 400 degrees for about 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: kathy glenn's blueberry cheese cake
directions: Mix crust ingredients well.
Press into well-greased 8 to 10-inch spring-form pan. Refrigerate 15 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: easy fudge
directions: Heat chocolate and milk in 2-quart saucepan over very low heat, stirring constantly, until chocolate is melted and smooth. Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla, salt and walnuts.
Spread in 8 x 4-inch or 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Refrigerate 30 minutes or until firm.
Cut into squares.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: fresh vegetable medley
directions: Combine water, butter, salt, pepper and garlic powder in a Dutch oven; bring to a boil. Add carrots; cover, reduce heat, and simmer 5 minutes. Add green pepper, onion, yellow squash and zucchini; cover and simmer 10 minutes. Stir in mushrooms; cover and simmer 3 to 4 minutes; drain. Place vegetables in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish; sprinkle with cheese. Broil just until cheese melts. Yields 8 servings.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Drain string beans and place in casserole dish.
Mix soup with 1/4 cup water or milk.
Stir into string beans.
Top with onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: homemade cake
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, butter and flour and beat until it is smooth.
Pour into a greased pan.

title: roasted red pepper and feta cheese spread
directions: Roast red pepper under the broiler until charred on all sides. Place in a paper bag for 20 minutes.
Peel, remove seeds, wash and chop finely.
Crumble Feta cheese in mixing bowl and add red pepper.
Mix well, adding small amounts of olive oil until blended smoothly.
Serve with crackers or use as celery stuffing.

title: mom's baked beans
directions: We preboil the beans for a short time in baking soda in water to de-gas them and then rinse them off good.
As the beans are cooking for that short time, we throw all the ingredients into our crock-pot (and then add the beans).
Simmer on low all day or overnight for noon meal the next day.
Before serving, we sift in some flour to thicken them up.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix dry ingredients first, then add other ingredients, one at a time.
Stir or mix well after each addition.
Bake for 1 hour at 325° or until top springs back when pushed down.
Keeps well if wrapped in foil.

title: gingerbread with caramel sauce
directions: Mix molasses, soda and spices.
Add sugar, butter, flour and water; beat well.
Add egg yolks and fold in whites.
Pour into a greased ring mold and bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes. (Don't worry if batter seems thin, it's supposed to be.)

title: broccoli puffs
directions: Place unopened broccoli pouch in boiling water.
Do not cover. Bring water to a second vigorous boil and heat for 18 minutes. Empty broccoli and cheese sauce into small bowl and cut broccoli using 2 knives into 1/2-inch pieces.
In medium bowl, combine corn meal, flour, sugar, garlic salt, baking powder and salt.
Stir in broccoli with cheese sauce, milk and egg; batter should be fairly thick.
Allow batter to set 5 to 10 minutes.

title: caramel apple delight
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients using electric mixer.
Use as a dip for apples.
Tastes like caramel apples.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Mix together flour, nuts and butter. Press into 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Let cool.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit and cut into bite sized pieces.
In a double boiler, cook the next 3 ingredients until thick.
Cool.
Add to fruit and refrigerate overnight.
When ready to serve, add whipped cream.

title: spinach mock quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Roll out pie dough to fit into a 9-inch deep dish pie pan.
Defrost spinach, drain and squeeze dry.
In a bowl, combine spinach, cheese, nuts and seasonings.
In a small bowl, beat the egg with the milk.
Add to spinach mixture.
Pour mixture into unbaked pie shell.
Keep filling even around crust. Bake for 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve hot.

title: date loaf candy
directions: Stir sugar and milk together over low heat until sugar is dissolved, then bring to a boil.
Cook until mixture forms a soft ball in water or 238° on thermometer.
Add chopped dates; cook about 5 minutes longer.
Remove and beat thoroughly.
Add nuts and vanilla; beat until stiff enough to mold.
Form in a long roll. Work on covered board with a damp cloth or powdered sugar.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix together and put on top of squash mixture. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender; drain. Add butter and mash. Mix sugar, egg, mayonnaise, pepper, onion, salt and cheese. Add to squash. Pour into buttered casserole and top with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: date cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: swampy salad
directions: Mix everything together in a medium bowl.
Pretend you are a Brachiosaurus hiding in a swamp from a fierce meat-eating dinosaur.

title: carol's extra crispy blueberry crisp
directions: Mix together and place in a baking dish (about 9 x 5-inch). Cover with topping.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, or until brown.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° until golden brown. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: mashed potato rolls
directions: In a mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Add milk, butter, oil, sugar, egg and mashed potatoes; mix well.
Stir in the salt, baking powder, baking soda and enough flour to form a soft dough. Turn onto a floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic, about 6 to 8 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top.

title: perfect yeast bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and let set until it bubbles (about 5 minutes). Stir flour and mix well. Put dough on floured board and knead well. Put in a large bowl with 2 tablespoons oil. Cover with cloth until double in size (about 1 hour). Punch down and divide in 2 pieces. Knead on floured board until smooth. Form into a long roll. Do both pieces. Put in a long greased cookie sheet. Cut about 4 diagonal slits on top. Brush with melted margarine. Let rise about 1 hour. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: microwave beef stroganoff
directions: Stir oil and meat in 2-quart casserole until beef is coated. Cover and microwave until meat is no longer pink (4 to 5 minutes). Remove from casserole and reserve juices.
Add mushrooms and onion to meat juices. Cover, microwave until mushrooms are tender (5 to 6 minutes).
Shake water and flour in covered jar.
Stir in mushrooms.
Microwave to a boil.
Boil for 30 seconds.
Add rest of ingredients.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix 1/4 cup sugar, salt, flour, egg, pineapple juice and vinegar.
Cook, stirring until thick.
Cool.
Add Cool Whip, bananas, pineapple, pears and cherries.
Freeze.
Use aluminum bread pans.
Serve frozen.
Slice and remove what you need and return the rest to freezer.

title: deluxe strawberry pie
directions: Spread two cups of whole raw berries over bottom of cooked pie shell.
Mash remaining two cups of berries; add sugar, cornstarch and baking powder and mix thoroughly.
Put over heat and slowly bring to boil.
Turn heat low and cook, stirring constantly, about 10 minutes or until mixture thickens.
Add a few drops of red food coloring for deep color, if desired.
Cool mixture.
Pour over pie shell.
Cover with whipped cream or cream cheese if desired.

title: strawberry cooler
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Chill for about 1 hour until syrupy.
Pour 1/2 cup gelatin syrup into each of 6 chilled (16 ounce) glasses.
Divide half the ginger ale equally among the glasses.
Stir well.
Divide ice cream equally into glasses and fill with remaining ginger ale.
Garnish with whole strawberries, if desired.

title: vegetable crunch
directions: Mix all ingredients together in dish. Take some Zesta crackers (crumbled) and spread over mixture in dish. Bake at 350° until crackers are golden brown.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken breasts. Cook broccoli.
Mix soup, sour cream, mayonnaise, grated cheese and seasonings.
Drain broccoli and arrange in greased 3-quart casserole. Sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese. Remove skin from chicken and debone. Cut into large pieces and spread over broccoli.
Sprinkle again with Parmesan cheese.
Pour sauce over all.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika. Dot with butter.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven or until bubbly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pork n bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate and serve cold.

title: cereal crunch
directions: Measure into saucepan and boil for 3 minutes.
While hot, pour over cereal and mix well.
Spread on two cookie sheets.
Let cool and break into pieces, then in airtight containers.
For cereal, use bite-size Rice Chex, Wheat Chex, Corn Chex, Kix, Cheerios, pretzels and etc.

title: caramel sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a 2 or 3-quart saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and put in container.
Refrigerate after cooled down.
Microwave when ready for more.
Great for dipping apple slices in it.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Make syrup of sugar, water, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add butter and heat until butter melts.
Pare and core apples and cut in halves.

title: chad and michael's homemade pizza
directions: Roll biscuits out on a pizza pan to form a crust.
Brown hamburger and drain thoroughly.
Spread paste over raw crust evenly.
Sprinkle hamburger over paste.
Top with cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until biscuits are done.

title: monster cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix all ingredients in order. Drop by teaspoons onto cookie sheet and flatten slightly. Bake 12 minutes.

title: 4 minute quail
directions: Soak quail for 4 hours in buttermilk. Drain. Coat with flour, salt and pepper to taste. Deep fry for 4 minutes.

title: taco salad appetizer
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning and spread on large platter.
Place on top of spread, in order: lettuce, tomatoes, black olives, green olives, browned hamburger and Cheddar cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: pickled cucumber salad
directions: Slice cucumber (pickle style). Slice tomatoes and onion into small pieces. Combine all the ingredients. Allow to set for awhile. Refrigerate and serve.

title: spaghetti san giovanni
directions: Peel garlic.
Wash parsley and chop with the garlic.
Chop anchovy filets.
Place in saute pan; oil 1/2 cup and when very hot, add mixture.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste and 1/2 cup water (hot). Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook on high for 5 minutes, then add capers.
Cook for a few more minutes, then toss over cooked spaghetti.

title: dilled onions
directions: Place first 5 ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Do not boil but a second.
Pour over sliced onions.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator at least overnight.
Stores well in refrigerator.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Place margarine in large oblong pan.
Melt in oven as you mix other ingredients.
Stir eggs into persimmon pulp and sugar. Alternate milk, flour, baking powder and salt.
Add margarine last.
Pour back in pan.
Sprinkle with nuts (optional).
Bake in 375° oven 45 minutes or until firm.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: bologna sandwich
directions: Spread mayonnaise on 1 bread.
Put a slice of cheese, then 1 bologna, then one more slice of cheese, then the other bologna. Put the lettuce on next and top with bread.
Eat the sandwich with a big pickle.

title: oriental-chicken salad(unusual and delicious)
directions: Toast sesame seed and almonds until golden.
Set aside. Combine salad oil, rice wine vinegar, lemon juice, sesame seed oil, sugar, salt and pepper.
In a large bowl, combine cabbage, onions, noodles and chicken.
Toss well.
Add dressing.
Toss again.
Marinate overnight for best flavor.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: vanilla brownies
directions: Cream the first 4 ingredients.
Combine and add dry ingredients.
Bake in an oblong pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cut while warm.

title: dream circle cake
directions: Grease 2 (8-inch) cake pans; dust with flour.
Mix orange cake mix, orange jello, Crisco oil, eggs and water and beat for 3 minutes.
Pour in pans and cook 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Let cool in pans 10 minutes.
Put on cake rack; cool.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Cut shrimp into small pieces. Mix all ingredients together well.
Chill.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Blend cake mix, 2 eggs and margarine well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend the next 4 ingredients; pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: peach cobbler deluxe
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13 baking dish.
Mix next 5 ingredients and pour into buttered dish.
Pour peaches on top of batter, do not stir.
Batter will rise up over peaches to make crust.
Bake at 375 degrees for about 45 minutes until golden brown.
Cool and serve.

title: orange smoothies
directions: Mix all the ingredients together in a blender.
Yields four 8 ounce servings.

title: citrus spice marinade(for flank steak or grilled veggies!)
directions: In a screw-top jar combine orange juice, lemon juice, cooking oil, Worcestershire sauce, garlic, cumin, onion powder, salt and pepper.
Cover; shake to mix.
If using on veggies mix together with veggies; top with Feta cheese and walnuts.
If using for meat marinade as you normally would.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: In large heavy saucepan, mix sugar, cornstarch, salt and cocoa. Gradually stir in milk until smooth.
Stir over medium to medium-low heat until mixture thickens and comes to a boil. Gradually blend a little chocolate mixture into yolks; add to remaining chocolate mixture.
Stir over very low heat 2 to 3 minutes longer or until slightly thicker.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.

title: biscuit topped italian casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 12 x 8-inch dish.
In a large skillet, brown beef and onion; drain.
Stir in water, pepper, tomato sauce and paste.
Simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vegetables and 1/2 cup of cheese.
Spoon in a baking dish.
Separate the biscuits into 10.
Place bread near outer edge, overlapping.
Sprinkle cheese in center and around the edge.
Gently brush butter on biscuits. Sprinkle with oregano.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken soup
directions: Wash chicken.
Place chicken in pot with just enough water to cover.
Add parsley, celery, carrot, onion and all seasonings. Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 hours or until thickest pieces are fork-tender.
When not serving immediately, allow chicken to cool in broth.
If using pressure cooker, cook at 15 pounds for 20 minutes.
When cool, remove meat from bones and skin.
Makes about 5 cups cubed, cooked chicken and 5 to 6 cups broth.

title: cooked green pumpkin
directions: Put water in pan.
Add vinegar and salt.
Bring to a boil. Add pumpkin and cook until transparent.

title: s.o.s. - creamed ground beef on toast(100 portions)
directions: Brown ground beef; drain fat when browning.
Put in 1 1/2 quarts water.
Harden grease and put water liquid back with meat. Blend together dry milk and 3 1/2 gallons cold water and add to ground beef.
Blend together flour and 2 1/2 quarts water until lump-free.
Add gradually to ground beef after the ground beef and milk are hot.
Add enough for gravy texture.
Cook until thickened.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add Worcestershire sauce.

title: easy vegetable barley soup
directions: Cook onion and garlic in oil until tender in a 4-quart saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 45 to 50 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes 10 one-cup servings.

title: strawberry sauce(ice cream, pancakes, waffles)
directions: Slice 1 cup of the berries; puree 1 cup in your blender.
Set aside.
In a small saucepan, combine and cook cornstarch, sugar and water, stirring constantly.
When smooth and sugar dissolves, stir in pureed berries and sliced berries.
Bring to a boil and continue stirring constantly.
Should boil 1 minute.
Add lemon juice; stir until slightly thickened.
Serve hot.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain and add seasoning and sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Layer a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with corn chips. Pour meat mixture over chips and sprinkle with grated cheese. Cook 20 minutes at 375°.

title: frito casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain fat.
Add canned items.
Let simmer 20 minutes.
In deep dish pan, line bottom with crushed Fritos, meat sauce and top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven until cheese is melted.

title: vegetable or chip dip
directions: Mix together and chill for at least 1 hour before serving.

title: baked meringues
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy (balloon whisk or hand hand beaters work best).
Add cream of tartar, salt and vanilla; beat until soft peaks form.
Add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, continually beating to form stiff peaks.
Pipe onto cookie sheet to form teardrop shapes.
Bake in a preheated 225° oven for 2 to 3 hours, or in a 275° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Be sure to line cookie sheet with foil.
When meringues are dried, let cool before removing from cookie sheet.
May be stored in an airtight container for 4 to 6 weeks.

title: potato salad
directions: Cut up potatoes and eggs; add other ingredients as listed.

title: very good dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook on low in crock-pot.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Have cheese at room temperature.
Add Coke a little at a time until well mixed with electric mixer.
Drain juice from cherries and pineapple.
Heat to dissolve jello.
Cool.
Add mixture to cheese and Coke.
Add nuts, pineapple and cherries.
Mix well with a spoon.
Place in refrigerator until congealed.

title: fruit compote
directions: (Fresh fruit and melons may be substituted for canned fruit when in season.)
Drain fruit and mix thoroughly.
Whip cranberry sauce with a wire whisk and pour sauce over fruit.
Mix thoroughly and refrigerate.

title: lemon poppy seed muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Cream together the butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour mixture alternately with sour cream and lemon juice.
Add vanilla, poppy seed and lemon zest.
Grease muffin tins and fill two-thirds full with batter.
For large muffins, bake 18 to 20 minutes; for mini muffins, bake 12 to 14 minutes.

title: never fail divinity
directions: Cook sugar, syrup
and	water
until
it
spins
a good thread (about 20
minutes).
Gradually beat half of syrup into the beaten egg whites.
Return other half of syrup to fire and cook until it forms a hard ball in cold water (about 10 or 15 minutes).
Beat slowly
into
the first mixture.
Add vanilla and beat
vigorously until candy will hold its shape.
Drop by teaspoon onto
buttered dish or waxed paper and top each piece with a pecan half.

title: sweet potato surprise
directions: Place sweet potatoes in greased baking dish.
In saucepan, combine brown sugar, cornstarch, salt, cinnamon and orange peel. Drain apricots, reserving syrup.
Stir 1 cup of syrup into cornstarch mixture.
Cook and stir over medium heat until boiling. Boil 2 minutes.
Add apricots, butter and pecans.
Pour over sweet potatoes.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: payday bars
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil.
Add peanut butter and mix well.
Add peanuts and Rice Chex.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool and cut into squares.

title: easy chocolate turtle pie
directions: Spread caramel topping on bottom of crust. Sprinkle with pecans. Refrigerate.
Stir pudding mix into milk in medium saucepan.
Stirring constantly, cook on medium heat until mixture comes to full boil.
Remove from heat. Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Pour into crust.
Refrigerate 3 hours.

title: e-z serve punch
directions: Combine sugar and water; stir until dissolved.
Heat to boiling and cool.
Add and mix remaining ingredients; freeze.

title: cinnamon bars
directions: Cream the margarine and brown sugar. Add the beaten eggs, then the dry ingredients, coconut and pecans. Put in a 3-quart casserole or 17 x 11 x 3/4-inch pan that has been greased and floured. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Cream oleo or oil and sugar together.
Add egg, vanilla and sour milk, beat thoroughly.
Sift flour and dry ingredients.
Blend into other.
Spoon in pan 9x13x2-inch Pyrex.
Sprinkle chocolate chips (1/4 cup) and nuts.
Bake 45 minutes in 325 degree oven.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter,
add beaten egg yolks, milk, salt, and beat well.
Crumble crackers very fine and mix with baking powder and add to sugar/butter mixture.
Add vanilla and fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into 2 round greased layer cake tins.
Bake 20 minutes at 325°.

title: blond brownies
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine flour with melted margarine, sugar and eggs.
Spread in pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.

title: dirt pie
directions: Grind cookies until it looks like dirt.
Best to use a food processor; set aside.
Mix butter, sugar and cheese in a small mixing bowl.
Mix pudding, milk and Cool Whip in a large mixing bowl, then combine the 2 mixtures in a large bowl.
Layer cookies, then mixture in medium size flowerpot with cookies as last layer. Put gummy worms on top and an artificial flower, if desired.
Can even serve with a new garden spade for more fun.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt, baking soda and salt together. Add remaining ingredients, except cranberries and nuts.
Mix well until blended.
Stir in cranberries and nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool on rack 5 minutes; remove from pan.

title: poppy seed pound cake
directions: In small bowl, stir poppy seed and buttermilk.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in eggs and vanilla.
In large bowl on high speed, beat margarine and sugar until smooth.
Combine flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Blend milk.
Mix flour mix into margarine until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, until toothpick comes out clean.
Drizzle with glaze.

title: yampone
directions: Peel yams and grate if using fresh. Stir together the yams and melted butter. Add eggs, beating after each one. Add milk, molasses and vanilla. In another dish, stir together flour, salt, cinnamon, sugar and nutmeg. Add to yam mixture and blend well. Pour into a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours, stirring several times during
the first hour. Serve hot or cold. May be reheated.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind pears, onions and peppers.
Cook 30 minutes or less on low heat.
Drain.
Heat vinegar, sugar and spices on low heat. Add salt, then pears, peppers, onions and pineapple.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Put in jars.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese together.
Add sugar; cream well. Beat in 6 eggs, one at a time.
Add sifted flour and flavorings. Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Put in cold oven; set at 350°.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.
Test with a toothpick to see if done.
(Have butter, cream cheese and eggs at room temperature.)

title: chess pie
directions: Blend all ingredients together and pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in preheated oven.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Combine margarine and lemon juice.
Brush chicken with mixture.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place in baking dish. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Combine rice, chicken broth and water in medium saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 5 minutes or until broth is absorbed.
Serve next to baked chicken.

title: velveeta cheese candy
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and nuts in large bowl.
Make a hole the size of a smaller bowl in the middle of the mix.
Melt cheese and margarine in a pan with a wooden spoon.
Add vanilla.
Pour into hole and mix fast.
Pour into two 10 x 14-inch buttered pans.
Pat out with buttered hands.
Makes 8 pounds.
I quit making fudge years ago when I got this recipe from my sister-in-law in Louisiana.

title: wilma's never fail pie crust
directions: Sift together the flour and salt.
Add and mix in Crisco.
Add beaten egg, vinegar and cold water; mix well.
This is enough dough for 3 pies.
Divide dough into 3 balls.
Refrigerate to cool before rolling out.
You may roll out, place in pie pans and freeze for later use.

title: pink perfections
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Add 1 cup cherry pie filling.
Chill before serving.

title: chunky beef soup
directions: Mix together water, beef broth, beef, tomato juice, sugar and salt.
Bring to a boiling point.
Brown hamburger in onion and butter.
Add this then to boiling juice, then add frozen vegetables.
I double the juice part.
Makes 10 quarts.
Very good.
